ID: QXCR1001532051

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Strygin,Maxim [maxim.strygin@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The previous version of Cloud Interconnect Server (VNF Manager) did not support a High Availability feature. Therefore, it was considered as a single point of failure.

Resolution:

Cloud Interconnect Server has been extended to support High Availability setup. A dedicated set of tools have been added to manage CIS instances in HA setup. For more information, see the eIUM Virtualization User Guide.

Submitter Text Notes:

Based on the initial planning and feedback from customers, High Availability setup and mode is a high want requirement for Cirrus Server.

Test Info Notes:

â€¢ List of suggested new test cases Standalone setup should remain unaffected 1) Install and configure CIS normally, it should operate as before.

Failure use case 2.1) Install more than one CIS servers and configure them to use the same remote Database (as alternative, one may configure database replication). 2.2 Register at least two CIS servers to join HA cluster in standby mode. 2.3 In standby mode, no operations except user authentication, version and HA should be available. 2.4 Switch one of the CIS server into the Active mode. 2.5 Use its URL to perform all operations as usual. 2.6 Get the list of servers participating in HA. 2.7 Disconnect the VM where active CIS is running (or kill the process to imitate hard failure). 2.8 Using URL of the different CIS server (information available from the list request), request it to become ACTIVE. 2.9 All operations should become available on the newly activated CIS server. 2.10 Get the list of servers participating in HA. There should be only one ACTIVE CIS, the previous one should be marked as Standby.

Maintenance use case 3.1 Repeat all the steps from 2.1 to 2.6. 3.2 Login to the CIS server from CLI tool 3.3 Subscribe for alarms and KPIs 3.4 Initiate switch over from the current machine to another one 3.5 Get the list of servers participating in HA. The previously active CIS should become Standby. 3.6 Previously Active CIS should not accept further operations except user authentication, version and HA should be available. 3.7 In 5 minutes, all login session and notification subscriptions (KPIs, alarms, etc) should be terminated

â€¢ Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix Kill CIS process or shutdown the VM, there is no way to continue managing VNFs via CIS.

â€¢ Sample configurations that may help implementing test cases (may be an attachment) Attachments include examples of the input/output messages for Restful API HA dedicated operations, Postman Collection, and the document explaining HA of the CIS.

ID: QXCR1001531247

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

There should be a separate command to secure, unsecure, and update HTTPS for web applications in eIUM.

Resolution:

The new command "secactivate webapp" has been created to handle this for web applications, using the arguments "-secure", "-unsecure", and "-httpsupdate". For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

Test Info Notes:

"seactivate init" does not activate any web applications now. -hybrid option has been removed from the "secactivate init" arguments. New command "secactivate webapp" has been added which will secure, unsecure and update https certificates whenever needed.

The command Synopsis is: webapp [[-secure] | [-unsecure] | [-httpsupdate]] [-hybrid] [-server <security server host>] [- storepass <host keystore password>] [-identities <identities to be updated with keystore>] [-httpsport <https port>] -certificateKeystoreFile <certificate keystore file> -certificateKeystorePassword <password for keystore> -certificateKeystoreType <type for keystore>

-secure : Arguments [-hybrid] [-server <security server host>] [-storepass <host keystore password>] deals with securing web applications.

-unsecure : Unsecures web applications

-httpsupdate : Arguments [-identities <identities to be updated with keystore>] [-httpsport <https port>] -certificateKeystoreFile <certificate keystore file> -certificateKeystorePassword <password for keystore> -certificateKeystoreType <type for keystore> deals with updating the https port and certificate keystore details.

By default the identities is optional and the default value is : webappserver

This means the -httpsupdate command updates the %VARROOT%/webappserver/conf/server.xml

In future if new identities added (like licenseserver) then the -identities option can be specified as -identities "webappserver,licenseserver" or -identities "licenseserver" and the corresponding folder under %VARROT%/<identities>/conf/server.xml

Activator has been enhanced to ask for https details on web applications activation screen. This provision will be there even if the deployment is secure or unsecure.

> Make sure activating security from activator also activates web applications. (Even though internally it has been split into 2 commands but it should be invisible to customer who is activating security from activator)

> Make sure de-activating security from activator also de-activates web applications. (Even though internally it has been split into 2 commands but it should be invisible to customer who is de- activating security from activator)

> Make sure if the external web application certificates are provided on webapplication screen under HttpsUpdate flag then the same is getting updated for all web applications under webappserver.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC6
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
==============
It was verified that securing webapps action moved to new command from init.

ID: QXCR1001531202

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The JsonResponseGenerator ResponseRootElement attribute is a multi-valued configuration attribute, allowing multiple types of JSON responses to be sent. The VirtualRoot configuration attribute, however, is not, and hides only one root element.

Resolution:

VirtualRoot has been made a multi-valued configuration attribute. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

JsonResponseGenerator.ResponseRootElement is a multi valued configuration attribute. That means it can generate multiple JSON messages with different root elements. But VirtualRoot (which hides the root element) takes only one value. It should be made multiple to hide the multiple ResponseRootElements.

Test Info Notes:

Configure JsonResponseGenerator with multiple ResponseRootElements. This will allow it to generate responses with different root elements. You should use EncodeAttribute to specify which root to use each time. Now configure VirtualRoot with the same multiple values as ResponseRootElement. This will make each of those responses to hide their respective root elements.

Verifier:

==========

* Start the session server.
* Send the below siuinvoke request to test all the cases mentioned under "TestCases"
	./siuinvoke -n JSON -rulechain SendRequest -data RequestType post

===========

not configured.

configured.

3. Verify the behavior when the ResponseRootElement is configured to multiple root elements and 
VirtualRoot is not configured.

VirtualRoot is configured to a single root element which is not part of the response.

5. Verify the behavior when the ResponseRootElement is configured to multiple root elements and 
VirtualRoot is configured to a single root element which is part of the response.

6. Verify the behavior when the ResponseRootElement is configured to multiple root elements and 
VirtualRoot is also configured multiple root elements as in ResponseRootElement.

ID: QXCR1001531043

Engineer: Nair,Rajesh P [rajeshn@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a a new login module for the eIUM security server, which can search and find a user dn using a privileged user identity and credential. The discovered user dn should be used to authenticate the user.

Resolution:

The new ExternalDirectoryLoginModule login module has been implemented to search and bind a user identity.

Submitter Text Notes:

This enhancement is related to eIUM security server infrastructure. In addition to the existing LdapDirectoryLoginModule , provide an alternate ldap login module implementation that uses searches for locating the user to bind.

The search could be performed using a more privileged user , locate the user to authenticate (bind) using a configurable filter, perform the bind using the discovered user dn.

Test Info Notes:

Please see the example configuration provided. The login module need to be configured with a prviliged user that can search under the root context for a user id.

Store user entries under a organization unit node that is different from the configured user_context_pattern in the external-dir.properties. Verify that the user authentication works using ExternalDirectoryLoginModule.

ID: QXCR1001530330

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The TimeAdornmentRule ShiftTime attribute did not compensate for time gain or loss during DST begin or end. It added the configured time (say 24 hours), even though there are 25 hours during a DST end. This resulted in a destination time being one hour earlier than expected.

Resolution:

The new AdjustmentForDST configuration attribute has been added, which when set to 60, adds an hour to ShiftTime during DST end, and deducts one hour during DST beginning. This will add 25 hours instead of 24 hours during DST end, compensating for the extra hour gained. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

TimeAdornmentRule ShiftTime attribute is not working correctly during DST timezone switch. For e.x, in Rogers, the config is

#@ ClassName=com.hp.siu.collector.rules.TimeAdornmentRule #@ ParseTimeString=Gx_CurrentBillCycleStartDateString,Gx_SPStartDateTimeTime,yyyyMMdd #@ ParseTimeString=Gx_CurrentBillCycleEndDateString,Gx_SPEndDateTimeTime,yyyyMMdd #@ ShiftTime=Gx_SPEndDateTimeTime,Gx_DurationTempInteger,Gx_SPEndDateTimeTime,h #@ TimeZone=America/Toronto

and the duration value Gx_DurationTempInteger is set to 24hrs. During DST in Nov, it triggered the bill cycle at 11:00pm on the DST switch day and on March, the shift time will be 1:00am the next day. What we need is the shifttime compute the next day at 12:00pm every day.

This issue is in 70FP01Rogers branch.

More details in the following email thread:

From: Kandasamy, Jayaseelan Sent: Tuesday, December 06, 2016 10:36 AM To: S, RamaKoteswararao <ramakoteswararao.s@hpe.com>; Bal, Sangram Kes <sangram.bal@hpe.com> Cc: PDL-IUM-Rogers-DSR-SMS-Team <ium-rogers-dsr.sms@hpe.com>; Gnidziejko, Karen <karen.gnidziejko@hpe.com>; Yao, Nai-Rong <nai-rong.yao@hpe.com>; Kim, Suntae <suntae.kim@hpe.com> Subject: RE: #1709 - 5315434794 - IMT.1612.001988 - Large number of pre-active/initial accounts on bill cycle 4

Hi Ram,

Here the root cause is the DST window fall on the bill cycle. While performing bill cycle start/end date calculation if the start date fall in DST windows then epoch time tagged with GMT-4 and if it is outside of the DST window then the epoch time tagged with GMT-5. Below are the lab test data. If you look at carefully the start date fall in DSST window so it tagged with GMT -4 whereas the Endtime out of the DST windows so it tagged GMT -5 even though we did the test on yesterday which is outside of DST.

The DST for this year starts from Mar 13 to Nov 06 at 2 AM. The end time calculation in IUM End date + 24 hours so it becomes Nov 6 +24 (20161106 +24 GMT-4). We were not considering and DST window in our calculation. Hence we need to consider these DST window and adjust the hours (add 25 hrs/23 hrs) for SP end time accordingly to avoid this issue. Otherwise this will occurs early twice of DST on/off.

Impact: Bill cycle triggered 1 hour ahead and deleted all the account. Next Gx came for few of the accounts at the end of 23:00 hour on Nov 06 and those accounts became activated and rest all in status ???P???.

Hi Jayaseelan,

I tried to get all of the SPM recovery records for a few accounts we were investigating. It looks like the issue with bill cycle 4 is related to daylight savings time.

DST ended on Nov 6, with clocks going back by 1 hour, meaning that the 6th actually had 25 hours in the day. It looks like the bill cycle renewal job ran one hour early, at Nov 6 23:00 EST, but the new bill cycle start time was calculated as Nov 7 00:00 EST. It seems like the system then deleted all of these accounts and they eventually were re-added in P or I status during Gx.

Can we get a detailed analysis on what occurred here? We also need to ensure it does not happen again on Dec 6/7 renewal.

Dan

Test Info Notes:

Configure TimeAdornmentRule as below

ClassName=TimeAdornmentRule ParseTimeString=SrcHost,StartTime,MM/dd/yyyy HH:mm:ss ShiftTime=StartTime,Duration,EndTime,h,+ FormatStrings=EndTime,DstHost,MM/dd/yyyy HH:mm:ss,TimeZone TimeZone=America/Toronto

Pass an NME with SrcHost = 11/05/2016 10:00:00 Duration = 24 TimeZone=America/Toronto

First ParseTimeString will convert the SrcHost into time in StartTime. Then ShiftTime will add 24h to it and store it in EndTime. Then FormatStrings will format it back to human readable form in DstHost. You will see

DstHost = 11/06/2016 09:00:00

It is one hour lesser because DST ended on 5th Nov and one hour was added to that day, making it 25 hours. With the new configuration attribute AdjustmentForDST set to 60, 25 hours will be added instead of the configured 24h, making

DstHost = 11/06/2016 10:00:00

ID: QXCR1001529755

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

JDS is currently using non-standard database configuration format. Namely, instead of defining corresponding Environment variables under /deployment/Environment or /deployment/host/Environment, database parameters are written directly into JDSStoreService config node.

This should be changed to use approach consistent with other databases: JDS_DATABASEURL, JDS_DATABASECLASS, JDS_DATABASEUSER and JDS_DATABASEPASSWORD as Environment variables on the host level. These variables should be referenced in the JDSStoreService template.

Test Info Notes:

Please ensure that:

- after activating IUM 9.0 with JDS enabled, JDS_... variables are added under /deployment/<host>/Environment - in JDSStoreService configuration node, database parameters are specified as variable references ${JDS_...} instead of raw values - JDS is able to start correctly and connect to database

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001529712

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Popov,Alexey [alexey.popov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

AVPDecoderHolder/StructuredAVPDecoderHolder should be able to skip mandatory AVPs in a message without decoding.

Resolution:

The new CheckMandatoryAVP configuration attribute has been added in AVPDecoderHolder and StructuredAVPDecoderHolder. If the attribute is set to false, AVPDecoderHolder/StructuredAVPDecoderHolder can skip mandatory AVPs in decoding without generating errors. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

If AVPDecoderHolder/StructuredAVPDecoderHolder is used as a partial decoder, it should be possible to skip a mandatory AVP in a message without generating MandatoryAVPUnsupportedException.

Test Info Notes:

1. Create Diameter Server with AVPDecoderHolder. Set CheckMandatoryAVP to false in AVPDecoderHolder.

Run the server and send a request with a mandatory AVP, which is not cofigured in AVPDecoderHolder. The server should send back the regular answer.

Set CheckMandatoryAVP to true in AVPDecoderHolder.

Run the server and send a request with a mandatory AVP, which is not cofigured in AVPDecoderHolder. The server should send back an error answer with DIAMETER_AVP_UNSUPPORTED (5001) result code.

2. Repeat the same test for StructuredAVPDecoderHolder.

ID: QXCR1001528740

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

LoopRule Does Not Support Infinite Number of Retries

Resolution:

LoopRule now Supports Infinite Number of Retries by configuring RetryCount=-1 in configuration

Submitter Text Notes:

LoopRule needs to support infinite number of retries. Currently user need to configure very big value for the RetryCount. It is required to provide an option to configure RetryCount=-1 which would mean infinite loop. I such case the loop will stop only when ExitConditions are met. ======================================================================================

// Chandan.V 17th Mar, 2017

The RetryCount is not working as expected when configured to -1 and shall be moved back to Development state.

Without patch It will never execute the logic even once.

ID: QXCR1001527604

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Popov,Alexey [alexey.popov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

It is required to check in the ConditionalRule that one ListAttribute contains elements of another ListAttribute.

Resolution:

Two new operations are introduced in ConditionalRule: 1) "containsAll" checks that a list NME attribute contains all elements of another list NME attribute; and 2) "!containsAll" checks that a list NME attribute does not contain some elements of another list NME attribute. The same operations could be used in FilterRule, ConditionFlushTester, SwitchConditionRule, and NMEAttributeValidationPostProcessor. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

It is required to check in ConditionalRule that one ListAttribute contains elements of another ListAttribute.

Test Info Notes:

Create collector/session server that use ConditionalRule with containsAll and !containsAll operations for ListAttributes. Check that these operations are executed correctly according to their descriptions.

Repeat the test for FilterRule, ConditionFlushTester, SwitchConditionRule, NMEAttributeValidationPostProcessor.

Symptoms:

HTTPProtocol doesn't support incoming and outgoing request throughput count in server and client mode respectively.

Resolution:

HTTPProtocol now supports incoming and outgoing request throughput count in server and client mode respectively.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently HTTPProtocol doesn't support incoming and outgoing request throughput count in server and client mode respectively. It needs to support these features.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup: 1)Please find the attached HttpClient and HttpServer config files for the test setup. Both are TCPConnector using HttpProtocol component in client and server mode respectively.

2) For this test two license files are needed. One license file without HTTP-based connector and another with HTTP-based connector premium component.

3) Please refer to the images to know how to enable HTTP-base connector component while applying an IUM 9.0 license.

Test Scenario 1:(License with HTTP component enabled)

Test Case 1: When both the HTTP client and server starts running, under MBeans of HTTPClient and HTTPserver, there should appear an entry as Licensing=HttpProtocol. Licensing=HttpProtocol MBean should have two attributes under it. They are IncomingRequestThroughput and OutgoingRequestThroughput. These attributes represent number of messages/second sent and received by corresponding components. However both the attributes are not applicable for both Http client and server.

Test Case 2: For HttpServer only IncomingRequestThroughput is incremented and for client only OutgoingRequestThroughput Mbean attribute is incremented.

Test Case 3: Suppose the license is applied for 10 and 10 as outgoing and incoming throughput for Http and the number of sending and receiving messages per second crosses 10 in the runtime, then an alarm should be generated. The licensing Server should be able to view it.

Test Scenario 2:(License WITHOUT HTTP component enabled)

Test Case 1: When both the HTTP client and server starts running, under MBeans of HTTPClient and HTTPserver, NO entry should appear as Licensing=HttpProtocol. There should be no IncomingRequestThroughput and OutgoingRequestThroughput MBean attributes enabled.

Test Case 2: The HttpProtocol component should run as is before. (A regression run is required after this change.)

Test Case 3: TestCase 2 and TestCase 3 of Test Scenario 1 are not applicable here.

ID: QXCR1001526573

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Mail from Maxim Patrushev =========================

We need all the user interfaces in eIUM (including CLI) to force user login/authentication whenever Security or Security Hybrid mode activated in IUM. Programmatically, you should check for the following condition:

If(SIUInfo.isSecure() || SIUInfo.isMixedSecurity()) { // force user to login â€¦ } else { // the system unsecure â€¦ }

The difference between Hybrid/Mixed and Secure modes is that the latter assumes that all IUM services and communication secure and require SSL. On the contrary, in the Hybrid mode all the services in IUM are being unsecure (no SSL), but the end user must authenticate in order to access the tools and interfaces.

Basically, all you need to support the Hybrid mode is to force user login. Everything else will be similar to the regular unsecure mode.

Test Info Notes:

Install IUM in hybrid security mode. Execute any IUM command. They should work only when username and password are provided.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC3
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
============

It was verified that login is mandatory now for CLI tools web apps in case of Hybrid/Mixed security
enabled.

ID: QXCR1001526231

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Aithal G,Hrashikesha [hrashikesha.g@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

NME and SNME in the log file were printed on different lines, that is, by default the newline character was used as a separator character between NME and SNME. The separator character needs to be user-configurable.

Resolution:

The new NmeSnmeSeparatorCharacter configuration attribute has been added, which can take any string, escape sequences, or Unicode values, which will be used as separator characters between NME and SNME during logging. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

NME and SNME should be printed in log file with user defined separator character. Initially default file systems's new line character(\n or \r\n) was being place between NME and SNME, in short NME and SNME printed in different lines. Now it is required to have a user defined character(either new line, tab or space or with Unicode ) or special character (like :or ; or , or -) or user defined string in between NME and SNME.

Test Info Notes:

List of suggested new test cases - Need to test in different scenarios like 1. Have set of NMEs in a configuration , set values for each NME and have a LogNMERule after values are set. 2. Have set of SNMEs in a configuration , set values for each SNME and have a LogNMERule after values are set. 3. Have set of NMEs and SNMEs in a configuration , set values for each NME and SNME and have a LogNMERule after values are set.

All three cases should be tested with NmeSnmeSeparatorCharacter config attribute set to \n(or unicode \u000A), \t(or unicode \u0009) , blank space(or unicode \u0020) (one or more), any other special character like colon(:), semi colon(;), period(.), hyphen(-) or any other special character or with user defined string

All three cases should be tested with NmeSnmeSeparatorCharacter config attribute not configured.

All the above scenarios should be tested SingleLineSNME attribute set to true and also false.

Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix - To Reproduce: Create a config having set of NME and SNME with some AdonmentRule to set values to all. Have a LogNMERule after values set.

Before fix:When Rule get executed, NME and SNME will be printed in different line in respective log file

After fix : When Rule get executed, NME and SNME will be printed with configured NmeSnmeSeparatorCharacter as separator character.

Sample configurations that may help implementing test cases (may be an attachment) - Attached SampleConfig.config

Any other information or warnings or comments that need to be conveyed to the QA Engineer that will verify the defect - NA

Verifier: 

Test Plan:
-----------

* Load the attached config "SNMETest.Config" and merge the config "nme.config"
* Also Load the attached "Openstack_TokenRequest.xfd" in the Repository as below
-Open IUMStudio--->Connect--->CheckOut--->Under Datamodel--->User--->Place the file 
"Openstack_TokenRequest.xfd" and save it--->Check in.
* Start the config "SNMETest.Config"
* Accordingly configure LOGNme's for "NmeSnmeSeparatorCharacter" and test different cases

Note: Also have configured for "SingleLineSNME=true" and Tested
Checked the scenarios both on Linux and Windows Machines

ID: QXCR1001526029

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Chen,Ming [ming.chen5@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The Decision Table feature should support IPV6 regular expressions.

Resolution:

The new IPv6RegExp data type was added to support the following IPV6 regular expressions:

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:e921:a333:ff5e:fd3b -> fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:e921:a333:ff5e:fd3b

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:*:*:*:* -> fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:[0x0000-0xffff]: [0x0000-0xffff]: [0x0000- 0xffff]: [0x0000-0xffff]

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:b3ff:95af:[123a,123f]:(999a,999f] -> fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:b3ff:95af:123a:999b,fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:b3ff:95af:123f:999f and so on.

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee::fd3b -> fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:0000:0000:0000:fd3b

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:fd3b:9fd0:192.168.1.* ->fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:fd3b:9fd0:192.168.1.1, fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:fd3b:9fd0:192.168.1.2 and so on.

fd4e:316e:e84a:a4e0::/60 -> fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ee:b3ff:95af:123a:999b,fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ef:b3ff:95af:123f:999f, fd4e:316e:e84a:a4ea:b3ff:95af:123f:ffff and so on.

Submitter Text Notes:

support ipv6 regex

ID: QXCR1001524449

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Tsoukanov,Victor [victor.tsoukanov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

It was not possible to clear multiple alarms in the Operations Console.

Resolution:

Multiple alarms can now be acknowledged and cleared simultaneously in the Operations Console. For example, on the Alarms panel for a process, you can select particular alarms using check boxes, and acknowledge or clear them using the context menu selection "Ack/Clear Selected", respectively. Along with selected alarms, you can also acknowledge or clear all alarms using the corresponding context menu selection "Ack/Clear All".

Submitter Text Notes:

Please, add the checkboxes and the new style group menu at the title of the last Action column, as we do for the Deployment view. This menu should have the only item "Clear" to clear select alarm(s)

Test Info Notes:

Check if there is a new menu in alarm table header with items to acknowledge and clear all or selected alarms. Check if it works as expected

Verifier: 

Release: 90(rc3)
=================
New menu in alarm table header appeared, see pict attached. 

It was checked that:

- "Ack Selected", "Clear Selected", "Ack All", "Clear All" new operations could be applied.
- Ack and Clear old operations for each alarm continue working.
- no alarms were acknowledged/cleared using operations "Ack Selected"/"Clear Selected" if no
checkboxes were selected.

ID: QXCR1001523471

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Sharma,Surendra [surendra.sharma@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

A licensing limit will be imposed on RadiusAdapter: 1) If RadiusAdapter is configured as a server, a throughput license policy will be applied on the number of requests received by the server. If the license limit is reached, in the Operations Console interface, an alarm will be activated. The adapter will still work and will not be stopped; 2) If RadiusAdapter is configured as client, a throughput license policy will be applied on the number of requests sent by this client. If the license limit is reached, in the Operations Console interface, an alarm will be activated. The adapter will still work and will not be stopped; and 3) If no throughput is mentioned while requesting license, then there will not be any business logic executed to calculate or publish the throughput limit.

Resolution:

Users can create an eIUM license with the throughput value for the RadiusAdapter. If the throughput is provided in the license, then this limitation will be applied on the RadiusAdapter. The same license throughput limitation is also applicable for DiameterAdapter.

Submitter Text Notes:

Licensing limit will be imposed on Radius adapter. 1. If Radius adapter is configured as server. Throughput license policy will be applied on the number of request received by the server. If license limit crosses, on Ops UI alarm will be activated. Adapter will still work and will not be stopped. 2. If Radius adapter is configured as client. Throughput license policy will be applied on the number of request sent by this client. If license limit crosses, on Ops UI alarm will be activated. Adapter will still work and will not be stopped. 3. If no throughout is mentioned while requesting license. There will not be any business logic executed to calculate or publish the throughput limit.

Test Info Notes:

Test case 1: Radius as server ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ 1. Request license with throughput threshold values. 2. Configure radius adapter as server. 3. Start the radius server. 4. Send requests less than throughput threshold value. 5. On Ops UI there should not be any alarm. 6. Increase the request load such that server crosses the throughput threshold value. 7. On Ops UI it will show alarm.

Test case 2: Radius as client ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ 1. Request license with throughput threshold values. 2. Configure radius adapter as client. 3. Start the radius client. 4. Send requests less than throughput threshold value. 5. On Ops UI there should not be any alarm. 6. Increase the request load such that client crosses the throughput threshold value. 7. On Ops UI it will show alarm.

Test case 3: License with no throughout threshold value ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ 1. Request license without throughput threshold values. 2. Configure radius adapter as server. 3. Start the radius server. 4. On Ops UI there should not be any alarm.

Test case 4: License with no throughout threshold value ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ 1. Request license without throughput threshold values. 2. Configure radius adapter as client. 3. Start the radius client. 4. On Ops UI there should not be any alarm.

Verifier: 

IUM Version : 90 Tissot (RC5)
Test Status : PASS

kpi=class:RadiusLicensingStats,group:Licensing,attribute:OutgoingRequestThroughput,threshold:5
3.Start the RadiusClient/RadiusServer

<HostName>/<RadiusClient_01>/IUM.Here you can see the mbean for licensing:RadiusProtocolAdapter

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The Cloud Interconnect Server (CIS) feature from eIUM 9.0 should support integration with VNFs instantiated by VNFM from eIUM83 Feature Pack 1.

Resolution:

Apart from the "vnfdmigrate" command for VNFD migration to version 2, there is a new "vdd" command in "cistools" for import and export details about instantiated VNFs. For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

Allow the user to migrate (import) data from existing VNFM installation (IUM 8.3 FP01) to new VNFM/Cirrus installation (IUM 9.0).

This should be an optional operation and performed as part of activation procedure.

Test Info Notes:

Verify that vdd command from "cistools" (aka vnfmtools) can be used for doing export/import operations on particular VNFs as it's described in command ref. As a test scenario we can assume the following:

1) take CIS with some instantiated and scaled VNF 2) export that VNF to VDD file 3) create new VNF identifier 4) import VDD file for new VNF identifier 5) verify that new instance is identical to the instance (1) and supports the same operations

For details about VDD format please refer to these files in GIT:

XML Schema - \siu\plugins\com.hp.usage.cirrus.common\src\com\hp\usage\vnfm\vdd\model\vdd.xsd

XML Sample - \siu\apps\nfv\vnfm\dev_artifacts\deployment_descriptors\VDDTest-vdd.xml

instantiate & scale operation and now create a new vnfid and then export the vdd, if we see the

ID: QXCR1001522157

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

secserveractivate should support truststore configuration parameters, and also for ldaps connections for LookupLdapServer and LoginLdapServer.

Resolution:

secserveractivate has been enhanced with following new arguments. For Login server: "loginldapts" , "loginldaptspwd" , "loginldaptstype", "loginldaptsprovider"; while for Lookup server: "lookupldapts" , "lookupldaptspwd" , "lookupldaptstype" , "lookupldaptsprovider". These will only be used if "loginldapserver" or "lookupldapserver" URLs are ldaps (LDAP over SSL) connections. For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

Test Info Notes:

secserveractivate had been enhanced with below new arguments: For Login server : "loginldapts" , "loginldaptspwd" , "loginldaptstype", "loginldaptsprovider" For Lookup server : "lookupldapts" , "lookupldaptspwd" , "lookupldaptstype" , "lookupldaptsprovider"

These will only be used if "loginldapserver" or "lookupldapserver" url are ldaps (LDAP over SSL) connections.

> You can validate the final config changes under %VARROOT%\securityserver\conf\external-login.config

Below are the points to consider: > There param values will only be used if the url starts with "ldaps" > loginldapts and loginldaptspwd are required to update truststore properties for login module. > lookupldapts and lookupldaptspwd are required to update truststore properties for lookup module. > type and provider are optional.

Validate the same through new Activator also.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC5a
RHEl 7x64
Java 8u112
==============

It was verified that truststore config is supported for ldaps.
All new parameters of secserveractivate are working properly both from console and activator.

Issue : The DB table associated with the collector / sessionServer is not getting cleared.

*******************************************************************************************

Re-opened the CR on Jan 31st

ANAND's reply -

Pankaj,

1) I propose a tracingtool CLI command with a cleanup function to clean up the tracing data. It can get the DB/table information from the config server, the same place as tracing GUI gets it from, particularly the TracingDataDB and TracingDataTable components. In fact, if we implement these components to do the cleanup, then we can use it from both CLI as well as tracing GUI.

Qingyang,

1) Can you add a cleanup button to the tracing GUI, so we can clean up the tracing data? I will have Pankaj implement the actual cleanup in the TracingDataDB component. You just need to configure it in your code and call it.

One more addition to the above enhancement - (13th Feb 2017)

Pankaj,

The cleanup function should drop the "tracing_data" table itself, instead of just clearing the contents. This is required because - the user is not able to create the table with same name scecond time with different set of columns - INFORMATIVE: Configured DB table tracing_data_3 is not present in DB , creating the table ... 02/13/2017 12:11:11.572 IST main (DBStore) ERROR: Error creating table through liquibase changelog Validation Failed: 1 change sets check sum /var/opt/SIU_09_RC3_secure/tracing_demo/tracing_data_3.xml::9.0-Tracing::eIUM was: 7:80b455dd2bad856915fa36159db4d61b but is now: 7:d22d02ccbd17f24a7395fb34b5b91b4e

This is beacuse the entry is already there in 'databasechangelog' table.

Test Info Notes:

tracingmanager cli command can be used to clean up the tracing data table from DB.

command will take dbnode and table name as input to execute. Here DB node is one the TracingDataDB nodes under "/deployment/host/WebAppServer/TracingConfig" and table name is the table to be dropped.

>>tracingmanager cleanup -dbnode DB1 -tn tracing_data

Once cleanup is executed the specified table is dropped. User can create the table again when collector is restarted.

------------ In Administration page of GUI, add 'Cleanup' action for the tracing group row. If click 'Cleanup' action the DB table relevant to the tracing group will be dropped.

ID: QXCR1001521966

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Li,Zhiwei [zli@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The Load Balancer should also be able to support balancing for a FrontEnd connector.

Resolution:

To enable the eIUM Load Balancer to support front-end load balancing, the eIUM Load Balancer introduces a new "AssociateConnectorName" attribute for the BackEndServerGroup component. For a back-end group which is slated for front-end load balancing, the user needs to configure the "AssociateConnectorName", and specify the inbound connector name for it. The front-end load balancing is similar to normal load balancing, and it depends on the configured algorithm for the corresponding back-end server group. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Test Info Notes:

please reference attached "FrontEnd Load balancing 2 FrontEnd.msg" for the original request and the use case.

please reference attached "DLB_front_LB.config" as the example configuration to support the front- end load balancing case.

Verifier:

Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC6

      With the Fix : LoadBalancer supports FrontEnd groups
      Without the Fix : FrontEnd groups is not supported by LoadBalancer

ID: QXCR1001521942

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Pavlenko,Andrey [andrey.pavlenko@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

High Availability (HA) support is needed for the configuration and repository servers.

Resolution:

Starting with eIUM 9.0, multiple instances of the configuration server and repository server are now supported. If one instance is down, eIUM processes are automatically switched to another.

Test Info Notes:

To install config servers running on 2 hosts in HA mode:

1. Install and activate CS on host1. 2. Install IUM on host2 and launch the activator. 3. During the activation select the "Join an existing config server" option and enter the address of CS1. 4. On the DB configuration page you need to specify the same DB that is used by CS1.

ID: QXCR1001521532

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Kerberos login authentication for the security server accepted krb as the flag and host, port, and domain through: kdchost, kdcport, and dr arguments. It should support it through an input Kerberos configuration file also.

Resolution:

The new secserveractivate init argument "krblogincfg" has been added, which will be used only if the "krb" option is set. The Kerberos configuration file path can be specified under this argument, which will be used for Kerberos authentication. If "krblogincfg" is specified, kdchost, kdcport, and dr will be ignored. If "krblogincfg" is not specified, kdchost, kdcport, and dr will be used to create the Kerberos login file. See the eIUM Command Reference for more information.

Test Info Notes:

Test secserveractivate init with "krb" flag and all the combinations of : krblogincfg OR "kdchost, kdcport, dr"

The new activator also should support he same.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL6 x64
Java8u112
---------------

It was verified that Kerberos login is supported through config file.

ID: QXCR1001521244

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Popov,Alexey [alexey.popov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

DiameterAdapter should be able to accept or reject incoming and outgoing Diameter connections.

Resolution:

The new DiameterRuleChainAuthorizer component has been added. It authorizes all incoming and outgoing connections by calling a rule chain when a CER or CEA is received. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

On CER/CEA receiving Diameter Adapter should be able to invoke authorization RuleChain

Following attributes should be passed to the RuleChain: Origin-Host Origin-Realm IP (transport level) Request Flag

RuleChain should be able to define if this Diameter session is allowed or restricted. If it is restricted, Diameter Adapter should send CEA with error code (if it received CER) For received CEA RuleChain should be able to identify necessity to send DPR or to send it directly using DiameterDisconnectRule if diameter session is restricted

This enhancement should be supported in connector framework to provide similar functionality for HTTP connector.

Test Info Notes:

Create Diameter Client and Diameter Server.

Test 1.

Configure DiameterRuleChainAuthorizer in Diameter Server. NME attribute referenced by ResultAttribute should be set to non-zero value by the end of the called rulechain.

Run the client and the server. Ensure, when client establishes a connection, the authorizers rulechain is called and NME attributes are filled by values from received CER. Ensure that the connection is accepted: CEA with Result-Code DIAMETER_SUCCESS is sent and requests from the client are processed.

Test 2.

Configure DiameterRuleChainAuthorizer in Diameter Server. NME attribute referenced by ResultAttribute should be set to zero value by the end of the called rulechain.

Run the client and the server. Ensure, when client establishes a connection, the authorizers rulechain is called and NME attributes are filled by values from received CER. Ensure that the connection is rejected: CEA with Result-Code DIAMETER_UNKNOWN_PEER is sent and the connection is closed.

Test 3.

Configure DiameterRuleChainAuthorizer in Diameter Client. NME attribute referenced by ResultAttribute should be set to non-zero value by the end of the called rulechain.

Run the client and the server. Ensure, when client establishes a connection, the authorizers rulechain is called and NME attributes are filled by values from received CEA. Ensure that the connection is accepted: it is not closed and requests from the client are sent successfully.

Test 4.

Configure DiameterRuleChainAuthorizer in Diameter Client. NME attribute referenced by ResultAttribute should be set to zero value by the end of the called rulechain.

Run the client and the server. Ensure, when client establishes a connection, the authorizers rulechain is called and NME attributes are filled by values from received CEA. Ensure that the connection is rejected: DPR is sent immediately and client requests are not sent.

Verifier: 

Verified by : Sujit Kumar                           
Release     : eIUM9.0
Verified in : RC5a 
Branch      : next-tissot
Time Spent  : 2hr
TET Status  : Need to automate       

Diameter LB is able to authorize CER and CEA received 
from Diameter client and Diameter server.

Diameter LB configuration and NMESchema used for testing is attached.

Symptoms:

The SplitArrayRule SplitAttribute configuration attribute had to be an array of NME types in the SNME Schema. It did not support an array of primitive types.

Resolution:

The attribute can now be configured with an SNME attribute that is of the primitive array type (such as boolean[], byte[], short[], int[], long[], char[], double[], float[] or string[]) in the SNME Schema.

Submitter Text Notes:

SplitArrayRule Needs to Support Array of Primitive Types

The new AndCondition, OrCondition, and NotCondition components have been added. See the eIUM Component Reference for more information.

Submitter Text Notes:

SNMECondition Needs to Support AND, OR & NOT operators to enable more complex conditions based on the SNME attributes. Another option is to implement the Scripting based condition.

Test Info Notes:

Test new components AndCondition, OrCondition and NotCondition under ConditionalRule. See attached config AndOrSample.config.

Verifier:

==========

=============

configured under the AndCondition component.
Case 2: To verify that for the AndCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns false 
and the RightCondition returns true, the result of the AndCondition evaluated to false.
Case 3: To verify that for the AndCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns true 
and the RightCondition returns true, the result of the AndCondition evaluated to true.
Case 4: To verify that for the AndCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns true 
and the RightCondition returns false, the result of the AndCondition evaluated to false.
Case 5: To verify that for the AndCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns false 
and the RightCondition returns false, the result of the AndCondition evaluated to false.

OrCondition:
============
Case 1: To verify the behavior when the 2 mandatory nodes LeftCondition and RightCondition are not

and the RightCondition returns true, the result of the OrCondition evaluated to true.
Case 3: To verify that for the OrCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns true and 
the RightCondition returns true, the result of the OrCondition evaluated to true.

the RightCondition returns false, the result of the OrCondition evaluated to true.
Case 5: To verify that for the OrCondition, the SNMECondition undet LeftCondition returns false

ID: QXCR1001520839

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Vdovichenko,Vadim [vadim.vdovichenko@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a reference between XFD types from different namespaces.

Resolution:

Now in the XFD file, you can import the namespace defined in another XFD file, and refer to types from that namespace. For instance, if the XFD describes an XML format which includes types defined in different XML namespaces, then it is possible to define one XFD per one XML namespace, and then import those XFDs and refer to types from them, instead of putting all the types into a single namespace and introduce potential name collisions.

Test Info Notes:

Check references between XFD types from different namespaces.

ID: QXCR1001519411

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kopylov,Sergey [sergey.kopylov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

During performance tests it was found that one script (in the ScriptingRule) could be compiled many times for different rule chains. This resulted in increased eIUM server start-up time.

Resolution:

Now each script can be compiled only once by setting the new "CacheCompiled" ScriptingRule attribute. CacheCompiled is set by default to true for the Groovy scripting engine, and false for the MVEL scripting engine. Requests to compile an already compiled script will be served by creating a copy of the already compiled script. As a result, this will improve eIUM server start-up time. Also see the eIUM Component Reference for more information.

Submitter Text Notes:

Provide compile-once feature for IUM scripting framework

Verifier:

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Users want to throttle request throughput to each back-end server, so that the system can run within the pre-defined threshold, and keep the back-end server running safely to avoid being overload.

Resolution:

The eIUM Load Balancer provides the new ThroughputLimitationAlgorithm component, which can throttle the request throughput to a back-end server, according to a user-specified throttle threshold. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

apply LeakyBuckyAlgorithm to throttle throughput to backend

Test Info Notes:

please reference the component ref doc about: ThrughputputLimitationAlgorithm. with this algorithm user can pre-define throughput threshold for back-ends. the Loadbalancer should be able to throttling throughput to back-ends.

ID: QXCR1001518975

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Sadovnycha,Mariia [mariia.sadovnycha@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Templates should be able to include another template configuration. Link functionality is not enough, as when linked configuration is not customizable in the template user interface (eIUM Studio or Operations Console).

Resolution:

The new annotation @Import(path="path to a template in the repository", node="note to merge") is available. The node argument is optional. If it is not defined, the full template will be merged into the current node). After deploying such a template, all imported templates will be merged into a single one and copied to the main configuration.

Test Info Notes:

Try to create templates with import annotations (2 examples are attached to the CR). To import external template to the current tempalate, add annotation to node where configuration from external template should be added (see attached file ImportTemplate.config): @Import(path="pathInTheRepositoryToTemplate") [/rootNodeForExternalConfiguration]

If only some subtree should be imported from external templates, use next annotation (see attached file ImportNode.config): @Import(path="pathInTheRepositoryToTemplate", node="fullNodeName") [/rootNodeForExternalConfiguration]

Run 'New config from Template' in IUMStudio or 'New Server' in OpsUI: expected result configuration from external template should be merged, all merged customizable parameters should be available in the wizard.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 IC7
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
================

It was verified that required functionality is available in IC7 build.

In case of default @Import(path=...) annotation whole tree is merged.

In case of @Import(path=..., node=...) annotation only content of "node=..." is merged.

Symptoms:

The Security Server has been enhanced and now includes an embedded LDAP server. As the Security Server is not required on every eIUM host, the customer may want to avoid installing this additional software. As a result, it is desirable to separate the Security Server and provide it as an additional option bundle.

Resolution:

The eIUM Security Server is now provided as an additional option bundle. This bundle requires no specific license, so it could be installed on every Standard or Bare eIUM host. Installation on Client hosts is prohibited and inapplicable.

Test Info Notes:

1. Please check that official build artifacts for Tissot (and CI build artifacts on eIUM Dashboard) include new merge module called "SecurityServer*.iam.zip". There should be just one module for all platforms and architectures (*).

2. Ensure that this module installs correctly.

3. Ensure that when this module is installed, additional activation steps are shown (asking to activate Embedded LDAP and Security Server).

(*) Please note that this module will not work correctly on HP-UX. There was a special change done to securityserver.ini properties for HP-UX which is currently switched off by commit 8b52a656f5951. Should this module be supported on HP-UX, this properties mangling should be applied in activator.

ID: QXCR1001518193

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Tsoukanov,Victor [victor.tsoukanov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a command-line interface tool to dump collected statistics.

Resolution:

The new statdump tool has been added to fulfill this requirement. The statdump "dump" command can dump statistics collected by the central management server, while the statdump "audit" command allows creating an audit report. For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

We need CLI to dump collected statistics

Test Info Notes:

Test command /bin/statdump in correspondence with its usage. See command ref for more details usage: dump [-attribute <attributeName>] [-end <endTime>] [-format <format>] [-host <hostName>] [-instance <instanceName>] [-job <jobName>] [-limit <limit>] [-output <output>] [-process <processName>] [-silent] [-start <startTime>] -attribute <attributeName> Specify the name of attribute that should be used to export statistics data. -end <endTime> Specify end time that should be used to export statistics data. -format <format> Specify format that should be used to export statistics data. -host <hostName> Specify name of host that should be used to export statistics data. -instance <instanceName> Specify the name of connector. -job <jobName> Specify name of job that should be used to export statistics data. -limit <limit> Specify the number of records to return that should be used to export statistics data. -output <output> Specify name of file that should be used to export statistics data. -process <processName> Specify name of eIUM process. -silent Runs the command in non-interactive mode -start <startTime> Specify start time that should be used to export statistics data.

Test command /bin/statdump audit to test license information collected by license management. It can be tested when QXCR1001514961 will be ready.

ID: QXCR1001515879

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kapil,Kumar [kkapil@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a new HDFS Copy Task.

Resolution:

The new File HDFS Copy Task has been added. This new task is another copy task variant, which can copy files to an HDFS file system. The task uses the webhdfs scheme for non-secure transfer, and swebhdfs for a secure connection to the HDFS. The URL takes the following format: webhdfs://<ip>: <port>/.

Submitter Text Notes:

This CR is created to track separately item #4 from main CR (QXCR1001512026 -- Hadoop/HDFS Integration Points in IUM)

4)BPMN2 Work Flow:- A new task HDFSCopyTask has been introduced to copy the file to HDFS filesystem.

HDFS copy task should be integrated with JDSFileOPeration Task to copy the file to hdfs and send the notification to jds server.

ID: QXCR1001514078

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

New validators and value generator needed for security server activation through eIUM activator.

Resolution:

New Validators created are: CertificateDurationValidation, EncryptionStrengthValidation, LDAPConnectionValidation. New value generator created are: NMEValueGenerator

Test Info Notes:

Below are the Validator and details on how to test these: ========================================================= Activator : CertificateDurationValidation Enabled When : Security Server Activation Purpose : Validates the duration of certificates to be provided on "Security Server Configuration" screen

Activator : EncryptionStrengthValidation Enabled When : Security Server Activation, Client Activation Purpose : Validates the JDK JCE cryptography strength on the first screen of Security server activation or client security and ask the user to update the policies before proceeding.

Activator : LDAPConnectionValidation Enabled When : Security Server Activation Purpose : Provides the option to check/validate the connection for external LDAP server.

New value generator created are: NMEValueGenerator This is used internally to create the option values (dropdown) for the user runtime from NME attribute. This is used in Security Server activation to dispaly the root context available in the LDAP server.

Test these validators while activating security server and client security.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL6 x64
Java8u112
---------------

It was verified that JCE encryption strength/certificates duration correctness/external LDAP
connectivity could be properly validated on activator screens.

ID: QXCR1001513379

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Sadovnycha,Mariia [mariia.sadovnycha@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

When a configuration is opened with the follow link flag and the linked attribute is uncommented and modified, then the entire linked configuration should be carefully analyzed, and according to configuration entries, manually uncommented. This process should be automated in eIUM Studio.

Resolution:

Linked nodes can be shown in the Outline by selecting "Show linked nodes" in the Outline menu. To edit a linked node with the Outline, you should select a linked node in the Outline tree and choose "Overwrite node" from right-click menu, to uncomment the linked node, or "Reset node" to use the default linked node configuration and the linked node will be commented. The ConfigEditor also provides hot-keys CTRL+# (CTRL+SHIFT+3) to comment/uncomment a linked configuration.

Test Info Notes:

Edit linked configuration : 1. via outline Select "Show linked nodes" * Select linked node in the outline tree -> Right-click menu "Overwrite node" Ex.b: uncomment linked node (and required subtree) if linked configuration was commented or create new subtree in the editor

* Select linked node in the outline tree -> Right-click menu "Reset node" Ex.b: comment (#-> ) selected node and its children if they overwrite linked configuration As well empty parent nodes will be commented

2. ConfigEditor, hotkeys to comment/uncomment linked configuration CTRL+# Select line or multiple lines in ConfigEditor and press Ctrl+# if a first selected line is linked comment (start with #->), all selected lines will be uncommented and required nodes definition as well

if a first selected line is linked attribute or node, all selected attributes and nodes will be commented. Node will be commented only if it does not contain attributes or non empty child nodes. All empty parent nodes and empty child nodes (if they are linked) will be commented as well.

Verifier: 

Returned to dev per request from developer.
Some additional functionality should be added.

Symptoms:

In the eIUM Studio Deployment Manager, it was not possible to pin the JMX view, in the same manner as the Statistics view or Log view.

Resolution:

A new "Pin" option has been added the to JMX view menu. In pin mode, the JMX view will not change its contents when a selection in the Deployment tree is changed. The maximum number of opened JMX views is configurable in Window -> Preferences -> Deployment Manager.

Submitter Text Notes:

Provide "pin" functionality for JMXView

Test Info Notes:

Pin works for not empty JMX view (attributes/operations levels and etc) Select jmx object in deployment tree -> Open JMX Details view -> Pin it -> Select other jmx object in the tree Expected behavior: JMX View content is not changed when selection changes, JMX View name corresponds to object name

ID: QXCR1001512026

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kapil,Kumar [kkapil@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is need for Hadoop/HDFS integration in eIUM.

Resolution:

Hadoop/HDFS integration in eIUM is exposed as the new FileManagerDelivery and FileManagerSource components, the new BPMN2 worfklow HDFSFileCopyTask, as well as JDS integration in terms of the webhdfs scheme name. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference and eIUM Foundation Guide.

Submitter Text Notes:

These are the following integration points of Hadoop/HDFS in IUM.

1)FileManagerDelivery:- A new transport component has been introduced which can be configured under DeliveryAgents to upload the files into HDFS.

2)FIleManagerSource:- A new Source component has been introduced which can be under encapsulator to download the files from HDFS.

3)JDS Integration:- The FileServiceURI attribute support HDFS scheme.Like:- webhdfs/hdfs

4)BPMN2 Work Flow:- A new task HDFSCopyTask has been introduced to copy the file to HDFS filesystem.

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001512024

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Activating the security server and security activation for eIUM should be done at the time of eIUM activation.

Resolution:

The eIUM Activation Wizard now allows activating the security server, if the security server module was selected during installation. It additionally allows activating security at the time of activation only. In addition, the secserveractivate and secactivate commands have been enhanced for a better user experience. See the Command Reference and eIUM Installation Guide for more details.

Test Info Notes:

New commands added for secserveractivate are: rootcontext, usercontext, hostcontext, groupscontext, ldaptype, servercertduration, hostcertduration, hostcertduration, usercertduration, adminkeystorepwd, rootcacert, rootcacertpwd.

- All these are optional. Details can be read from Command reference. - Existing layout option is optional now. If layout file is not specified then user will be prompted for : rootcontext, usercontext, hostcontext, groupscontext - All these optional attributes are prompted with default value.

============================================= New command added is : secldapcontrol. This command is currently used to add/remove/list the existing partitions in ApaceDS and OpenLdap servers. Details can be read from Command reference. =============================================

eIUM activator should support activating security. There are 2 new modules added to activator for security: M1) Security server activation M2) Activating security for eIUM

M1 : ==== > Additional merge module bundle will be provided for securityserver. This bundle includes embedded apacheds server also.If this bundle is selected while installing then the security server options will appear while activating eIUM. > We allow eIUM bare installation with only this securityserver bundle also. This means that securityserver can reside on some other machine while eIUM is installed, activated and security enabled on some other machine. > Select securityserver bundle while installing eIUM. Activate security server. Security server activation should create one security admin user. > Test reactivation scenario also.

M2 : ==== > Activating client security for eIUM should be enabled by default whether securityserver module is selected or not. Since securityserver can be installed on different machine also. > Try activating security and validate it. > Test reactivation scenario also. > Test activating eIUM and security for secondary host also (non config server).

================================================= Apart from activator flow, try to activate securityserver and client security through command line also using secserveractivate and secactivate commands.

> Please make sure the activate flow should be tested for following LDAP server: - Embedded ApacheDS - External ApacheDS - External OpenLdap

These are must support Ldap servers. It can be additionally tested for eDirectory,Redhat

Symptoms:

The eIUM license was bound to concrete IP addresses where the configuration server could be deployed.

Resolution:

With the new eIUM license server, customers are free to decide where to deploy eIUM configuration servers. All configuration servers will connect to this licensing service to obtain run permission (namely, a license token). For more information, see the eIUM Installation Guide.

Submitter Text Notes:

Provide license server IA merge module for eIUM 9.0

Test Info Notes:

1. Install license server merge module with IUM bare installer. 2. Activate license server - make sure native launcher "licenseserver.exe" or "licenseserver.bin" exists in bin directory. - make sure license server installed as daemon in Lunix - connect to license server dashboard at http:/<host>:8477/licenseserver - play with license server dashboard

3. Request IUM license for licensing server - specify <host>:8477 in IP address input field

4. Add requested license to license server via dashboard

5. Install and activate IUM with requested license. Also check - reactivate with different repository port - license token prolongation - deactivation

processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV Cleared 1 alarm(s) processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 Cleared 1 alarm(s) processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test1 -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test2 -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -t com.hp.Test Cleared 1 alarm(s) processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -t com.hp.Test? Cleared 2 alarm(s) processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test -s Critical -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>sendalarm -n ds1 -t com.hp.Test -s Major -m message Alarm sent successfully. processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -s Critical Cleared 1 alarm(s) processmanager>>clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -s Major Cleared 1 alarm(s)

1. clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV - clear all alarms on host 2. clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 - clear all alarms on server 3. clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -t com.hp.Test - clear alarms by type 4. clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -t com.hp.Test? - clear alarms by type with pattern (? - wildcard for one symbol, * - - wildcard for several symbols) 5. clearalarm -n /deployment/VTSOUKANOV/ds1 -s Critical - clear alarm by severity

ID: QXCR1001509714

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

TCPConnector with DynamicEndPointSelector configured as a proxy client created many TCPEndPoints, which were registered to the management server and crashed it.

Resolution:

The new "Managed" configuration attribute has been added to DynamicEndPointSelector, which when set to false, will avoid registering the numerous TCPEndPoints to ManagementServer. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

It should be possible to disable TCPEndPoint statistics via its configuration.

Test Info Notes:

Create a session server out of template "Netty web server and client". It has a DynamicEndPointSelector under TCPConnector 'nettyClient'. Start it, send a few requests through it (siuinvoke -n colName -rulechain SendRequest -data RequestType get) and view its MBeans (in JConsole or OpsUI). Without the patch, you will see an MBean for the DynamicEndPointSelector and the TCPEndPoint. With the patch and DynamicEndPointSelector.Managed configured to false, you will see there are no MBeans for DynamicEndPointSelector and TCPEndPoint.

Verifier: 

//Vikram Pai M on 29/9/2016

Functional Testcases:
---------------------

1.To verify in Netty Webserver client having Tcpconnector component and TCPEndpoint using 
DynamicEndPointSelector class with 'Managed' configured to true,sending HTTP requests and verifying 
whether netty client realted statistics is getting updated or not in ops-ui/jconsole.

2.To verify in Netty Webserver client having Tcpconnector component and TCPEndpoint using 
DynamicEndPointSelector class with 'Managed' configured to false,sending HTTP requests and 
verifying whether netty client realted statistics is getting updated or not in ops-ui/jconsole.

3.To verify in Netty Webserver client having Tcpconnector component and TCPEndpoint using 
DynamicEndPointSelector class with 'Managed' not configured(Default),sending HTTP requests and 
verifying whether netty client realted statistics is getting updated or not in ops-ui/jconsole.

Test Step:
---------

1.Setup 83VivoRC4 customer patch environment with patch version as shown above.
2.Create a session server out of template "Netty web server and client"
3.It has a DynamicEndPointSelector under TCPConnector 'nettyClient',update 'Managed' config item 
with appropriate config value as mentioned in testcase.
4.Similarly for checking 'nettyServer' statistics behaviour,update 'CollectStatistics' config item 
present in 'HTTPProtocol' component located at netty server with similar config values.
5.Start it, send a few requests through it
(./siuinvoke -n Netty_Client -rulechain SendRequest -data RequestType post)
6.In Ops-UI check for statistics items updation for Netty client and server,snapshot for which has 
been attached with this CR.
7.And also check jconsole whether proper values are getting updated for statistic items.

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 IC2 RHEl 7 x64 Java 8u102 ==================

It was found that after normal acceptance launched over eIUM90 IC2 instance size of Git repos are enourmously large. For example main repo /var/opt/SIU/repositoryserver/server/base was about 800Mb. Two cache repos /var/opt/SIU/cache/repository, were about 1.5Gb each.

Simple "git gc" command launched over these repos reduced size 10 times. So it means that there are lots of garbage objects in these repos, which we should investigate how to remove.

For example it was found that loadconfig launched over some folder (loadconfig -dir) makes a git commit for each file loaded, while it is reasonable to make 1 commit for such an operation.

ID: QXCR1001506937

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

A configuration attribute is required to control the sending of test SMS to the SMPP server, when a connection is created through the JMX operation.

Resolution:

The new SendSMSOnConnectionOpen configuration attribute has been created for this purpose. See the eIUM Component Reference for more information.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently sending test SMS requires configuration of TestSMSCreator sub-node under SMPPClientEndpoint. If the test SMS not desired to be sent, then this sub-node needs to be removed from config. However, the customer wanted it to be controlled through an config attribute.

Test Info Notes:

1) Please refer to the attached config.

2) Configure SessionServer, SMPPClientConnector and SMPPClientEndPoint under it.

3) In order to send test SMS upon connection creation through JMX operation, please configure TestSMSCreator sub-node under SMPPClientEndPoint.

4) Configure NEW config attribute SendSMSOnConnectionOpen, value of which is set to JMX.

Test Case 1: If SendSMSOnConnectionOpen is set to JMX, then TestSMSCreator sub-node must be configured. Or else config exception will be thrown.

Test Case 2: If SendSMSOnConnectionOpen is set to value JMX and then if TestSMSCreator sub-node is properly configured, then when a new connection is created through JMX operation ONLY, then test SMS will be sent to SMPP server. This test SMS will NOT be sent to SMPP server, if the connection is created through Rule Chain.

Test Case 3: If SendSMSOnConnectionOpen is not set to JMX, then it doesn't matter whether TestSMSCreator sub-node is configured or not, test SMS will NOT be sent to SMPP server, when connection is created through JMX operation.

Test Case 4: SendSMSOnConnectionOpen can be configured as a EndPointDynamicConfigAttributes. That means, when an endpoint is created at runtime, a JMX value can be passed for this attribute, determining at runtime whether test SMS will be sent or not.

Test Case 5: If SendSMSOnConnectionOpen is configured to any other value other than "JMX" (case-insensitive), then ConfigurationException will be thrown.

Test Case 6: Please check the documentation of SMPPClientConnector, SMPPClientEndPoint, SMPPEndPoint and ESMEConnection components. There should NOT be any mention of attribute RetryDelayInSeconds anywhere, neither in documentation nor in sample config examples.

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-327.28.3.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.08.03 2015/04/02"
Patch Version: eIUM83IM.20160808-1446
Point Patch Version: eIUM83IM_QXCR1001506995_20160912
Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
==========================================================

It was verified using attached configuration SMPPClientCon_05 and SMPPSim that proper fix was 
introduced.

All test cases passed. Test SMS is being sent only when connection is opened from JMX and proper 
configuration of SendSMSOnConnectionOpen and TestSMSCreator presents.

For Test Case 4 it is always required to provide some value for dynamic attribute, so we could pass 
either JMX to have end point with "test sms" enabled or NOJMX with "test sms" disabled.

ID: QXCR1001506704

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Sharma,Surendra [surendra.sharma@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

in Current version, there is no Rule to enable NMELinkConnector to sent out an NMELink answer message. this would be useful in case of NMELink loadbalancer.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup ~~~~~~~~~~ NMELink Exporter(end client) => NMELink Collector + NMELink Exporter(LB) => NMELink Collector (End server)

Brief intro how it works? ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ End Cleint i.e. NMELink Exporter sends request to NMELink Collector which is one of the connector in NMELink loadbalancer session server configuration. After receiving request NMELink collector invokes rule chain which has NMELinkClientRule. NMELinkClientRule invokes NMELink Exporter configured under NMELink loadbalancer session server configuration. NMELink Exporter invokes LB using LoadBalancerRouter to get destination. NMELink Exporter will send request to end server i.e. NMELink Collector.

Where to place NMELinkAnswerRule? ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ NMELinkClientRule (Synch mode): NMELinkAnswerRule will be configured just after NMELinkClientRule. NMELinkClientRule (Aynch mode): NMELinkAnswerRule will be configured in the response rule chain configured under NMELinkClientRule.

I have attached one sample configuration. You need to change the router configuration. LB configuration is present in sample configuration.

Test case 1: Test the NMELink loadbalancer with NMELink Collector contains NMELinkClientRule synchronous mode.

Test case 2: Test the NMELink loadbalancer with NMELink Collector contains NMELinkClientRule asynchronous mode.

In both the test cases, Response should be redirected to the end client i.e. NMELink Exporter(end client).

Verifier: 

IUM Version - 90 Tissot (RC5a)
Test Status - PASS

Execute the 2 testcase's mentioned in the testinfo notes.(Attached configs used)
Tested with NMELink Exporter(end client) => NMELink Collector + NMELink Exporter(LB) => 3 NMELink
Collectors (Back End servers).
Algorithm used is RoundRobinAlgorithm.

Result:
Response gets redirected to the end client i.e. NMELink Exporter(end client).

ID: QXCR1001506134

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

An attribute in JNDILookupConnector should be provided to configure a complex LDAP query.

Resolution:

The new MatchQuery attribute allows configuring complex LDAP queries. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

Need an attribute in JNDILookupConnector to configure complex LDAP query.

Test Info Notes:

Step 1:

configure MatchQuery under JNDILookupConnector

example : MatchQuery=(|(objectClass=%NMEAttr1%)(objectClass=%NMEAttr2%))

Step 2:

Now execute the rule through SIU Invoke by passing the value for the NMEAttr1,NMEAttr2

Step 3:

You must be able to get response from the LDAP server for the query you configured

Note: if both MatchKeys and MatchQuery are configured under JNDILookupConnector,MatchKeys Attribute will be ignored,And query string(query to LDAP server) will be created based on MatchQuery

For your information : LDAP query now can be created in two ways by configuring MatchKeys or by configuring MatchQuery.If both are configured MatchQuery will be given priority.

ID: QXCR1001504160

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

JDBCEncapsulator should pass the Filter value to JDBCTimestampTailingPolicy or JDBCSeqnumTailingPolicy if configured.

Resolution:

JDBCEncapsulator has been fixed to pass the Filter value to JDBCTimestampTailingPolicy or JDBCSeqnumTailingPolicy if configured.

Submitter Text Notes:

Implement â€œwhereâ€ clause in the TailingPolicy as an enhancement of IUM?

Under the system configuration of our customer, itâ€™s impossible to separate the table, and employing JDBCSeqnumTailingPolicy instead for JDBCTimestampTailingPolicy is difficult since multiple collectors simultaneously write (bulk insert) to the database. So we think if the filter was effective in TailingPolicy, only a small amount of modification can enable their system work properly

Test Info Notes:

> Create a database table from where JDBCEncapsulator will read record. Make sure there is one additonal column (like ID or CollectorName) which will differentiate the inout for multiple collectors reading data from it. > Configure collector with JDBCEncapsulator and Filter attribute configured under it. > Configure either JDBCTimestampTailingPolicy or JDBCSeqnumTailingPolicy under JDBCEncapsulator. > the flush should happen for collector based on this control column in the database > Currently the flush condition (query) do not append the configured Filter to the query hence the the retrieved result might not be correct. > With the patch, the query for Tailing Policy has been updated to append the Filter also. Hence the functionality should work as expected.

Run regression for JDBCEncapsulator (JDBCTimestampTailingPolicy, JDBCSeqnumTailingPolicy )

Steps to reproduce the issue:

insert a record in the database with random time stamp value ranging from 11:05- 11:10(timestamp,control column) belonging to collect ID 1

Wait for the flush to happen.

Now insert a time stamp value with 11:30 belonging to collector ID 2

try inserting values into the database between the time interval 11:10-11:15

Without Point Patch:

Records will be skipped by the encapsulator and not flushed

With Point Patch

Records will not be skipped by the encapsulator and successfully flushed
