ID: QXCR1001503123

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kumar,Pankaj [pankaj.kumar3@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for tracing and tracking of records in eIUM.

Resolution:

The new components TracingRule, TracingService, and TracingManager have been created to achieve this functionality. See the Tracing chapter in the eIUM Foundation Guide, as well as the Tracing category of components in the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM servers such as Session Server and Collector creates and processes NMEs. At various stages of processing the NME content changes and the NME can be passed into another server for further processing. There is a need to be able to trace through the NME instances at various stages of processing for debugging purpose. The purpose of tracing framework is to provide a consistent way to collect and access NMEs at various processing points in eIUM Collector and Session server processes.

Test Info Notes:

Please refer attached config to start testing of tracing feature.

Testing will include below basic functionalities-

1. Tracing manager. 2. Tracing Service 3. Tracing rule

Install IUM9.0 and start launchpad and import the attached config.

1. After management server starts open ops console UI , go to advanced tab and look for tracingmanager mbean. This mbean should be present with few standard operation to update/get filter critierion, start time, expiry dates for tracing points.

2. Start the session server and go to advanced tab and look for mbean created under the session server tree with the same name as configured tracingservice.

3. Create the DB table configured in the DBStore node under tracing service.

4. Start the tracing point from tracingmanager mbean.

5. execute siuinvoke from cmd prompt with the nme attributes configured in DB Store or file store.

6. The nme data should be persisted to the mentioned table or file.

Verifier: 

Test Plan
=========

Ran the test cases for validating the tracing functionality

ID: QXCR1001502316

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Shao,Shun-Zhong [sshao@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

We need support for group statistics alarms. Because group statistics is not related to host, it is not correct to mix performance alarms generated for ordinary statistics providers and performance alarms generated for group statistics providers. In case of receiving alarms, IUM server moved to alarmed state, while for groups we do not have such state currently. So we need to extends existing support for alarms and include support for alarms for generated for group statistics providers. For this purpose we need to develop following functionality 1. Change behavior of icon to show the number of active alarms instead of the number of alarmed servers (e.g. 10/34 where 10 is an number of active alarms, 34 total number of alarms). 2. onClick should show panel with all alarms (instead of hot list), similar to panel shown for server 3. Group with active alarms in deployment panel should have an icon used to show alarmed servers (yellow triangle) 4. Drop down menu for groups in deployment panel should have an item "Alarms" and shows alarms specific for selected group, similar to same item in server drop down menu.

See attached email for more details

Verifier: 

Release: 83fp02(rc1)
TET Status: to automate
=======================
The CR was verified according test scenario below:

2 Demo and Diameter Client/Server configuration were used for testing.

Test#1 - new functionality
1. Check the behavior of Alarmed icon which shows the number of active-alarms/total-alarms. 
2. Check that Alarmed icon transfers to Alarms page.
3. Create Group of servers and create threshold monitor for this Group. Alarm should be thrown.
Check that only group becomes alarmed(yellow triangle). The number of active alarms is triggered
under Alarmed icon. This alarm can be seen in the "Last Active Alarms" portlet, but "Alarmed IUM
Processes" and "List of Groups" portlets don't show this alarm as expected.
4. Check that in Dropdown menu for groups in deployment panel the item "Alarms" is present and shows
alarms specific for selected group, where alarms can be cleared and acknowledged.

Result: Passed.

Test#2 - old functionality
1. Check that processes included in created groups can be alarmed separately. The number of active
alarms is triggered under Alarmed icon. This alarm can be seen in the "Last Active Alarms" portlet,
"Alarmed IUM Processes" and "List of Groups" portlets as expected.
2. Check that in Dropdown menu for processes in deployment panel the item "Alarms" is present and
shows alarms specific for selected process, where alarms can be cleared and acknowledged.

Test#3 - old functionality
1. Check that any processes not in groups can be alarmed. The number of active alarms is triggered
under Alarmed icon. This alarm can be seen in the "Last Active Alarms" portlet, "Alarmed IUM
Processes" and "List of Groups" portlets as expected.
2. Check that in Dropdown menu for processes in deployment panel the item "Alarms" is present and
shows alarms specific for selected process, where alarms can be cleared and acknowledged.

Note: the message "Handle alarm null" doesn't appear in MS log when clear alarm from OpsUI. Expected
behavior.

Symptoms:

Support is needed for integrating ApacheDS into eIUM.

Resolution:

eIUM now provides embedded ApacheDS in the product. When selecting embedded mode in installation, ApacheDS will auto-start when eIUM starts.

Test Info Notes:

New function to integrate apacheds server into security server. it will auto start apacheds server when user select embedded mode for apacheds server when start eIUM.

it will add a new parameter in the SIU.ini #for embedded apacheds server apacheds.embedded=true

------------------- apacheds folder will be generated when do install embedded apacheds in securityserver folder. it will include two sub folders: lib and instances the apacheds-service.jar will locate in the lib folder and instance folder will store runtime data.

Symptoms:

Resolution:

The new msdump tool has been added (which contains load and save commands). This tool can export/import the following configurations from a running management server: group of servers; operations in the scheduler; measurement jobs; threshold monitors; derived attributes; configuration of group statistics providers. For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

ID: QXCR1001500750

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kapil,Kumar [kkapil@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for Kafka integration points in eIUM.

Resolution:

Kafka integration points in eIUM are now available, to send and receive Bulk/Single NMEs to and from a Kafka Broker. See the new Kafka category of components in the eIUM Component Reference, as well as the eIUM Foundation Guide.

Submitter Text Notes:

Please follow the share points link for the documents. It is having funtional requirements as well as High level design. These are the main highlights of this enhancements.

1) Kafka Integration with JDS as a infinite storage. 2) Kafka Integration with FCS as a infinite storage. 3) Kafka Integration with session server and collector server as a KafkaConnector.

KafkaConnector is a new component being added to serve as a sending data and receiving data from Kafka Broker. This can be configured under session server as well as collector server to fullfill the following use cases.

1) can be used as a communication channel between eIUM server as well as external services. 2) can send and receive NME's or Bulk NME's to and from Kafka Broker.

For detail information, please go to share point and read the documents.

Verifier:

Test Status : PASS

Tested the following :
1)KafkaConnector as SessionServer and CollectorServer.
2)KafkaConnector is able to send and receive NME's or Bulk NME's to and from Kafka Broker
3)JDS with Kafka as Storage.

All the related testCase's will be attached soon.

ID: QXCR1001494988

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

ClientConnector EndPoints need to have a throttling feature to limit the sending rate of messages to remote servers.

Resolution:

ClientConnector EndPoints now possess this feature.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently in our client connector framework, no throttling feature exists at the endpoint level that can decide the rate of sending of messages to the remote server. We need to support a throttling feature to limit the rate of sending of messages.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure SessionServer and SMPPClientConnector under it. Please refer to the attached configuration for testing of Throttling feature.

2) Configure ThrottlingThreshold under SMPPClientEndPoint. This represents the number of SMS messages to be sent per second.

3) Configure ThrottlePerConnection under SMPPClientEndPoint. This represents whether rate of sending should be applied at the EndPoint level or individual created connection level. If set to true then throttling will be applied at each connection level. False, it will be applied at EndPoint level.

4) Please make sure, MaxConnectionIdleTime is either not configured or configured to zero or less. If this is enabled then throttling feature will not be enabled.

Test Case 1:

ThrottlingThreshold = 2 and ThrottlePerConnection = true

Test Scenario: Suppose 3 message are sent together and the EndPoint created 2 connections to serve it as per the load. Suppose connection 1 is used by 2 requests and connection 2 is used b the 3rd one.

Test Result: Please look for the "Sending message" log for each message. The timestamp of messages that are sent by Connection 1 should have gap between of 500 milliseconds. 500ms is calculated based on throttling time of 1000ms(per sec) / 2 (throttling threshold) .

Connection 2 message is sent anytime and independent of it. So here, the time difference between two consecutive messages using a same connection should be at least 500ms. This is how ThrottlePerConnection = true behaves. The message arrival can be verified by checking the timestamp of message at the SMPP server level also.

Test Case 2:

ThrottlingThreshold = 2 and ThrottlePerConnection = false (Message are throttled per EndPoint now)

Test Scenario: Suppose 3 message are sent together.

Test Result: Please look for the "Sending message" log for each message. Now as per the configuration, 2 messages are expected to leave the EndPoint per second. Therefore, the timestamp of messages that are sent by Connection 1 should have gap between of 500 milliseconds. 500ms is calculated based on throttling time of 1000ms(per sec) / 2 (throttling threshold) .

So here, the time difference between each and every message irrespective of connections used should be around 500ms. This is how ThrottlePerConnection = false (Per EndPoint) behaves. The message arrival can be verified by checking the timestamp of message at the SMPP server level also.

3) Please check for documentation in SMPPClientEndPoint for attributes ThrottlingThreshold and ThrottlePerConnection.

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-327.13.1.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.08.03 2015/04/02"
Patch Version: eIUM83IM.20160726-1408 (005-RC1)
Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
=================================================================

It was verified using attached configs that throttling works correct per connection and per end point.
If scheduler in SMPPClientCon_throttle session server invokes 5 messages per second, and throttling
in SMPPClientEndpoint is configured to 4, it means that 2 connections should be created, since 1
connection is unable to serve load. Same linear dependence is visible with other values of messages
per second and throttling threshold. For example 10 messages per second from 2 scheduler jobs and
throttling threshold 2 per connection means that 6 connections should be created to serve load.

In case of throttling per end point configured (ThrottlingPerConnection=false) throttling threshold
is applied to end point itself, despite of number of connections created.

ID: QXCR1001492869

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Popov,Alexey [alexey.popov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for configuring port numbers that can be used for outgoing connections in SCTPMessageTransport and DiameterSCTPTransport.

Resolution:

The new OutgoingPort configuration attribute has been added to these components. OutgoingPort allows configuration of one port, or a port range for outgoing connections. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

It should be possible to configure port that can be used for outgoing connections in SCTPMessageTransport and DiameterSCTPTransport.

Test Info Notes:

Create Diameter Client and Diameter Server with SCTP transport.

Test 1. Set OutgoingPort config attribute to a single value X in DiameterSCTPTransport in Diameter Client.

1. Open a connection from Client to Server. It should be open successfully and its outgoing port should be equal to X.

2. Open another connection. It should fail with "Address already in use" exception.

3. Close the first connection.

4. Open another connection. It should be open successfully with the same outgoing port.

Test 2. Set OutgoingPort config attribute to a range X-Y in DiameterSCTPTransport in Diameter Client.

1. Open a number of connections from Client to Server equal to the size of the range. They should be open successfully and their outgoing ports should be within the range.

2. Open another connection. It should fail with "Address already in use" exception.

3. Close the one connection.

4. Open another connection. It should be open successfully with the outgoing port in the range.

Repeat opening and closing connections several time.

Engineer: Sharma,Surendra [surendra.sharma@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for components to send and receive NMEs to/from remote session servers or collectors.

Resolution:

The NMELinkConnector allows sending and receiving NMEs to/from remote session servers or collectors. The component can send and receive NMEs from a remote NMELinkConnector configured in an eIUM process (session server process or collector process). NMELinkConnector uses the IPDR/SP protocol to transport NMEs. The NMELinkConnector has both the capabilities, that is, it can send and receive data from another eIUM process, and it can send and receive data either using a request-response model or bulk mode. Several new NMELink components have been added to support NMELink functionality. For more information, see the NMELink category of components in the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

This CR is created for the NMELink connector development which is 83fp02 requirement. Refer NMELinkConnector requirement document for more details.

Features added which is not present in requirement document. 1. Integration of NMELink connector with the IUM statistical framework. As part for this integration NMELink should support all the default attributes which are provided by statistical framework. 2. As Statistical framework provide attributes only for request response model. There are customized attribute handler which is created to show bulk data send information.

ID: QXCR1001487761

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Strygin,Maxim [maxim.strygin@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

All VNF life-cycle operations were synchronous and blocking, and ETSI has a renewed Or-Vfnm interface and specified information model in October 2016 (http://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_gs/NFV- IFA/001_099/007/02.01.01_60/gs_NFV-IFA007v020101p.pdf).

Resolution:

All VNF life-cycle operations were switched to asynchronous (non-blocking) mode.

The Or-Vnfm API has been reworked to comply with the latest finalized ETSI MANO Specification and Information Model (ETSI GS NFV-IFA 007 V2.1.1 (2016-10) Network Functions Virtualisation (NFV); Management and Orchestration; Or-Vnfm reference point - Interface and Information Model Specification). All long running operations, mostly Lifecycle Operations, have been switched to asynchronous mode. Custom extensions of the Or-Vnfm interface have been migrated from the previous version with improvements in input/output message structures. The eIUM EMS plug-in has been extended with functionality to manage Threshold Monitors and retrieve eIUM component statuses.

The Apache Ant-based Execution Engine has been updated with a new pluggable and extensible mechanism for custom ANT plug-ins. This approach allows developing and adding new ANT plug-ins by third party vendors for integration with 3rd party VNFs.

VDU types have been extended with an extensible mechanism that allows third party vendors to develop and provide third party VNF-specific KPI and Alarm managing plug-ins.

VNF Descriptor Model Extensions Integration of external components as new type of VDUs: -Allows seamlessly integrating third-party components or entire VNFs into the standard model. -Allows leveraging the full range of existing capabilities on unknown elements Integration of custom tasks into the standard or extended life cycle. -In addition to the wide range of standard tasks, new VNFM-specific tasks could be developed to interact and control third-party components. -New tasks could be used in the context of the standard or custom targets and could be combined with the standard tasks.

Integration of custom KPIs providers via new KPI provider types - New KPI providers can be developed to collect (poll or push) extended KPIs at the VDU level.

Test Info Notes:

Test use cases could be build based on the Cirrus Server and Cirrus UI FNS documents:

https://hpenterprise.sharepoint.com/teams/policy_1/SNAP%20Product%20Releases/eIUM/eIUM%209.0/Engineering/Functional%20Spec/QC1814_VNF_MANAGER_ENHANCEMENT.docx?d=w5b8d0c37a53849f49370625f1814c93a

https://hpenterprise.sharepoint.com/teams/policy_1/SNAP%20Product%20Releases/eIUM/eIUM%209.0/Engineering/Functional%20Spec/QC1814_VNFM_VIM_FNS.docx?d=w68dec071d3dc451d90c9c54e78237172

Symptoms:

Cloud Interconnect Server (formerly VNF Manager) did not have a graphical user interface. Only a command-line interface tool and Restful API were available.

The Cloud Interconnect Server (CIS) user interface is a web-based application designed for CIS operators who need to monitor and manage VNF Instances on a daily basis. It builds on top of the CIS REST API and command-line interface tools to streamline the user experience. The CIS web application uses the eIUM web framework, providing a similar look and feel as other modern web applications on the eIUM platform. For more information, see the eIUM Overview Guide or Virtualization User Guide.

ID: QXCR1001485477

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Strygin,Maxim [maxim.strygin@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

NFV OpenStack systems (like Helion) expose Telemetry services, and the Ceilometer service is one of them. It provides access to the samples collected by various meters in a virtualized environment. Existing eIUM components required comprehensive configuration to retrieve data from the Ceilometer service. Moreover, the tight integration with the OpenStack identity service was not addressed, but the Ceilometer service periodically requires a fresh security token. For more details about Telemetry API v2, see http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-telemetry- v2.html.

Resolution:

The new CeilometerConnector component allows the eIUM Session Server to collect usage data from an NFV OpenStack system (such as Helion). The integration with the OpenStack Identity service manages security tokens, which are renewed automatically for the CeilometerConnector. The new CeilometerEncapsulator and CeilometerNMESource components reuse the CeilometerConnector and allow collecting telemetry data by the eIUM Collector. Meanwhile, CeilometerRequest specifies a bridge to ResponseHandlers. The data collected can be converted into an NME and processed as any other mediation data. This allows building a metering solution for virtualized networks and solutions, and to calculate how much resources each of the v-applications consumed from NFV, and so on. Integration with Telemetry services is based on Telemetry API v2. For more details about Telemetry API v2, see http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-telemetry-v2.html. Also see the eIUM Component Reference for more information on the new components.

The Ceilometer API is already deprecated in OpenStack (see http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ceilometer/webapi/v2.html). It is suggested to use the APIs from Aodh (alarms), Gnocchi (metrics), and/or Panko (events) services.

The CeilometerConnector also only supports simple queries. No complex query structures should be expected (see http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ceilometer/webapi/v2.html#simple-query).

Test Info Notes:

List of suggested new test cases 1) SessionServer use case: CeilometerConnector receives input SNME, builds a query based on the received information, fetches data from the ceilometer, pushes result NME further. 2) Collector use case: CeilometerEncapsulator and CeilometerSource are configured to periodically fetch new data using CeilometerConnector.

Sample configurations that may help implementing test cases In attachments together with request xsd, response xsd, and other artefacts required for the complete set up.

ID: QXCR1001483486

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SMPPClientConnector needs to support sending of SMS messages over SMPP.

Resolution:

The component now supports such functionality.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently ESMEConnector exists to send SMS message. But it is not compatible with the client connector framework. Requirement came to support the functionality through client connector framework. Therefore, SMPPClientConnector is required to support sending of SMS messages through client connector framework.

Test Info Notes:

Intro:

It is highly recommended that the test person goes through the SMPP_v3_4 specification in detail so that different SMPP message parameters and functionality are understood ahead of the testing of SMPPClientConnector.

This enhancement is mostly porting of previous ESMEConnector related to SMPP from existing structure to new client connector framework. Because of this existing functionality of ESMEConnector now resides into SMPPClientConnector component. This change introduced the following new components.

1- SMPPClientConnector 2- SMPPClientEndPoint 3- SubmitSmOperation

4) Please refer to attached SMPPConfig file for SMPPClientConnector for details of the configuration.

5) Currently only SubmitSmOperation is supported as a requesting of SMPP message from client to server in the new client connector framework.

6) This enhancement also supports receiving of DeliverSm message from Server to client.

Test Setup: 1) Setup a session server and SMPPClientConnector under it. 2) Configure DynamicEndPointSelector under the connector. 3) Configure SMPPClientEndPoint under EndPointSelector. 4) Configure SubmitSmOperation under SMPPClientConnector.

Test Case:1 (Sending of SubmitSm and DataSm messages):

1) Please refer in detail the configuration of SubmitSmOperation for SubmitSm SMPP message detail and DataSmOperation for DataSm message detail that is sent from client to server.

2) Please refer in details the configuration of rule chain SmppRequestChain to check the NME attributes that helps creating the SubmitSm message that goes from client to server using Lookup rule.

3) perform siuinvoke to send the SubmitSm message. This siuinvoke is in sync with the configuration.

siuinvoke -n SmppClient -rulechain SmppRequestChain -data HostAddress 127.0.0.1 Port 2775 SmppOperAttr SubmitSmOperation SMPP_short_message "Hello SMPP Message"

Test Result: The message should go through properly.

3A) DataSm Message

Please refer in details the configuration of rule chain SmppRequestChain to check the NME attributes that helps creating the DataSm message that goes from client to server using Lookup rule. The DataSm message uses same set of NME Attributes to create a DataSm message as used in SubmitSm message. Please refer the configuration for details of DataSm message. Please use the following siuinvoke to send a DataSm message.

siuinvoke -n SmppClient -rulechain SmppRequestChain -data HostAddress 127.0.0.1 Port 2775 SmppOperAttr DataSmOperation

Test Result: The message should go through properly.

Test Case2: (Receive of DeliverSm message)

1) SMPPServer can send DeliverSm message to client. Configure DeliverSmRuleChain under SMPPClientEndPoint to execute the rule chain when a DeliverSm message is received.

2) Configure DeliverSmDecoder under SMPPClientEndPoint to decode the incoming DeliverSm message from server. Once the message is decoded properly, the DeliverSmRuleChain will be executed.

Test Result: Upon arrival of the message, NME attribute should be populated properly and the rule chain should be executed.

Test Case 3: (Add/Remove of EndPoint through Jconsole)

1) As a part of the enhancement EndPoint can be created upfront through JMX interface like JConsole. 2) If Managed=True under SMPPClientConnector, then the following MBeans are registered.

a) DynamicEndPointSelector, SMPPClientEndPoint and SMPPClientConnection.

2) Currently only DynamicEndPointSelector (DEPS) supports adding and removing EndPoints on demand.

3) DEPS currently supports 3 JMX operations. AddEndPoint, RemoveEndPoint and ListAllEndPoints.

4) To create an EndPoint from DEPS through JConsole , please pass comma separated values of the keys that are configured under DEPS in the configuration in the same order. EndPoint should be created and it's mbean should registered and visible in JConsole.

5) This above created endpoint w

ill be used by siuinvoke without any need of another endpoint creation if same key vaues are passed.

6) To remove the endpoint from DEPS through JConsole, the endpoint key will be required and it is not the comma separated values passed in add end point.

7) To successfully remove an EndPoint, it is expected to list all the endpoint first through listEndPoint operation and get the key of an endpoint there. Once the key is obtained, then the key cab be passed to the remove endpoint operation. The endpoint should be removed through that and the mbeans and all must be unregistered.

Test Case 4: (Create/Close connection - JConsole)

1) Create/Close connection can b

e performed through JMX interface like JConsole once SMPPClientEndPoint is created. 2) Create connection is done at the level of SMPPClientEndPoint.

3) CloseConnection is done at the connection level. That user can execute the close operation that is found at each connection MBean. Connection should be closed and mbean should unregistered.

Test 5: Each connections' state and JMX attributes should be visible in the JConsole. For different events like sending of messages, server failure etc corresponding JMX attributes should be updated.

Test 6: If after successful sending operation once, the server goes down, then the stales connections must be removed from the EndPoint and corresponding MBean should be unregistered from Mbean server. It should retry to send the message based on the attempts and retry interval configured under EndPointSelector.

Test Case 7: 1) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is configured under SMPPClientEndPoint, then connections will be used based on first in/first out order instead of roundrobin which is default. This can be verified through total message sent JMX attribute of a connection. IN such case only one connection will be seen as used as long as it is valid and exists in pool.

2) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is NOT configured, then each created connection will be used in a roundrobin basis to send the SubmitSm message and TotalMessageSent counter will be updated for each connection.

3) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is configured and if a connection is idle for MaxConnectionIdleTime time then that connection will be removed from the pool. The connections will be reduced to the MinConnections configured value under EndPoint.

4) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is NOT configured, then valid and active connections will remain in the pool to be used by next request.

Test Case 8:

Please refer to the documentation of SMPPClientConnector, SMPPClientEndPoint, SubmitSmOperation for details of the operation and SMPP message details.

Test Case 9: (TestSMS send feature)

This testing is about to sending of a Test SMS when a new connection is about to be created and an SMPP session is bound successfully to an SMPP server.

1) In order to enable this feature, please configure SendSMSOnConnetionOpen=true under SMPPClientEndPoint.

2) Configure the sub-node with the name TestMessageCreator under SMPPClientEndPoint.

3) This TestMessageCreator sub-node represents the SMSMessageCreator component. Please refer to the attached config for details of it.

4) The attached config represents the attributes that will be used to send the SMPP message of either SUBMIT_SM type or DATA_SM type. If needed then please refer to the SMPP version 3.4 specification for details of the values used against each attributes.

5) Configure CommandType under the TestMessageCreator sub-node in order to determine whether the test message will be of SUBMIT_SM type or DATA_SM type.

Scenario 1:

If CommandType is configured with SUBMIT_SM value then a SUBMIT_SM type test SMS will be sent to SMPP Server.

Scenario 2:

If CommandType is configured with DATA_SM value then a DATA_SM type test SMS will be sent to SMPP Server.

Scenario 3:

If any invalid value is passed for which an SMS cannot be se nt or the SMS sent gets a negative response back from the SMPP server, there exception should be thrown and that connection should not be created. The connected session should be unbind and closed then.

Scenario 4: Please refer to the documentation of the SMPPClientEndPoint and SMSMessageCreator component for description of these.

ID: QXCR1001482576

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SMTPClientConnector did not support specifying an explicit date for the Date header field of an e-mail.

Resolution:

The component now supports such functionality.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently SMTPClientConnector doesn't support specifying an explicit date to the Date header field of the email. It is always default system specified. Customer wanted to have a support for explicitly specifying a date for Date header field that represents the creation date of the message.

Test Info Notes:

Setup: Please find the attached sample config for reference.

1) Configure SMTPClientConnector under a session server.

2) Configure SentDateAttribute under SMTPClientConnector. It must be be configured through an NME attribute of LongAttribute or TimeAttribute type only.

3) The SentDateAttribute attribute specifies the date at which the email message is created and ready for delivery.

4) Run the connector using the siuinvoke. It can be found from the description of the connector config attached.

Test Case: 1) When No SentDateAttribute attribute is configured.

Result: Email should be sent as is and the email message creation date should be as specified by the system.

Test Case 2: When SentDateAttribute is configured to a LongAttribute where a long value is passed specifying a particular date.

Result: Email should be sent with the the email message creation date set with the value specified through LongAttribute type NME attribute.

Test Case 3: When SentDateAttribute is configured to a TimeAttribute. In this case the value must be passed in the string form of "mm/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss" . Where mm - month dd - date yyyy - year hh -- hour mm -- minute ss -- seconds

Result: Email should be sent with the the email message creation date set with the value specified through TimeAttribute type NME attribute.

Test Case 4: If either no value is obtained from NME attribute, a warning message will be displayed in the log. In such case, system specified value will be used as the email message creation date.

Test Case4: Please check the documentation for new attribute SentDateAttribute under SMTPClientConnector.

Verifier: 

Test Plan
=========
Case 1:
~~~~~~
1. Do not configure 'SentDateAttribute' attribute.
2. Start smtp conn.
3. Execute siuinvoke :-
siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" 
FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" Subject Hi Content Hello

3. Start smtp conn
4. Execute siuinvoke :-
siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" 
FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" Subject Hi Content Hello SentDateLong 1462250419690

Case 3:
~~~~~~
1. 'SentDateAttribute' is configured to a TimeAttribute i.e. SentDateAttribute = SentDateTime. 
2. Pass the date in string form "mm/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss" i.e. "05/03/2016 10:10:10"
3. Start smtp conn
4. Execute siuinvoke :- 
siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" 
FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" Subject Hi Content Hello SentDateTime "05/03/2016 
10:10:10"

~~~~~~

siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" 
FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" Subject Hi Content Hello

~~~~~~

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a new JSON transformation framework.

Resolution:

JSON has been added to/from the serialization framework, and a generic serialization API has been added. BeanToJson and JsonToBean transformers have also been added. The LogNMERule has also been enhanced to add logging in JSON format, plus Umbrella SNME support. Furthermore, the new SerializerRule can serialize/deserialize NMEs using any available serializer. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Test Info Notes:

Test new transformers and rules.

Symptoms:

Support is needed for a component that can execute rules according to a flexible schedule.

Resolution:

The new TimerExecutor component allows scheduling rule execution in a flexible configuration manner. Also see the new TimerRule component, which can create, update, delete or fetch timers. This rule can have a common configuration with the TimerExecutor connector. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

Timer executor is a connector that execute timers created by timer rule

Test Info Notes:

1. Confiure timer rule and executor. Use log rule as rule chain to invoke from timer executor 2. Create a new timer using timer rule with nearest fire time 3. Waite for a new entry from log rule with timer properties defined in timer rule 4. Create a new timer with start/end date and define fire time as cron expression 5. Check if a new timer executed in defined time range, new fire time calculated properly and timer removed if fire time > end date

Use case should be checked in different configurations 1. Using flat NME or SNME. In case if SNMEType is configured, connector will work with SNME, otherwise with flat NME 2. In case of using SNME, connector can be configured to support umbrella SNME, for this purpose it should be configured SNMERoot attribute 3. Connector can be configured to process several partitions. Statistical partition configuration should be defined in Partitions attribute. For dynamic configuration, partition service should be configured, see QXCR1001492766 for details 4. In case of High Availability connector should process partitions depends on running session servers. Partitions are assigned by MS component TimersClusterManager, see QXCR1001492766 for details

ID: QXCR1001478035

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SyslogFormatter restricted log messages to 1024 bytes.

Resolution:

The new MaxMessageLength configuration attribute has been added to SyslogFormatter to allow larger messages to be logged. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

Hello Lukasz,

We have an issue about SyslogFormatter. Could you please quote cost and time frame to enhance below requirement? - Requirement SyslogFormatter (in the Logging with SvrLogManager) can send over 1k byte syslog message. Please find attached for our config.

- Background We thought to log long SQL with LogNMERule. But when the SQL exceeds 1k byte, only 1k byte is logged (the rest SQL was cut).

We understand it's compliant with RFC1364. https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3164.txt 4.1 syslog Message Parts The full format of a syslog message seen on the wire has three discernable parts. The first part is called the PRI, the second part is the HEADER, and the third part is the MSG. The total length of the packet MUST be 1024 bytes or less.

However, we found rsyslog can handle over 1k byte message. http://www.rsyslog.com/doc/v5-stable/configuration/global/index.html#true- global-directives $MaxMessageSize <size_nbr>, default 2k - allows to specify maximum supported message size (both for sending and receiving).

Weâ€™d like to use it, so we're considering to enhance IUM. (It haven't been decided yet.)

Best regards, =========================== Keita Nakagawa (ä¸­å·æµå¤ª)

Test Info Notes:

Configure SyslogFormatter under /Logging configuration sub node of your SIU server. Use LogNMERule to print a large log message (bigger than 1024 bytes). Without the patch, only first 1024 bytes will be logged. With patch, you can configure MaxMessageLength under /Logging to specify bigger log message size.

Please refer to the attached config file

Submitter Text Notes:

Found in Version : vSRF Found in Build : RC2 Target Version : 83FP01 Tester : Arun

Observation:

1. On trying to run multiple instances in the same machine, observed that the Repository Server and the WebappServer instance does not come up and does not run for the second instance because of the Shutdown port .

The Serverport mentioned in the "server.xml" file in the path "/var/opt/SIU_83RC2/repositoryserver/conf" is "8008"

<Server port="8008" shutdown="SHUTDOWN">.

ID: QXCR1001466029

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SMTPClientConnector needs to support sending of emails over SSL.

Resolution:

SMTPClientConnector now supports sending of emails over SSL. See the eIUM Component Reference and the EnableSSL attribute of the SMTPEndPoint component for more information.

Submitter Text Notes:

SMTPClientConnector doesn't support SSL as of now. It needs to support SSL connection to connect to SMTP server.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure session server and SMTPClientConnector under it to send emails to SMTPServer.

2) Configure SMTPEndpoint to point to SMTP server.

3) Please refer to the attached sample config for configuration.

IMP NOTE:

**************HOW TO GENERATE KEYSTORE AND TRUSTSTORE **************************** KEYSTORE will be used at the JAMES SMTP server side and TRUSTSTORE will be referred by SmtpClientConnector.

When the client wants to connect server through SSL, then the server sends its certificate to client. Then the client must refer to it's configured truststore to verify that certificate. That's why beforehand itself, the client's truststore must contain James SMTP server's certificate.

Follow the following steps to generate stores.

1) Generate a Keystore to be used at the server side. Run the following command to generate a keystore.

keytool â€genkey â€alias james â€keyalg RSA â€keystore james_keystore.jks

After the enter it will ask for details OrgUnit name, company name etc. Fill all details. AFter all it will ask for keystore password. Enter that and remember it. Configure this in the sections mentioned below for James server.

2) Generate a .cer certificate from the above created keystore.

keytool â€export â€alias james â€file james.cer â€keystore james_keystore.jks

This will create a james.cer certificate which will be added to a truststore referred by client.

3) Create a truststore and add the above created james.cer to it.

keytool â€import â€v â€trustcacerts â€alias james â€file james.cer â€keystore james_truststore

Here a new truststore james_truststore will be created and it will contain the cert that server will send while SSL handshake happens. The client will refer to this file.

*******************NOTE FOR APACHE JAMES SSL CONFIGURATION***************

Now in order to test SSL connection, the following pre-reqs must be satisfied. The SMTP server must provide a certificate as its credential. At the client side, the certificate provided by the server must be added to a truststore and SMTPClientConnector must refer to the truststore in order to validate the server as a trusted one. Through this the SSL handshake will be successful before communicating SMTP messages.

Apache James can be used a SMTP server with SSL enabled at it side. To enable SSL in Apache James

1 - Start the server from bin directory. Shut it down. It should have created the directory \apps\james under installed location. 2 - Go to SAR-INF directory under it. It should have 3 files config.xml, assembly.xml, enviroment.xml file under it. Sample files with SSL enabled sections are added in the CR. Please look for SSL/TLS sections in all these files and it is self-explanatory.

3 - The Server certificate should exist in install-dir/apps/james/conf directory as required by the SSL section of config.xml.

<sockets> <server-sockets> <factory name="plain" class="org.apache.avalon.cornerstone.blocks.sockets.DefaultServerSocketFactory"/> <factory name="ssl" class="org.apache.avalon.cornerstone.blocks.sockets.TLSServerSocketFactory"> <ssl-factory> <keystore> <file>conf/james_keystore.jks</file> <password>james_keystore</password> <key-password>james_keystore</key-password> <type>JKS</type> <protocol>TLS</protocol> <algorithm>SunX509</algorithm> <authenticate-client>false</authenticate-client> </keystore> </ssl-factory> </factory> </server-sockets> <client-sockets> <factory name="plain" class="org.apache.avalon.cornerstone.blocks.sockets.DefaultSocketFactory"/> </client-sockets> </sockets>

This should start the SMTP server with SSL being enabled.

****************

4) Under SMTPEndPoint configure the following attribute.

EnableSSL=tru e TrustStoreFile=<path to the truststore file> TrustStorePassword=<password of the trust store file> TrustStoreType=JKS -- default is this. Or else any other certificate type according to the cert.

5) Make sure we have an SMTP server listening for SMTP messages over SSL on a port. That IP address and port must be configured in SMTPEndpoint.

6) For local testing, I had used SSL enabled Apache James. The Apache james config files and keystore of it, TrustStore files for client along with SMTP server ceritificate are attached to the CR.

7) Try to have 2 truststore files, one containing SMTP server certificates and another without. This will help confirming SSL connections success or failure. The attached truststore files are like this. Once contains james.cer from SMTP server cert and another doesn't.

Test Result:

Test case 1: 1) If the SMTP server certificate is added to trust store then the email communication will happen successfully after a successful SSL handshake.

2) If the SMTP server certificate is NOT added to trust store then the SSL handshake will fail. No email will be sent.

Test Case 2: When EnableSSL=false, then it will try to send email without SSL. This is existing behavior before the enhancement. This should work fine.

Test Case 3: Check for documentation of the above mentioned attributes under SMTPEndPoint.

ID: QXCR1001463909

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SMTPClientConnector needs to support attachments.

Resolution:

SMTPClientConnector now supports file, binary, text and composite attachments.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently SMTPClientConnector doesn't support sending of attachments. Customer requirements came to support.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure session server and SMTPClientConnector under it to send emails to SMTPServer.

2) Configure SMTPEndpoint to point to SMTP server.

3) Please refer to the attached sample config for configuration.

4) Configure Attachments attribute under SMTPClientConnector to define the sub-nodes of Attachments. The following attachments are supported. Please refer to the component reference of Attachments for details of the component.

Behavior of each attachment

1 - FileAttachment

a) This attachment should send the files from the file system as the attachment in the email. The Files attribute can be configured with static file location or through dynamic NME attribute where the file location can be obtained at run time.

b) If a file is missing then warning will be displayed and then the process will be continue skipping that file.

2 - BinaryAttachment

a) This attachment should read the content of the Binary Attribute and send it as attachment in the email.

b) The BinaryAttribute must be configured with NME attribute from where the binary data will be fetched from.

c) MIMEType specifies the MIME type of the binary data. Default will be text/plain.

d) If BinaryAttribute content is null, then this attachment will be skipped.

e) If BinaryAttribute is present and no name is obtained through AttachmentName config attribute then exception will be thrown and email will not be sent.

3 - TextAttachment

a) This attachment should read the content of the StringAttribute and send it as attachment in the email.

b) The StringAttribute must be configured with NME attribute from where the text data will be fetched from.

c) MIMESubType specifies the MIME sub-type of the text data. Default will be plain.

d) If StringAttribute content is null, then this attachment will be skipped.

e) If StringAttribute is present and no name is obtained through AttachmentName config attribute then email will be sent with the default name assigned by the system with .txt extension.

4- CompositeAttachment

a) A CompositeAttachment is a grouping of attachments, where inside it, All the above attachment types can be configured through Attachments config attribute.

b) A CompositeAttachment can contain another CompositeAttachment under it which further can contain the above 3 types of attachment further.

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001463199

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

StringTokenizerRule should support multi-characters as delimiters to tokenize the string, and should also handle empty token values.

Resolution:

StringTokenizerRule has been enhanced to support multi-characters as a delimiter to tokenize the input string. It also now handles an empty token value. The new UseRegexDelimiter configuration attribute has been added to StringTokenizerRule, which when set to true, provides both the features of a multi-character delimiter and handling empty tokens. For more information, see the eIUM Component Reference.

Test Info Notes:

Configure StringTokenizerRule with multichar as Delimiter.

e.g. say the delimiter is <f> and the input string is : abcde<f><f>ghfijk<lmnofpqr>stuv<f> --------------------------------------- Current implement will tokenize it as : --------------------------------------- Token 1 : abcde Token 2 : gh Token 3 : ijk Token 4 : lmno Token 5 : pqr Token 6 : stuv

---------------- Expectation is : ---------------- Token 1 : abcde Token 2 : Token 3 : ghfijk<lmnofpqr>stuv Token 4 :

Token 2 and 4 are empty tokens.

If you configure new attribute UseRegexDelimiter under StringTokenizerRule and set it to true then expected behavior can be achieved.

Run regression for StringTokenizerRule.

ID: QXCR1001459789

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The WriteToFileRule needs to support SNMEs, along with Base64 decoding, while writing to a file.

Resolution:

The component now supports such functionality.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently, WriteToFileRule doesn't support SNME and also Base64 decoding. Requirements came to support read value from SNME to write to file and also perform Base64 decoding on the fly while writing to file.

Test Info Notes:

This CR is to test the SNME support of WriteToFileRule and also the base64 decoding to be performed by it.

1) Setup WriteToFileRule in the rule chain. Make sure an SNME is passed to it. It can be done by having an NMEConversionRule before it. Please refer to the attached config to CR.

Testing can be done using following phases.

Case1: ---Support of SNME-------

1) Configure SNMEType = <Namespace>:<Root-Type-Name> This SNMEType represents the namespace and root attribute name of the SNME that will be passed to the rule at runtime.

Test Case:

1) Configure Attributes attribute. All the attributes configured here be valid SNME attribute reference to the SNME rootype. If the SNME attribute reference is an invalid one, then exception will be thrown.

2) Now if no configuration exception happens, the values read from the SNME from these attributes and will written to file.

3) If any SNME attribute is missing the value, then it will be skipped from being written and there will no value between the separators in the file. Like A,,C -- consider B is missing.

Case 2: --- Support of Base64 encoding/Decoding --- (both in NME and SNME modes)

1) Configure Base64 config attribute under WriteToFileRule . This attribute can take values encode or decode for according purpose.

2) Now if Base64 attribute is configured to encode, then the data will be encoded and written to the file. If the value is decode, the value will be decoded and then written to the file.

3) In binary mode, Base64 decoding will be only applied on the SNME attribute reference or NME attribute of String type value as it is only the String Attribute that is expected to be in base64 encoded or decoded form. It will not be applied in any other type attribute value, to be written to the file.

4) In text mode, if Base64 is configured, then the text/string line created from all the values of Attributes attribute will be written in base64 encoded or decoded form depending on the value of Base64 attribute.

5) If the value of the Base64 attribute is not encode or decode (case-senstivie) then exception will be thrown.

Case 3: --------------------------------------------------

Now both support of SNME and Base64 decoding support can be combined for test case. Where a string read data from SNME will be in base 64 encoded/decoded form , therefore will be written to file.

-------------------------------- Case 4: Please check the documentation of WriteToFileRule for the new attributes SNMEType and Base64 information.

****************************************************************

SIUINVOKES can be used with the attached config and NMESchema.

siuinvoke -n ReadWriteRule -rulechain rwchain -data sourceAttr "f1" strAttr "V3JpdGUgdGhpcyBsaW5lIHRvIGZpbGUgYW5kIHJlYWQgdGhpcyBsaW5lIGZyb20gZmlsZS4NCg==" Directory "C:/Users/parijaj\Desktop\IUMTasks\2016\ReadWriteFileRule-Tepco\output" base64Read encode base64Write decode

ID: QXCR1001459149

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The ReadFromFileRule needs to support SNMEs, along with Base64 encoding, while reading a file.

Resolution:

The component now supports such functionality.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently, ReadFromFileRule doesn't support SNME and also Base64 encoding. Requirements came to support placing of read value into SNME and also perform Base64 encoding on the fly while reading from file.

Test Info Notes:

This CR is to test the SNME support of ReadFromFileRule and also the base64 encoding to be performed by it.

1) Setup ReadFromFileRule in the rule chain. Make sure an SNME is passed to it. It can be done by having an NMEConversionRule before it. Please refer to the attached config to CR.

Testing can be done using following phases.

Case1: ---Support of SNME-------

1) Configure SNMEType = <Namespace>:<Root-Type-Name> This SNMEType represents the namespace and root attribute name of the SNME that will be passed to the rule at runtime.

Test Case:

1) Configure OutputAttribute. It must be a valid attribute reference to the SNME rootype. If the SNME attribute reference is an invalid one, then exception will be thrown.

2) If the OutputAttribute (SNME attribute reference) is not of type String nor Byte-array type, then exception will be thrown.

3) Now if no configuration exception happens, the data read from the file will be placed in the SNME attribute reference specified through OutputAttribute.

4) If the OutputAttribute is of String type then String value will be displayed in the attribute or else Byte-array.

Case 2: --- Support of Base64 Encoding/Decoding --- (both in NME and SNME modes)

1) Configure Base64 attribute to enable Base64 encoding/decoding while reading from file.

Test Result:

1) If the value is encode then data read from the file will be encoded and then placed into OutputAttribute. If the value is decode then data read from file will be decoded and will be placed into OutputAttribute.

2) If the value of the Base64 attribute is not either encode or decode (case-sensitive) then exception will be thrown.

3) If the OutputAttribute is not of String type either in NME or SNME, then Base64 attribute configuration will have no impact.

Case 3: --------------------------------------------------

Now both support of SNME and Base64 encoding support can be combined for test case. Where a read data from file will be Base64 encoded/decoded and placed into an SNME attribute reference of type String.

-------------------------------- Case 4: Please check the documentation of ReadFromFileRule for the new Attribute SNMEType and Base64.

siuinvoke -n ReadWriteRule -rulechain rwchain -data sourceAttr "f1" strAttr "V3JpdGUgdGhpcyBsaW5lIHRvIGZpbGUgYW5kIHJlYWQgdGhpcyBsaW5lIGZyb20gZmlsZS4NCg==" Directory "C:/Users/parijaj\Desktop\IUMTasks\2016\ReadWriteFileRule-Tepco\output" base64Read encode base64Write decode

ID: QXCR1001454558

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SSHEndPoint needs to support automatic removal of idle connections from its pool.

Resolution:

The component now supports automatic removal of idle connections from its pool via the new MaxConnectionIdleTime attribute.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently in EndPoints once a connection object is created, it remains in the pool forever as active connection. In non-peak situations many created connection need not exist as only one or two connections may be enough to server all requests. In such cases the pool is still full with unnecessary active connections. Customer needs the support to reduce the number of active connections in the pool in non-peak time, thereby releasing resources.

Test Info Notes:

The scope this CR's testing is SSHEndPoint.

1) Configure a session server. 2) Configure SSHClientConnector and SSHEndPoint under it.

3) Configure MaxConnectionIdleTime and MinConnections under SSHEndPoint. Please refer to the SSHEndPoint documentation for description of these two attributes.

4) Please find the attached sample configuration.

5) Run the SSHClientConnector to send SSH commands to destination server.

6) Sample siuinvoke: Please change as per your configuration.

siuinvoke.exe -n SSHClientConn -rulechain ssh_rulechain -data SSHServerHost 15.154.118.8 SSHServerPort 22 SSHServerUserName root SSHServerPassword siu98 SSHCommand ls SSHPrivateKeyFile "C:/Users/parijaj/.ssh/id_rsa" SSHPassphrase jimmy

*********** Test Case 1:

1) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is not configured or configured to Zero, then there should be no change in the functionality of SSHClientConnector and SSHEndPoint.

2) If MaxConnectionIdleTime is configured to less than Zero, configuration exception should be thrown specifying that MaxConnectionIdleTime cannot be less than zero.

********** Test Case 2: (Introduction of MaxConnectionIdleTime=30000 and MinConnections=0 ) -- MinConnections zero means no idle connections will be kept in the pool once time elapses.

1) Now when MaxConnectionIdleTime is configured to greater than zero, then connections which are not used beyond this time period will be removed.

2) Configure MaxConnectionIdleTime=30000 (30sec) under SSHEndPoint.

3) Now for example configure the NumConnections=5 in SSHEndPoint. This means in peak max 5 connections will be created in the endpoint.

4) Just have a traffic where all 5 connections are created in the endpoint and remains as it is. Please observe and make sure once 5 connections are created just send 1 by 1 requests where only one connection can serve the request and rest 4 need not be used.

Test Result:

In the above scenario, once 5 connections are created and then 1 connection is capable of handling incoming requests, it will be visible in the log that rest of the 4 connections are removed from the pool after the MaxConnectionIdleTime time period which is 30000 ms here. This ensures that idle connections are removed and need not be kept at pool.

********** Test Case 3:

In extension to test case 2, when all the 4 connections are removed from the pool, don't send any request and let the last left connection to be come idle.

Test Result: In the log it will be visible that last connection also is removed. Any subsequent request will create a new connection to the endpoint remote server.

*********** Test Case 4:

1) Configure MinConnections=2 and NumConnections=5 and REPEAT Test case 2.

Test Result: Now that MinConnections=2 and when one connection is handling all requests and the EndPoint will start removing the idle connections. However out of 5, 3 connections will be removed (as per logs) and 2 connections will remain active and will be there in the pool always. The pool will not be empty.

*********** Test case 5: Same as TestCase 4, except MinConnections is not configured or configured as Zero, then all the idle connections will be removed. It will be exact same as Test Case 2.

*********** Test Case 6: Please check the documentation of SSHEndPoint for attributes MaxConnectionIdleTime and MinConnections. They should exist there.

Symptoms:

eIUM security parameters and security algorithms and ciphers should be configurable.

Resolution:

The new configuration file "security.properties" has been created under the <VARROOT>/securityserver/conf/ directory. This contains the default values for all the security parameters. If this file does not contain any security parameter (missing parameter), then the old default properties will be used.

Submitter Text Notes:

We need to get all relevant security and encryption algorithm/parameters configurable for the eIUM Security Server and for the other processes in eIUM deployment. This configuration must be available to the end user in the following ways: 1) For the Security Server configuration shall be done in the deployment descriptor file at siu\apps\web\security-server\docroot\META-INF\context.xml 2) For the other regular IUM Servers such configuration shall be made available via setting System Properties for the corresponing process in IUM Config.

The instrumentation shall include at least following classes with hard-coded configuration: com.hp.usage.security.cert.CertificateGeneratorConfig com.hp.usage.security.cert.KeyGeneratorConfig com.hp.usage.security.ssl.KeyStoreConfig com.hp.usage.security.ssl.SecureRandomConfig com.hp.usage.security.ssl.SSLContextConfig and other relevant classes.

Symptoms:

Resolution:

To make rulechains configurable in the included eIUM product templates, re-export the templates with the LaunchPad.

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM83 RC5 RHEL 6 x64 Java 7u75 ============================

It was found that annotated template of Collector with 2 predefined rules in AggregationScheme could not be used to add more rules during configuration creation process.

Attached template is enhanced version of original template. It provides drop-down list of available rules on "edit template" window. But it is not possible to finish this configuration, as long as 2 pre-configured rules couldn't pass annotations calculation.

So using current language it is possible to create customized rules from list only in case that there are no predefined rules in configuration.

I think this is also valid for other types of sub-nodes which could be selected/added to already existing.

Test Info Notes:

To customize rule list, next annotations should be added: @Param(id="RULE_NAMES", value="$(sort $(name $(select /components/rules/*)))") [/deployment]

@Param(id="SCHEMENAME_RULE_NAMES", value="$(sort $(name $(select Aggregator/SchemeName/*)))") @Param(id="RuleNames_SchemeName", name="Rule name", type=ConfigEntry, default="{RULE_NAMES[0]}", enum="{RULE_NAMES}{SCHEMENAME_RULE_NAMES}", ref="/components/rules/{RuleNames_SchemeName} [/deployment/host/servername]

[/deployment/host/servername/Aggregator]

ClassName=Aggregator Description=Aggregator consists of a single AssignCallType aggregation scheme SchemeNames=SchemeName

[/deployment/host/servername/Aggregator/SchemeName] ClassName=AggregationScheme @Customizable(param="RuleNames_SchemeName", numvalues="1-unbounded") RuleNames=

Template converter was updated to generate collector templates with rule customization. So, please, run Launchpad -> Export -> Export templates to obtain new templates.

ID: QXCR1001261676

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kopylov,Sergey [sergey.kopylov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed in the LDAPConnector for additional connection handling capabilities, namely: adding connection timeouts for bound- and pre-bound connections; limiting the number of allowed opened connections (total and per client); and, providing a configurable buffer size.

Resolution:

The component now includes new configurable attributes to support this functionality (MaxConnections, MaxConnectionsPerIP, IdleTimeout, PreBindTimeout, and BufferSize). For additional details, see the IUM Component Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

It is required to enhance the LDAPConnector connection handling capabilities: - add connection timeouts fort bound and pre bound connections; - limit the number of allowed opened connections (total and per client); - provide configurable buffer size;

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: HP-UX
Operating System Version: B.11.23
Operating System Architecture: IA64N
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.06.00 FP03 2011/04/04"
Patch: IUM60FP03Verizon.20130123-0325 (005-RC3)
Java Version: 1.5.0.26
Java Home: /opt/java1.5/jre
============================================================

It was verified that with previous patch build (IUM60FP03Verizon.20121219-0331) all requested new
functionality attributes work as expected.

#1 MaxConnections attribute limits overall number of incoming connections. In case that limit is
reached and additional connection tried to be open it is discarded with following logging:

NioProcessor-3 (ldap) WARNING: Total number of sessions exceeds limit 2, closing incoming session
(0x00000003: nio socket, server, /127.0.0.1:52074 => /127.0.0.1:9389) 

#2 MaxConnectionsPerIP attribute limits overall number of incoming connections from unique IP
address. In case that limit is reached and additional connection tried to be open it is discarded
with following logging:

NioProcessor-2 (ldap) WARNING: Number of sessions per IP address 16.52.177.31 exceeds limit 1,
closing incoming session (0x00000002: nio socket, server, /16.52.177.31:60889 => /16.53.145.164:9389) 

#3 IdleTimeout attribute limits time during which bound session (passed BindRequest->BindResponse
sequence) could stay idle without RW operations performed. When this timeout reached session is
closed gracefully by sending NoticeOfDisconnect notification. Following logging could be found:

(ldap) WARNING: Closing already bound session (0x00000001: nio socket, server, /16.52.177.31:60876
=> /16.53.145.164:9389) by timeout

NoticeOfDisconnect notification could be found in tcpdump and looks as following:

ldap.LDAPMessage
LDAPMessage extendedResp(0) (UNAVAILABLE: The server will disconnect!)
resultCode: unavailable (52)
errorMessage: UNAVAILABLE: The server will disconnect!
responseName: 1.3.6.1.4.1.1466.20036 (iso.3.6.1.4.1.1466.20036)

#4 PreBindTimeout attribute limits time between tcp connection established by client and BindRequest
sent to server. If this timeout is reached connection is closed without any notification.  Following
logging could be found:

(ldap) WARNING: Closing not bound session (0x00000002: nio socket, server, /127.0.0.1:52521 =>
/127.0.0.1:9389) by timeout

#5 BufferSize attribute is internal one and couldn't be tested in functional testing. Thus it was
passed through smoke testing to verify that its configuration doesn't affect functionality

ID: QXCR1001544634

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

If JCE Unlimited Strength ("unlimited encryption") is not installed in user's JVM, IUM activation will fail telling that it will not be able to encrypt user's sensitive responses (e.g. passwords).

Resolution:

Recommended way to fix this is to install JCE Unlimited Strength.

If this is not possible for any reason, the workaround is to provide option

  -A EncryptResponses=false

when calling eIUM installer, activator, deactivator and uninstaller. Options passed to installer and uninstaller will be passed to activator and deactivator automatically.

The user must be aware, however, that it will result in all user responses written in cleartext to activateIUM.ini and transcript file (if requested with -w <transcript_file>).

Submitter Text Notes:

During activation, users are receiving:

Error while performing action 'Writing activateIUM.ini': Could not encrypt value for 'DATABASEPASSWORD': Illegal key size or default parameters Do you want to continue? (yes/no)?no

This is caused by attempt to use AES-256 cipher to write activateIUM.ini file while java unlimited security is not installed.

This must be mitigated in 3 ways, all of them are obligatory:

1. Provide information in the Troubleshooting.

2. Check for this problem specifically and warn the user in advance with appropriate message (existing validator class could be used).

3. Provide an option to activator to allow the user to use the cipher of lesser strength, but with an obligatory password.

Test Info Notes:

Please verify that, WITHOUT unlimited JCE:

- calling installation + activation without extra options will fail before activation wizard is shown with explanatory message and a hint how to avoid the problem - once failed, it's possible to call the activation specifying -A EncryptResponses=false and it will succeed - as a result, activateIUM.ini will be written with cleartext passwords (if any) - command "migratedb configure -useConfig no -- list" will show proper database URLs for databases with passwords (if any) (this means that DB parameters could be properly decrypted) - on reactivation, the passwords entered will be set for corresponding fields but masked - start a new fresh installation + activation by calling ./installer -A EncryptResponses=false -w responses.txt. Both the installation and subsequent activation should succeed (options are passed to activator). File responses.txt should have all passwords non-encrypted - uninstallation will fail on starting the deactivation (with an explanatory message) unless -A EncryptResponses=false is provided for uninstallation as well

To verify with UNLIMITED JCE:

- calling installation + activation without extra options will succeed - activateIUM.ini will have all passwords encrypted - command "migratedb configure -useConfig no -- list" will show proper database URLs for databases with encrypted passwords (if any) (this means that DB parameters could be properly decrypted)

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC8
Win 7x64
Java 8u131
---------------

It was verified that proper exception is thrown prior to activation in case that JCE is of limited
encryption strength. Thus it is not possible to start activation without unlim JCE by default,
preventing customer from unexpected failures later.

If it is required to bypass this restriction, option -A EncryptResponses=false on activation
restart, enforcing not encrypting passwords. In this case all external DB passwords are left in
clear text in activateIUM.ini. All embedded DB passwords will have empty values.

eIUM90 RC7 RHEL6 x64 Java8u112 ---------------

Deactivator doesn't attempt to start ConfigServer. This causes an issue for uninstallation of stopped eIUM90. Even security server is started, CS is not, thus steps like "backup config" and "remove config tree from host" are failing.

On Linux they are failing but deactivation is continued:

04/16/2017 21:22:55.109 PDT Thread-11 (Util) INFORMATIVE: Error: Could not contact configuration server using URL: file:/var/opt/SIU_90_sec/ConfigServer.iorCannot contact the configuration server 04/16/2017 21:22:55.157 PDT main (ProtectedRuleChain) ERROR: Error in protected rule chain 'Backing up host configuration to '/opt/SIU_90_sec/uninstall/host-bsasg.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net_backup.config'', will be calling recovery chain

...

04/16/2017 21:22:56.535 PDT main (ProtectedRuleChain) ERROR: Exception in protected rule chain 'Removing host configuration from Config Server': Could not remove node '/deployment/bsasg.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net': Cannot contact the configuration server 04/16/2017 21:22:56.536 PDT main (ProtectedRuleChain) ERROR: Error in protected rule chain 'Removing host configuration from Config Server', will be calling recovery chain

But on Windows deactivation freezes forever on step "backuping config".

Test Info Notes:

Please ensure that, on a CS host:

- if CS is up before starting deactivation, no attempt is made to start a second CS - if CS is down before starting deactivation, CS is started, configuration is saved to a file in uninstall directory, then CS is stopped before continuing deactivation - if CS could not be started for any reason, after 2 minutes timeout, deactivation should continue without asking the user any additional questions. Log file and final summary screen should mention failed actions (CS start, config save and remove)

On a non-CS host, obviously, no attempt should be done to start CS even if it's not accessible.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC8
RHEL6 x64
Java 8u131
---------------

It was verified that in case of CS stopped before uninstallation it will be started by deactivator
to backup config and then remove it from CS.

In all other cases duplicated CS isn't started by uninstaller (deactivator).

If CS couldn't be started within 2m deactivation will fail but uninstallation could be continued.

It was found that during reactivation (for example DB type from embedded to external) SIUJava.ini file is updated, but host defaults not. ID: QXCR1001542667

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC6 RHEL7 x64 Java 8u112 ================

It was found that in case that main DB is reactivated from embedded to external there are problems in CIS/JDS dbs reactivation.

Problem is that JDSUSEEMBEDDEDDB and CIS_USEEMBEDDEDDB values are not updated from true to false in activateIUM.ini, thus migratedb launched in activation still tries to work with embedded db and fails.

Test Info Notes:

Please ensure that controls on Activator's CIS DB and JDS screens are properly initialized and enabled :

- if Embedded DB is activated, allow selection of either Embedded or External DB for CIS and JDS - if Embedded DB is NOT activated, checkbox for "Use Embedded" should be disabled with value "false" (unchecked), thus allowing configuring the External DB - previous point should also hold if you are reactivating and changing main DB from Embedded to External (checkbox should be forcibly set to "false" and disabled even if previously CIS/JDS were using Embedded DB)

ID: QXCR1001541498

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Golubev,Alexander [alexander.golubev@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC5a RHEL 7 x64 Java 8u112 ====================

MySQL group replication instance was created. Idea was to try to activate eIUM over it. Activation failed since table DATABASECHANGELOG doesn't contain primary key, and such type of tables isn't supported for MySQL group replication.

We should add something like this to some generic change log file and include this change log into all all.xml change logs:

    <changeSet author="eIUM" id="1445089444925-0" dbms="mysql">
      <addPrimaryKey columnNames="dateexecuted,orderexecuted" constraintName="pk_databasechangelog"
        tableName="databasechangelog" />
    </changeSet>

Primary key construction is up to developer choice.

Test Info Notes:

Verify that standard ium database(siu20) is successfully initialized during activation with external MySQL having Group Replication feature. Please also check that reactivation has no issues as well as there are some changeSets with runAlways="true" but without any preConditions or comments explaining why they should be performed each time when migratedb is invoked and whether it's safe or not to repeat them.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL6 x64
Java8u112
---------------
It was verified that PK is added to DATABASECHANGELOG table and thus eIUM instance could be
activated over MySQL group replication.

ID: QXCR1001541315

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Fan,Qing-Yang [qingyang.fan@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for resolving the following issues: 1) On the login page of the Operations Console there was a hidden field named gwt.codesvr, which could be used for JavaScript injection. JavaScript going out to the server would work in the victim's browser when the response was returned unfiltered from the server. As a result it could be used for malicious purposes; and 2) The web application did not enable XSS (Cross-site scripting) protection. XSS enables attackers to inject client-side scripts into web pages viewed by other users.

Resolution:

The unsafe field 'gwt.codesvr' was removed from the login page. The following header information has been added to all pages, in order to prevent XSS attacks automatically: X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block.

Submitter Text Notes:

Malicious JavaScript (or other scripting) going out to the attacker's server and unchecked will work in the victim's browser when the response is returned unfiltered from the server; - Session key play - Route victim to attacker's site - Interference with DOM-based objects It can be used for malicious purposes. Note of TurkTelekom : As written in the sent case details as below:

Request : nulls5649'%3e%3cscript%3ealert(1)%3c%2fscript%3emzkkjcqcoqy Response: <script>alert(1)</script>mzkkjcqcoqy'/>

â€œAny of security developer should understand the security gap arisen from XSS underlined by these expressions as above sentences. Due to that reason, they do not need to give any more details about this case anymore. Also, he mentioned that XSS has not been in use/not preferred by security developers nowadays globally.â€

ID: QXCR1001540540

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Fan,Qing-Yang [qingyang.fan@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

It was observed that auto-complete was not disabled in the password fields used on the web login pages. If enabling auto-complete for the user name and password, this information would stay recorded in the user's web browser. As a result, all users who shared the browser could log in to the system. Also, an attacker with access to the browser would be able to read the saved information (if the storage was not password protected). Due to this vulnerability, all automatic password completion should be disabled in web applications.

Resolution:

As a result of this fix, password auto-completion capability has been suppressed in web applications.

Submitter Text Notes:

Customer tested IUM Web GUI (ops console) with VOLTRON PENETRATION TEST and discovered password auto completion capability enabled: â€¢ /ops-ui/ â€¢ /ops-ui/console.jsp It is observed that autocomplete is not disabled in the password fields used on above pages. The following directives should be used to prevent these fields from being automatically completed (and thus stored in browsers). <autocomplete=off> In this case, the browser does not receive this directive, so it can use a feature such as storing the password itself.

Disable password auto completion for all IUM and RTP Web Apps in all supported browsers.

Test Info Notes:

Automatic password completion dialog shouldn't be shown when login. (please refer to the attached picture) This should be verified in all browsers supported by eIUM web console. (IE11, Chrome, Firefox)

Symptoms:

Configuration environment variables with '$' in the value may prevent some processes to start.

Resolution:

Configuration environment variables with '$' in the value are correctly applied.

Submitter Text Notes:

Related with case SD01825323. Mexico Telcel SSO outage 5 hours.

The issue probably happens in any recient version of eIUM and OS. Tested eIUM8.3 and RHEL6

When the configuration include $ in configuration the saveconfig "-expandvars" and process as RTPStudio fail to start.

Entry password with $ --> workaround use securepassword to encrypt the plain text password with $ character

Please, investigate fix changing password without "$"

SSOADMPASSWORD=Thil$Ol0

03/22/2017 09:19:34.748 CST main (WebAppBase) ERROR: Error parsing /var/opt/SIU_SSO/webappserver/webapps/reporting/WEB-INF/web.xml java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Illegal group reference at java.util.regex.Matcher.appendReplacement(Matcher.java:808) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariablesR(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariablesR(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariablesR(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariablesR(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariablesR(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariables(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigEnvironment.expandVariables(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.utils.ConfigManager.getConfigTree_(Unknown Source)

Best Regards, Miguel

Workaround - add backslash before the dollar sign: \$.

3. Make sure the variable ${b} has been expanded: [/a] a=ab$c
