ID: QXCR1001539429

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

for the default root CA certificate, the default issuer name is always "CA" and domain name "SecurityServer" which causes issue in Firefox and web applications do not work.

Resolution:

For the default root CA certificate, the default issuer name is "CA" and domain name is "SecurityServer" which can be changed from secserveractivate command using additional arguments : caissuer and cadomain The same can be done through the activator while activating security server.

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC5a RHEL 7x64 Java 8u112 ===================

During testing Iâ€™m installing lots of instances with security on same machine. Here is what Iâ€™ve received today when I tried to access web apps through FireFox:

Your certificate contains the same serial number as another certificate issued by the certificate authority. Please get a new certificate containing a unique serial number. Error code: SEC_ERROR_REUSED_ISSUER_AND_SERIAL

So it seems that I have certificate stored already in my browser which was issued by some other security server on same host from different instance. And now Iâ€™m unable to access web apps of some another instance due to certificates mismatch.

To access finally web-console it is required to cleanup FireFox from all previously stored certificates for this particular machine. To prevent such an issue further it is required not to store permanently certificate but approve it's usage each time.

IE doesn't have such an issue.

Test Info Notes:

To fix the reported issue, security server's issued certificate's Issuer name or domain name should be changed. This has been exposed for the user to change from secserveractivate command line with additional arguments : caissuer(Default : CA) cadomain(Default: SecurityServer) caadmin(Default: _security_administrator_)

The same can be done through the activator while activating security server. Only CA issuer and CA Domain are accessible from Activator.

Verifier:

==============

Since new params are not exposed to Activator there is no use of them.
CR is returned to dev.

ID: QXCR1001539100

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The JDBCLookupOperation FieldsExtracted attribute overwrote results from one thread to another with looking up simultaneously from multiple threads.

Resolution:

JDBCLookupOperation has been fixed to avoid this multi-threading issue.

Submitter Text Notes:

JDBCLookupOperation caches the FieldExtracted attribute array and uses it for all requests, irrespective of the thread it will be on. This leads to one thread overwriting the attribute value of the NME over another.

Main from Kyoko Tanzawa

The summary of this system is following. - The receiving of HTTP request with TextContextProvider. - To get the Session-ID from TimesTen DB by MSISDN of HTTP request. - To send the diameter request with Session ID.

The result: ãƒ»sequential scenario with each HTTP request works well. ãƒ»The issue happens when HTTP requests occurs at the same time. Our test case is two HTTP requests at the same time with broadcast. - Each MSISDN has different session-id of diameter in DB. - IUM get session-id and another information from DB. - IUM send message with session-id in diameter. The session-id NME data is changed the another value of another threadâ€™s data.

Note: ãƒ»The issue happen on IUM8.3 FP01. ãƒ»The issue happens on IUM8.3 Softbank RC5. ãƒ»The issue happens on DEUBG3 level. But it doesnâ€™t happen with DEBUG4 log level.

Test Info Notes:

Have a HttpConnector that receives Http request and executes a rulechain. The rulechain should lookup a DB using JDBCLookupOperation and log the result using LogNMERule. Sending HTTP request with key1 should lookup value1 from DB. Sending HTTP request with key2 should lookup value2 from DB. But when the HTTP requests are sent together, multiple threads will process them and do the lookup on JDBCLookupOperation. Without fix, the same value (either value1 or value2) will be looked up for both requests in their respective threads. With the fix, first thread should lookup value1 and second thread should lookup value2 (though they are executed simultaneously).

This was encountered by delivery team and I dont have the configuration for it.

Verifier: 

Test Plan:
==========
* Load the attached configuration file.
* Start the session server.
Note:
=====
* Session server has the Scheduler configured to send the burst request.
* Each request has the id identified by "ActivityCode" -- values are Client1, Client2, Client3
* DB is queried on the primarykey STARTIPRANGE which maps to "Apary"
* For request Client1 - Aparty is 15.30.244.10
  For request Client2 - Aparty is 15.30.244.12
  For request Client3 - Aparty is 15.30.244.13

ID: QXCR1001538671

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Qing,Hai [hai.qing@hpe.com]

Test Info Notes:

Added by Sukhwinder on 24-3-17: secldapcontrol arguments are changed from "partitionid" to "partitionid" and "partitionsuf"

The partition suffix and id specified under partitionsuf and partitionid must be unique for LDAP server. The argument partitionid is optional for the new partition to be created. If not specified it'll be extracted from partitionsuf. If the extracted partitionid is duplicate for LDAP server then a unique alpha-numeric id of length 4 will be generated and new partition will be created as long as the suffix is unique. A unique alpha-numeric id will only be used if the extracted id is duplicate. Otherwise only the user provided id will be used.

Please test all scenarios for combination of partitionid and partitionsuf

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC6
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
=================

It was verified that secldapcontrol is able to generate additional partitions in ApacheDS even
though they have common parts in suffix.

CaseID: LB_TPL_Algo_21_Frontend_Balance_2Bes4Front

Summary: Load Balancer should be able to support balancing for FrontEnd connector as well. The messages from backend server can be dispatched to front ends according to their groups' algorithm. In this case there are two backend servers and four front ends. The requests from bes1 should be sent to group1, and requests from bes2 should be sent to group2.

Case LB_TPL_Algo_21_Frontend_Balance_2Bes4Front Steps: 1. Config two backend servers, four front servers(two in group1, the other two in group2) and one LB server. 2. Config in rulechain, the requests from bes1 should be sent to group1, and requests from bes2 should be sent to group2. 3. Start all servers. 4. Two backend servers send requests every 5 second.

Expect Result: The requests from bes1 should be sent to group1, and requests from bes2 should be sent to group2.

Actual Result: The requests from bes1 can be sent to group1, but requests from bes2 cannot be sent to group2, there's no message returned from LB.

ID: QXCR1001537805

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Subramanian,Anand [anand.subramanian@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

When comparing 2 IPv6AddrAttributes, SrcIPv6 with value ::0000 and DstIPv6 with value ::FFFF, a ConditionalRule with condition SrcIPv6 < DstIPv6, executes the FalseRule even though :0000 is lesser than ::FFFF.

Resolution:

IPv6AddrAttribute has been fixed to do unsigned byte comparison of each byte.

Submitter Text Notes:

When comparing 2 IPv6AddrAttributes, SrcIPv6 with value ::0000 and DstIPv6 with value ::FFFF, a ConditionalRule with condition SrcIPv6 < DstIPv6, executes the FalseRule instead of the true rule.

ID: QXCR1001537627

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Strygin,Maxim [maxim.strygin@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

In previous versions of the CIS feature (previsouly referred to as VNFM), all VNFs after instantiation were in a STOPPED/IN_ACTIVE state. The latest ETSI specification indicates that all VNFs should be in a STARTED state after successful instantiation.

Resolution:

In the current version, the CIS server by default leaves VNFs in a STARTED/ACTIVE state after successful instantiation. In addition, it is configurable in the descriptor to enable the previous behavior.

Submitter Text Notes:

We need to follow ETSI specification. At the same time, we should make initial state for VNFs configurable: either STARTED or STOPPED.

According to ETSI specification: Once a VNF is instantiated, i.e. all instantiation steps have been completed, the VNF instance is in the state STARTED.

The whole chapter (http://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_gs/NFV-IFA/001_099/007/02.01.01_60/gs_NFV-IFA007v020101p.pdf):

7.2.11 Operate VNF operation 7.2.11.1 Description This operation enables requesting to change the state of a VNF instance, including starting and stopping the VNF instance. NOTE 1: These operations are complementary to instantiating and terminating a VNF. NOTE 2: In the present document, only starting and stopping the VNF instance(s) are supported. Extension of this operation to support other VNF state changes is left for future specification. A VNF instance can be in the following states: â€¢ STARTED: the VNF instance is up and running. â€¢ STOPPED: the VNF instance has been shut down. A VNF instance is stopped if all its VNFC instances are also stopped. In the state STOPPED, the virtualised container(s), where the VNFC instance(s) of the VNF run, are shut down but not terminated. In addition, if the workflow requires a graceful stop, as part of this process the VNFM (producer of the interface) will interact with VNF/EM to gracefully stop the VNF application. Once a VNF is instantiated, i.e. all instantiation steps have been completed, the VNF instance is in the state STARTED.

Test Info Notes:

â€¢ List of suggested new test cases 1) a. Without changes to the VNF descriptor, instantiate a VNF. b. Query VNF, it should be in STARTED state.

2) a. Add the following properties to the descriptor. <properties id="vnf"> <property id="markingVnfAsStoppedAfterInstantiation">true</property> </properties> b. Instantiate a VNF. Query VNF, it should be in STOPPED state.

â€¢ Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix a. Instantiate a VNF. b. Query VNF, it is in STOPPED state.

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC5a 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

Without adding this property in descriptor "<properties id="vnf">
        <property id="markingVnfAsStoppedAfterInstantiation">true</property>
    </properties>"
when we do instantiate operation then it is executed successfully then that VNF will be in 
Started State. If add above property in descriptor, then after successful instantiation then it 
will be in STOPPED state. We need to move the STARTED state by using operatevnf api.

ID: QXCR1001537597

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Stepien,Sylwester (Everett) [sstepien@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

Quite often it happens that virtual machines created for VNF purposed are deleted outside of Cloud Interconnect Server e.g. using Openstack dashboard or Docker directly. In such situations if someone tries to terminate such VNF in CIS, operation fails with complaint that VM no longer exists and terminate fails in general.

Resolution:

It should be possible to terminate VNF regardless of existence of VMs

Submitter Text Notes:

It is a common situation when VNF resources (VM) are terminated outside of the CIS (VNFM). Then, the database remains with records for GHOST VNF that is no longer backed up by resources. When one tries to terminate such VNF, this process would not succeed. We should terminate VNF no matter what should be done and leave DATABASE in consistent state.

Test Info Notes:

1. Create VNF using CIS UI 2. Delete VNF VMs using Helion Dashboard 3. Terminate VNF using CIS UI 4. Verity that VNF has been terminated properly.

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC6 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

After successful instantiation operation, If we need to delete the VM's from the dashboard and 
then delete that VM's and call the terminate operation from cirrus-UI. Then the terminate 
operation will execute successfully and in vnfm.log we will not found any errors. If VM is not 
there in Hellion environment then we will get only message in vnfm.log saying that "target server 
not found for: <vnfid>". It's not a error/warning message.

ID: QXCR1001537140

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Nair,Rajesh P [rajeshn@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

There is some inconsistency in JDS allow/deny in premium components. In license we have following set of JDS components in case of "Allow"

[/License/Premium] â€¦ Allow=com.hp.usage.jds.server.JobDistributionServer,10 Allow=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSFileSource,10 Allow=com.hp.usage.ipdr.sp.JDSIPDRSpNMESource,10 Allow=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSLeafSource,10 Allow=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSFileDelivery,10 Allow=com.hp.usage.bpmn2.workflow.jds.JDSAgentTask,10 â€¦

And following in case of "Deny"

[/License/Premium] â€¦ Deny=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSFileSource Deny=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSLeafSource Deny=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSFileDelivery Deny=com.hp.usage.jds.client.JDSFilePersistentStore Deny=com.hp.usage.ipdr.sp.JDSIPDRSpNMESource Deny=com.hp.usage.bpmn2.workflow.jds.JDSAgentTask â€¦

First of all I'm confused with different components listed in allow/deny cases. In Allow we have unique line JobDistributionServer and in Deny we have unique line JDSFilePersistentStore. Why is it so?

But main issue is following - we don't have "com.hp.siu.adminagent.procmgr.JobDistributionServerProcess" in Deny, so even setting 0 for "Job distribution service" section during license creation we're not denying him from launching JDS. Other JDS related components like producers/consumers will fail as expected in case of not listed in Allow, since their components are properly listed in Deny section (JDSFileDelivery/JDSFileSource).

Also this line "Allow=com.hp.usage.jds.server.JobDistributionServer,10" means nothing, since this class isn't used in IUM JDS configuration.

Test Info Notes:

- Run JDS server after applying a license without JDSService premium component selected. E.g. license_nojds.config attached. It will have com.hp.usage.jds.service.JDSStoreService in the deny list. This should make the server shutdown with "no premium license" config exception.

- Replace the license with one that has JDSService premium component. E.g. license.config attached.It will have com.hp.usage.jds.service.JDSStoreService in the allow list. This should make the server start correctly.

ID: QXCR1001537084

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Li,Zhiwei [zli@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

AsynchNMEStore was registered as an IUM service. when user stopping IUM session server. the session server would stop IUM services which were registered on this server one by one. since AsynchNMEStore as an IUM service would block the stop the procedure for specified time figured by drainTimeout. And our IUM session server's longest stop time is 60 seconds. if there is several AsynchNMEStores they would block the stop procedure and cause session server print "Server stop takes too long. Forcing exit."

Test Info Notes:

please test in RC6 installtion. this should be fixed.

In case of Database validation or Security policy validation, activation fails without any possibility to reenter invalid values. Test Info Notes:

Please test group validation in Activator in console mode. In case validation fails, there is 2 retry and values input returns to the beginning of the page (To determine beginning of the page, you can refer to activator GUI mode).

1. Database validation for ex. JDS with custom database example DB properties: Driver jar: /SIU/lib/mysqlDriver.jar Driver class: com.mysql.jdbc.Driver Database URI: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/jds User: siu20 Password: siu20

Test cases: 1. Enter invalid values 3 times: activation should be aborted 2. Enter invalid values, request validation (as validation for DB is optional) and input valid values. Activation should continue/

2. JVM security policy validation Install US_export_policy.jar, local_policy.jar with limited security to your jvm. Start activation in console mode and enable security. You will get a message like: GeneralSecurityException while testing encryption strength with password of length 10 : {}exception decrypting data - java.security.InvalidKeyExceptio n: Illegal key size

Skip Security Server activation to continue!

Security activation will fail because JVM is not updated with unlimited JCE jurisdiction policy Do you want to continue? (yes/no)?

Use cases: * Continue activation and activate SecurityServer Ex.r: activation aborted after 2 retries * Select to not continue activation Ex.r.: activation aborted * Select to continue activation and disable Security Server Ex.r.: activation switches to next parameter/screen

3. Security login validation Activate IUM with enabled security. Try to reactivate IUM. Enter invalid login/pwd

Engineer: Pavlenko,Andrey [andrey.pavlenko@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC4 RHEL 7x 64 Java 8u112 ===============

I've created deployment with 2 hosts in HA mode: bsasg and bsasl

Then I've opened 1 launchpad on bsasg machine and 1 on bsasl machine. Later in this note I'll use "_G" and "_L" to separate them in descriptions. I've checked that configuration is in sync. Next I've created from launchpad_G collector on host_L and from launchpad_L collector on host_G. Each collector is visible only in launchpad where I've created it. After start situation doesn't change.

Only after restart of both hosts through services deployment becomes sync. But any new created processes follow same pattern.

*********Update********* Andrey Pavlenko suggested to check topology on both config servers and see if they both contain newly added processes. So finally it was found that problem is in topology "http://IP:8158/topology/*". Process added from launchpad_G to CS_L is visible only in topology of CS_G. And vice versa process add from launchpad_L to CS_G is visible only in topology of CS_L.

ID: QXCR1001536032

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

secactivate user, secactivate host do not work with when ldaps is used and trustore information is provided.

Resolution:

secactivate user, secactivate now works with ldaps when trustore information is provided.

Submitter Text Notes:

Look at the changes done for QXCR1001534810 considering only the changes done for : modified: core/security/server/src/com/hp/usage/security/server/ldap/LdapService.java

Test Info Notes:

Existing secactivate user and secactivate host commands do not work when the security server is initialized with ldaps (you specify the truststore information in external-login.config file).

New commands secldapcontrol add/remove/list have been fixed to work with ldaps connection. The trustore information can be passed with new arguments: "ts", "tspwd", "tstype", "tsprovider"

------------------------------------- How to create a keystore for testing: ------------------------------------- > You can either use keytool comamnd to create a keystore file OR > you can create a self signed certificate using below command: secactivate serverkey -name <KAURSUK1> -store keystore.p12 -storepass <pass> -storetype PKCS12 secactivate serverkey -name <KAURSUK1> -store keystore.ks -storepass <pass> -storetype JKS

You can use this at your LDAP server to allow only ldaps. And the client will use it for authentication.

----------- Test cases: ----------- > Create a keystore file either with keytool command or secactivate serverkey (this will work on an instance where security is already activated). ID: QXCR1001534810

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

secactivate user, secactivate host, secldapcontrol add, secldapcontrol remove and secldapcontrol list do not work with when ldaps is used and trustore information is provided.

Resolution:

secactivate and secldapcontrol have been fixed to work with ldaps.

Test Info Notes:

Existing secactivate user and secactivate host commands do not work when the security server is initialized with ldaps (you specify the truststore information in external-login.config file).

New commands secldapcontrol add/remove/list have been fixed to work with ldaps connection. The trustore information can be passed with new arguments: "ts", "tspwd", "tstype", "tsprovider"

------------------------------------- How to create a keystore for testing: ------------------------------------- > You can either use keytool comamnd to create a keystore file OR > you can create a self signed certificate using below command: secactivate serverkey -name <KAURSUK1> -store keystore.p12 -storepass <pass> -storetype PKCS12 secactivate serverkey -name <KAURSUK1> -store keystore.ks -storepass <pass> -storetype JKS

You can use this at your LDAP server to allow only ldaps. And the client will use it for authentication.

----------- Test cases: ----------- > Create a keystore file either with keytool command or secactivate serverkey (this will work on an instance where security is already activated). Once this is created, you can use the same file for testing for your any further testing for any instance. > Install ApacheDS (or other LDAP) and enable only LDAPS and disable LDAP. provide keystore inforamtion for SSL authentication. > Install and activate eIUM and make sure the activation goes fine with ldaps external ldap server with keystore information provided. > make sure secactivate user/add and secldapcontrol add/remove/list works fine with security server activated with ldaps ldap server.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC6
RHEL6 x64
Java 8u112
==================

It was verified that proper fix is there in RC6 build.
LDAPS works for communication between security server and ApacheDS.

Engineer: Golubev,Alexander [alexander.golubev@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

There is a new version 2 of VNF descriptor format is introduced with eIUM90 release and some capability is needed to migrate VNF descriptors from version 1 to version 2.

Resolution:

New migratevnfd command is provided as a part of vnfmtools CLI application. This command takes specified VNF descriptor of version 1 as input and produces new VNF descriptor of version 2.

Submitter Text Notes:

Please find a list of targets that we need to process during descriptor migration from v1->v2.

Moving standard operations into custom targets: <reset description="reset"> -> <target name="reset" description="reset">

<upgrade description="upgrade"> -> <target name="upgrade" description="upgrade">

<updaterollback description="updaterollback"> -> <target name="updaterollback" description="updaterollback">

<upgraderollback description="upgraderollback"> -> <target name="upgraderollback" description="upgraderollback">

Adding level attribute: <update description="update"> -> <update description="update" level="1">

Test Info Notes:

Verify that VNF v1 descriptor converted into v2 format by migratevnfd command from vnfmtools can be uploaded to CIS(VNFM) and used for instantiating and administrating new VNF instances.

Engineer: Kapil,Kumar [kkapil@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

IUM Version : 90 Tissot , 83fp02 with jdk8

This issue is a regression failure and seen only in jdk8.In 83fp02 with jdk8 also we have seen this issue. The failed TET is /tc/collector/encapsulator/FSTFileEncapsulator/XMLSNMEWriterFactory_02

The configuration's used here are you have a LeafCollector sending it to another SessionCollector.The SessionCollector has DatasetMuxEncapsulator ( 2 DatasetCollectorEncapsulator)

RESULT: ( The configs/log and input files are attached)

With jdk 7: ( Correct Behaviour ) ------------

We see flush occuring 4 times

1st Flush - 1 NME flush : TerminatingUSSDCDR 2nd Flush - 3 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR 3rd flush - 3 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR 4th flush - 4 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR

With jdk 8: ( Incorrect Behaviour ) ------------

We see flush occuring 4 times

1st Flush - 1 NME flush : TerminatingUSSDCDR 2nd Flush - 3 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR 3rd flush - 3 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR 4th flush - 4 NME flush : OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR,OriginatingUSSDCDR,TerminatingUSSDCDR

  You can see in the 3rd flush,the ordering of the NME records have been changed

//Kapil ====================== The TET should be corrected, since the shared configuration use HashMatchRule in aggregation scheme which do not preserve insertion order. The HashMatchRule documentaiton has been modified . So please verify the documentation.

Verifier: 

IUM Version : 90 Tissot (RC5a)
Test status : PASS

The o/p file (XMLSNMEWriter_XML_03.exp) for the TET
/tc/collector/encapsulator/FSTFileEncapsulator/XMLSNMEWriterFactory_02 was changed and checked-in
90(Tissot) branch.

In the component reference, documentation has been added for HashMatchRule as.
"This component makes no guarantees as to the order of the map; in particular, it does not guarantee
that the order will remain constant over time"

ID: QXCR1001533510

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Apiecionek,Arkadiusz (Everett) [apiecionek@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

When working with the Instances panel, if a lifecycle operation is triggered on a VNF Instance and then finishes without user changing the panel / reloading page, the VNF Instance item that was affected by the lifecycle operation will not be updated unless the VNF Instance state has changed (e.g. 'operate VNF' operation has finished and state changed from 'Stopped' to 'Started').

Resolution:

When working with the Instances panel, if a lifecycle operation is triggered on a VNF Instance and then finishes without user changing the panel / reloading page, the VNF Instance item that was affected by the lifecycle operation will be updated even if the VNF Instance state has not changed.

Test Info Notes:

Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix: 1. Create and instantiate a new VNF from a descriptor that supports scale-out / scale-in on at least one aspect. 2. Scale out the VNF by 1 step 3. Wait for the scale out operation to finish WITHOUT reloading the page or switching to panel different than 'Instances' (look at the number of 'Processing' operations in the upper-right corner) 4. Launch the 'Scale' wizard and pick 'Scale In', then the aspect on which Scale out was previously executed. 5. There will be a warning displayed that 'Scale In' is not possible on that aspect.

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC4 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

After doing successful instantiation operation and now we want to do scale-out operation, execute 
the scale-out operation successfully & don't refresh the page or don't move to other pages(like 
descriptors,Journals & operations), now see the scale-out operation is executed after that launch 
the scale wizard and try to execute the scale-in operation then pass the valid values and execute 
the scale-in operation, it will execute without any errors.

ID: QXCR1001532859

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Simoes,Kelly E [kelly.simoes@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

xsd2config/wsdl2config looked at only the schema level elementFormDefault to generate prefixes for XML tags. They ignored the element level Form attribute in the XSD/WSDL.

Resolution:

Fixed xsd2config to look at the element form in the XSD, before taking the schema elementFormDefault, while generating the XML.

Submitter Text Notes:

The file stateless.xtc.datatypes.xsd (in wsdl.zip attached) defines elementFormDefault=â€qualifiedâ€ but all the inner elements have form=â€unqualifiedâ€. IUM wrongly looks at the first one alone and generates prefix for all such elements.

The sample request generated by soapui looks like in wsdl.zip/SOAPUI_request/request.xml while the request generated by IUM looks like in wsdl.zip/eIUM_request/soap_request.xml.

Test Info Notes:

Setup SoapHttpRequest with attached wsdl (wsdl.zip) and generate a SOAP message. Without the fix, the SOAP request will have prefixes for RequestContext, Subscriber XML tags in the generated request. But a sample message generated by SOAPUI will not have prefixes for those. With the fix, SoapHttpRequest should also not have prefixes for those tags.

Verifier: 

Test Plan:
==========
* Load the attached configuration files.
* Start the session server
* send the below siuinvoke request.
siuinvoke -n barring_check -rulechain barring_check -data bc_rtc_user "abc" bc_rtc_pass "xyz"

Case 1:
=======
To verify the behavior when the elementFormDefault in the schema is set to "qualified" and in the 
elements set to "unqualified"

Case 2:
=======
To verify the behavior when the elementFormDefault in the schema is set to "qualified" and in the 
elements set to "qualified"

Case 3:
=======
To verify the behavior when the elementFormDefault in the schema is set to "unqualified" and in 
the elements set to "qualified"

Case 4:
=======
To verify the behavior when the elementFormDefault in the schema is set to "unqualified" and in 
the elements set to "unqualified"

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><env:Envelope

RIZE_SHORTCODE

ameter><ns1:RequestContext

RIZE_SHORTCODE 
xmlns:ns0="http://payperevent.rbp.tmobile.net/services/XAction/Stateless/v80/"><ns0:data><ns0:inPar
ameter><RequestContext><Authorisation><User>rtc</User><Password>rtc</Password></Authorisation></Req
uestContext><Subscriber><PrimaryIdentifier><Name>MSISDN</Name></PrimaryIdentifier></Subscriber></ns
0:inParameter></ns0:data></ns0:AUTHORIZE_SHORTCODE></env:Body></env:Envelope>

==================
The request would have qualifiers for the elements as the element has the form as "qualified" 
which takes the priority over the schema.

Even in previous version of 83Telcel-20161229 there was no such an issue. In latest build issue is caused by fix for this:

So, in normal life no problems are visible to user. And for 83Telcel build it is not an easy task to restore this table, since there is no migratedb functionality available.

ID: QXCR1001532067

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Stepien,Sylwester (Everett) [sstepien@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

The issue manifest itself to the Customer in situation when VNF instantiation fails, for example error in configure script of the descriptor. In such cases VNF is in inconsistent state, it is impossible to delete VNF Identifier from Cirrus UI as vnfr and children records have been created for failed VNF.

Resolution:

In situation when VNF instantiation fails it should be possible to delete VNF Identifier as there should be no active VNFR record for failed VNF.

Submitter Text Notes:

Vnf Record is created even when VNF instantiation fails. Therefore, Cirrus DB remains in the inconsistent state. That VNFR becomes a ghost DB record. No ways to delete it.

VNFR should be created only after successful VNF creation together with VNFInfo record.

Penumathsa, Chaitanya Varma Date:02/10/2017

VNFInstance ID is deleted but in the Cirrus-UI/vnfm database able to see the VNFInstanceId which needs to be erased when deleted operation performed successfully. We will see this issue when any Instantiate/Scale operations related to VNFInstanceId are failed.

Test Info Notes:

The goal: achieve VNF instantiation failure.

1. Modify descriptor to fail on script execution (e.g. use non existing tag in configure target of EMS vdu) 2. Upload descriptor to VNFM 3. Create a new ID using that descriptor 4. Try to instantiate new ID 5. Observe vnfm.log to see that instantion fails on configure script execution 6. Try to delete new ID identifier BEFORE FIX: - new ID is not deleted, after refresh of Instances page new ID comes up again AFTER FIX: - new ID is deleted from database properly

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC4 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

Before Fix
----------
Any VNFInstance Id is unable to delete from the VNFM DB when that VNFId instantiate was failed.

After Fix
--------

We can delete the VNFID which is not required means when we called the instantiate operation with 
valid VNFId but when instantiate operation is failed then we can delete that unnecessary VNFId. 
And also with this fix, in vnfm database there is no traces of delete vnfid.

Symptoms:

No symptoms for the end user.

Resolution:

This functionality has no visible effect for the end user. It is about internal VNFM cleanup for situations when users do not unsubscribe from subscriptions but simply close CLI window.

Submitter Text Notes:

All kind of subscriptions (alarms, KPIs, notifications) are kept by Cirrus server even when they are no longer used. There should be a mechanism to clean them up, and potentially to restore when needed.

Test Info Notes:

1. Open a few CLI windows 2. Subscribe to lifecycle notifications 3. call via postman or GUI create VNF id operations 4. notification should come up on each subscribed window 5. close one of the CLI window 6. open VNFM log and observe 7. call via postman or GUI create VNF id operations 8. notification should come up on each subscribed window 9. in vnfm.log there should be entry for closed window: "unsubscribing subscription: " + subscriptionId

Release     : eIUM90

After successfully updated XML(descriptor) in VNFM Database. Now open more that one vnfmclitools 
window and call the Life cycle operations with subscription in both windows at a time, and now 
create a VNFId through the Cirrus-UI or PostMan client, Now if we see the vnfmclitools windows 
both you will get a VNFInstanceId created. Now, close one of the cli window & Again open a new 
cli window & call life cycle subscription operation. And again create a VNFId through Cirrus-UI 
or PostMan client. Now if we see vnfm.log you can get a error saying that "broken pipe" & also a

ID: QXCR1001531994

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Apiecionek,Arkadiusz (Everett) [apiecionek@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

When VNF Instance ID is reused (an existing instance has been terminated and new instance has been instantiated) there's no Cirrus Server notification going out to subscription listeners. To circumvent that, Cirrus UI has a hardcoded logic to clear operation history for a given Instance ID when that instance is terminated (which is an incorrect logic).

Resolution:

When VNF Instance ID is reused (an existing instance has been terminated and new instance has been instantiated) Cirrus Server sends a notification to subscription listeners. Cirrus UI reacts to such notification by clearing operation history for a given Instance ID (which is reflected in the State Panel and Operation List panel).

Test Info Notes:

Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix: - create a new VNF Instance ID and instantiate it - start the VNF Instance - stop the VNF Instance - terminate the VNF Instance

When 'terminate' operation is finished, the State Panel will clear the operation history (the total number of operations will decrease). This should happen only after successful instantiation.

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC5a 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

After successful instantiation operation, we will select the terminate operation and then after 
successful terminate operation then vnfid will moved to the NOT-INSTANTIATED state and now if we 
delete the vnfid then number of operations will decrease. There will be no traces of deleted 
vnfid.

ID: QXCR1001531811

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Apiecionek,Arkadiusz (Everett) [apiecionek@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

When launching Scale Wizard on a VNF Instance that has been already scaled out on at least one aspect (scaling level on that aspect is > 0) it's impossible to execute 'Scale In' on that aspect: when user pick 'Scale In' as type and then picks the scaling aspect, a warning is displayed and user cannot proceed further.

Resolution:

When launching Scale Wizard on a VNF Instance that has been already scaled out on at least one aspect (scaling level on that aspect is > 0) user can execute 'Scale In' on that aspect: when user picks 'Scale In' as type and then picks the scaling aspect, a 'Number of steps' picker is displayed, allowing user to specify number of steps for scale in and then proceed to next step of the Wizard.

Test Info Notes:

Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix: - instantiate a VNF Instance from a descriptor that provides some scaling aspects for that flavor - execute 'Scale Out' operation on that instance - open the Scale Wizard, select 'Scale In' and then pick the scaling aspect on which 'Scale Out' has been previously executed

Verifier: 

Verified by : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
Release     : eIUM90
Verified in : RC4 
Branch      : next-tissot
TET Status  : Need to automate/automated

After doing the scale-out operation is executed successful then if we want to do perform the 
scale-in operation through the Cirrus-UI then we need to select the Scaling type is scale-in & 
specify the scaling aspect now specify the level. For example, If we do 2 times scale-out 
operation then in drop down you will get 1 & 2. Please select the 2. After selecting the level 
click next and specify VM name which we need to scale-in and click finish. Then scale-in 
operation will be executed successfully

ID: QXCR1001531077

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Patrushev,Maxim [maxim.patrushev@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The DES (Data Encryption Standard) encryption algorithm usage was considered not fully secure, since it is vulnerable to differential cryptanalysis (DC), linear cryptanalysis (LC), and Davies' kind of attacks. The DES (Data Encryption Standard) algorithm has been utilized by eIUM to encrypt user passwords in the eIUM configuration.

Resolution:

eIUM has switched to using the AES/ECB/PKCS5Padding cipher suite, and the RSA-encoded key has been replaced with a much stronger SHA-256-encoded key.

Submitter Text Notes:

Disable unsecure DES encryption with AES encryption. DES encryption and legacy hardcoded keys shall be used only to decrypt existing configurations and files.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC5a
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
===================
It was verified that DES encryption was removed from eIUM passwords.

ID: QXCR1001530606

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

eIUM configuration and silent-mode installation response files could contain clear-text passwords.

Resolution:

The eIUM activation parameters file ($SIUHOME/activateIUM.ini) is now always written with values of password parameters encrypted. The silent responses files for activation could be encrypted on the user's request by executing:

./activate encryptrespfile -i <cleartext_file> -o <encrypted_file> [-p <password>]

(-i and -o could point to the same file for in-place encryption.)

If the password is provided, it must be then also provided for the silent activation:

./activate silent -f <encrypted_file> -respFilePassword <password>

Installation has no password parameters, so it is not provided with dedicated encryption commands. However, the "activate" command could be used to encrypt all the parameters in the target file, including the installation ones:

./activate encryptrespfile -i <cleartext_file> -o <encrypted_file> -alsoEncrypt "*"

For more information, see the eIUM Command Reference.

Submitter Text Notes:

Make sure all input or control files used by the installation and activation contain no open text passwords. All the passwords shall be encrypted (with an advanced AES algorithm) and the user shall be prompted to provide a password to decrypt those during installation or activation.

Test Info Notes:

The easiest way to test this functionality is to perform an installation with "-w <file>" option and choose to activate as part of installation. During activation, select and external database and provide user/password parameters.

Please ensure that:

- password parameters saved to activateIUM.ini are encrypted - migratedb command when using activateIUM.ini is able to properly read the encrypted parameters (e.g. "migratedb configure -useConfig no -- list" works as expected) - the response file generated by installing with "-w <file>" option has password parameters encrypted - calling activate encryptrespfile -i <file> -o <file> -alsoEncrypt PARAM1,PARAM2 will encrypt PARAM1 and PARAM2 even if those are not passwords (choose random parameters from file as PARAM1 and PARAM2) - calling activate encryptrespfile -i <file> -o <file> -alsoEncrypt "*" will encrypt all parameters in <file> - it is possible to use encrypted <file> as input for "installer -i silent -f <file>" or "activate silent -f <file>"

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
==============

It was verifeid that all password in all config/ini/silent files are encrypted.
It was verified that activator is able to work with encrypted passwords.

When configuring/checking HA manually it is very important to follow following steps:

1. Turn Off WebApp and MS1. Close Web-Console!
2. Configure active HA for MS1 and set STARTUPMODE=Manual.
3. Create MS2 with stand-by HA and set STARTUPMODE=Manual.
3a. Only for sec mode and if embedded LDAP is used: $_SIUHOME/bin/secactivate $cmdSecOption host
-add -identities "management:ManagementServer1"
4. Start WebApp and MS, MS2.
5. Open Web-Cobsole-> Deployment. Only active MS1(not MS2) is displayed.
6. Stop MS1 and wait for opened Web-Console. It should switch to MS2. Deployment should show MS2 now.

ID: QXCR1001530096

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

CCFFileEncapsulator got stuck during process cleanup, when errors occurred while executing the aggregator rule chain.

Resolution:

CCFFileEncapsulator has been fixed to move to the next file for this scenario.

Submitter Text Notes:

Hello L3 team we have a collector which process asn file records using CCFFileEncapsulator. It have some errors inside. Collector configured for error parking, but was stuck after some file. So we tried to find the root problem with help of DEBUG4 trace. And found different behavior for INFO and DEBUG mode. In INFO it can process some files (from one to several) ??? finding errors, stop processing and move files into error folder, but then suddenly stuck. Always on the messages:

01/17/2017 05:11:14.956 EST main (08.036.04) WARNING: Exception encountered: Can not copy attribute elementRecords.rcsRecord.fileTransferModeIndicator to CDF_OUTAGE_FileTransferModeIndicator_Binary 01/17/2017 05:11:14.957 EST main (08.036.05) WARNING: Encapsulator.invokeRuleChain(): Cleaning up

When used DEBUG4 mode ??? all files every time are to be processed without any hanging or problems or stucks. In Outage.zip you can find full config, CCF important files and examples with INFO and DEBUG where in INFO 3 files processed and stuck.

01/23/2017 05:09:52.259 EST main (08.036.04) WARNING: Exception encountered: Can not copy attribute elementRecords.rcsRecord.fileTransferModeIndicator to CDF_OUTAGE_FileTransferModeIndicator_Binary 01/23/2017 05:09:52.259 EST main (08.036.05) WARNING: Encapsulator.invokeRuleChain(): Cleaning up

In Jan232017.zip you can find another experiment where we get thread dump for the stuck collector. Also there DEBUG4 another example, where all files are processed (marked as problem and moved to error folder)

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup: 1) Please find the attached resources.zip in the CR. 2) Import the config file to setup a CCFFileEncapsulator. 3) Get the CCF files and upload it to the repository server in order to have the SNME schema loaded. 4) Extract the Input files to a certain location and point that location in the configuration under FileRollPolicy.

5) Additionally, please create a directory for putting files when error occurs. In the config it is called ParseError directory.

Test Issue: Currently, the CCFFileEncapsulator gets stuck in the cleanup process when error occurs while trying to execute the Aggregator rule chain. This happens after processing some files. Like for example if the input directory has 8 files, then such the CCFFileEncapsulator gets stuck after processing 2nd or 3rd file. In the log it is visible that it gets stuck in the cleanup process and roll over to the next file doesn't happen. Therefore, processing of all the files never happen.

Here the attached input files are all fine and their decoding is successful. But to simulate the issue, in the aggregator rule chain, the config is using NMEConversionRule which is trying to copy a String value to a Binary attribute. This is intentionally creating an error for which the input should be error parked or put into the ParseError directory.

Test Case 1: (Before the fix)

When the Encapsulator is run with without patch, we can see some of the input files will be put in the ParseError directory and rest of the input files are not processed at all. The log will show the last line as CleanUp process and there is no movement forward. The encapsulator gets stuck right then.

After the fix: Since we are intentionally creating the error in the rule chain, therefore, all the input files will be put in the ParseError directory. The encapsulator will not get stuck and all the files will be processed.

Please note that here the intentional error creation in the rule chain is not an issue. It is the same in customer case also, which they have fixed on their own. The main issue is the encapsulator doesn't process any file after processing one or two error files.

Submitter Text Notes:

-------------------------------------- Verified by : Vikram Pai Malpe Release : TISSOT(eIUM 9.0) SIU version : B.09.00 2017/01/16 (RC2) TET Status : Need to be automated --------------------------------------

Defect Description: -------------------

Netty Server statistics are not disabled eventhough config items i.e 'Manageable' and 'CollectStatistics' present in HttpProtocol component located under TCPConnector is set to 'false',statistic items such as 'TotalRequestsReceived' and 'TotalResponsesSent' are still getting updated as shown in snapshot

Config,log,Jconsole and webconsole snapshots are attached with tarred filename 'QXCR1001529964_IUM9.0.zip' along with this CR.

Doc snippet: ------------

CollectStatistics Optional Single-valued

Starts collecting server-side statistics about this component, which will be available through JMX (Java Management Extensions). This configuration attribute will be used only when the Servers configuration attribute is specified.

Since: eIUM 8.3

Syntax: <Value>

Datatype Boolean

Default Value False

Range:

Value Description

True Collect server side statistics.

False Do not collect server side statistics.

Manageable Optional Single-valued

Specifies whether to enable statistics or not.

Since: eIUM 8.3 Feature Pack 1

Syntax: <Value>

Datatype Boolean Default Value true

Test Step: ---------

ID: QXCR1001529655

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kopylov,Sergey [sergey.kopylov@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Attributes with names "class"/"Class" and "type"/"Type" conflict with java.lang.Object#getClass() and com.hp.usage.nme.NME#getType() interfaces. This has been discovered due to some performance related changed made to POJO- NME framework. When POJO-NME (and POJO) comes across such attributes the getters and setters generated will be escaped by an underscore "_" character on the POJO interface with no visible impact on the NME interface. Hence, the regular NME interfaces will continue working correctly nme.getInt(factory.getAttributeRef(nmeType, "type")) or nme.getLong(factory.getAttributeRef(nmeType, "class")). While the POJO interface will have the following methods: get_type/set_type for "type" get_Type/set_Type for "Type" get_class/set_class for "class" get_Class/set_Class for "Class".

The fixes have to be applied to the Transformation and to the Codec layers of CCF in order to handle such situation correctly.

Currently, we will receive the following error: Reserved word used as an attribute name [Type] for type com.hp.usage.datastruct.beans.nlstlv.TLVHeader Replacing getter [getType] with [get_Type] for type com.hp.usage.datastruct.beans.nlstlv.TLVHeader Replacing setter [setType] with [set_Type] for type com.hp.usage.datastruct.beans.nlstlv.TLVHeader

java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: com.hp.usage.datastruct.beans.xfd.nlstlv.TLVHeader#get_Type not found

when we configure the XFD like the following:

<type id="TLVHeader"> <codec> <raw /> </codec> <sequence> <field id="Type" type="int" codec="Int14" /> <field id="Length" type="int" codec="UInt16" /> </sequence> </type>

Test Info Notes:

1. Check that field names "type" and "class" is working in CCF codecs.

2. Check that field names "type" and "class" is working in scripting rule. 2.1 Read updated scripting rule component reference 2.2 Create test case with SNME which contains attributes Class and Type 2.3 Make sure you can reference these attributes in script code as described in component reference

Verifier:

Verified by : Pavlov Peter

=====================================================

repositorymanager.

ALSO, IUM SDK and all scripting Studio validation must be verified: "class" is deprecated 
attribute/variable name.

ID: QXCR1001529508

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Baikerikar,Vivekananda [vivekananda.baikerikar@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Collector clean-up generated an SQLException with the Oracle Database 12c Enterprise Edition Release 12.1.0.2.0.

Resolution:

The issue has been fixed by setting auto-commit to false for clean-up operations.

Submitter Text Notes:

Hi R&D team,

The customer is getting the following error while cleaning up a collector:

01/17/2017 10:47:33.518 COT main (siucleanup) ERROR: Error: com.hp.siu.utils.ClientException: [Failed - java.sql.SQLException: Could not commit with auto-commit set on] at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.failed(siucleanup.java:598) at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.dropTableOrView(siucleanup.java:586) at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.clearDatabase(siucleanup.java:552) at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.removeData(siucleanup.java:324) at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.cleanup(siucleanup.java:788) at com.hp.siu.tools.siucleanup.main(siucleanup.java:631) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method) at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke (NativeMethodAccessorImpl.java:62) at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke (DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43) at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:498) at com.hp.usage.console.commands.MainRunner.execute(MainRunner.java:59) at com.hp.usage.console.handlers.LegacyMainRunner.execute(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.console.framework.CommandContextImpl.executeInternal (CommandContextImpl.java:259) at com.hp.usage.console.framework.ApplicationContextImpl.executeBatch (ApplicationContextImpl.java:390) at com.hp.usage.console.framework.ApplicationContextImpl.executeInternal (ApplicationContextImpl.java:292) at com.hp.usage.console.framework.ApplicationContextImpl.executeInteractive (ApplicationContextImpl.java:206) at com.hp.usage.console.spring.Main.executeInteractive(Main.java:96) at com.hp.siu.loader.Command.executeCLI(Command.java:158) at com.hp.siu.loader.Command.execute(Command.java:104) at com.hp.siu.loader.CommandLaunch.run(CommandLaunch.java:57) at com.hp.siu.loader.CommandLaunch.run(CommandLaunch.java:95) at com.hp.siu.loader.CommandLaunch.main(CommandLaunch.java:101)

They are using eIUM8.3-FP01 and Oracle as external DB. The full version of Oracle is: Oracle Database 12c Enterprise Edition Release 12.1.0.2.0 - 64bit Production.

While investigation about that message, I found out it can be solved by turn off the following JVM option. However, as we can see they had already deployed it:

[/deployment/probigidcl002-vip/TBDA_FIXED_NET1/Properties]

JVMOPTS=%DEFAULTS% JVMOPTS=-Doracle.jdbc.autoCommitSpecCompliant=false PROCESSARGS=-l 4 STARTUPMODE=Manual

By the way if they turn on to true that JVM option, then the collector is not able to start.

I'm attaching the relevant information to this case: configuration, log file, <HostName> log file and siucleanup log file along with their full deployment configuration. Kindly let me know if any additional information/data is needed to understand the issue. Thanks.

     Best Regards,
          Hector

Test Info Notes:

Please test it with Oracle Database 12c Enterprise Edition Release 12.1.0.2.0 - 64bit Production.

Please test this wit all the Datastores: MuxDatastore, FileJDBCDataStore, IDRJDBCDatastore The cleanup should work even without the jvm option.

Test Plan
=========
* Create a demo collector from the template and modify the "Database" and
"DatabaseClass" to point to any oracle 12c server and oracle driver
respectively.
* The datastore used should consist a MuxDatastore.
* Add "ojdbc7.jar" in the CLASSPATH of "Host Default Properties"
Case 1
* Configure "JVMOPTS=-Doracle.jdbc.autoCommitSpecCompliant=false" under /Properties" node 
under the collector as
[/Demo_Coll/Properties]
JVMOPTS=%DEFAULTS%
JVMOPTS=-Doracle.jdbc.autoCommitSpecCompliant=false
PROCESSARGS=-l 4
STARTUPMODE=Manual

* Start the collector
--> Check whether the collector starts
* Stop the collector
* Cleanup the collector
--> Check whether the collector gets cleaned up

Case 2
* Configure "-Doracle.jdbc.autoCommitSpecCompliant=false" in the "Host Default Properties" 
under "JVMOPTS"
[ i.e Under Launchpad--> <HostID>--> Host Default Properties--> JVMOPTS-->]
* Start the collector
--> Check whether the collector starts
* Stop the collector
* Cleanup the collector
--> Check whether the collector gets cleaned up

Case 3
* Do not configure "-Doracle.jdbc.autoCommitSpecCompliant=false" anywhere
* Start the collector
--> Check whether the collector starts
* Stop the collector
* Cleanup the collector
--> Check whether the collector gets cleaned up

With the fix:
==============
Case1,case2: 
There should not be any difference
Case3:
The collector start should be successful, and should flush records.
The cleanup should be successful and should not thrown any exception.
(Ref# siucleanup.log)

Without the fix:

ID: QXCR1001528439

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Strygin,Maxim [maxim.strygin@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

SNMEType attribute present in CeilometerConnector is mandatory only in case RequestAttribute or TargetURLAttribute are present. Check for attribute was too strict and was raising exception when it is not present irrespective to other attributes.

Resolution:

SNMEType attribute present in CeilometerConnector is mandatory only in case RequestAttribute or TargetURLAttribute are present. Check for attribute was refactored to raise exception when it is null, but one of the dependent attributes is present.

Submitter Text Notes:

-------------------------------------- Verified by : Vikram Pai Malpe Release : TISSOT(eIUM 9.0) SIU version : B.09.00 2017/01/16 (RC2) TET Status : Need to be automated --------------------------------------

Syntax: <SNMEType> Datatype String

ID: QXCR1001527975

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Tsoukanov,Victor [victor.tsoukanov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

A tight loop occurred in the Management Server under certain conditions.

Resolution:

No more tight loops occur in Management Server alarm processing.

Submitter Text Notes:

A tight loop in ManagementServer under certain conditions , that blocks alarm processing threads that leave those threads waiting for locks and eventually leading to unbounded thread growth. This would eventually kill MS process with OOM error , cannot create native threads on reaching resource limit. Under normal conditions this it probably take weeks to reach this state and a restart would happen. We were able to accelerate it under lab conditions until the crash of MS and then validate a fix that mitigate this condition.

Test Info Notes:

One of possible test case to reproduce it, to send alarms with high rate and execute alarm database cleaner more frequently. For this purpose you need to 1. Using CLI send alarms FOR /L %%A IN (1,1,999999999999999999999) DO ( processmanager login -u admin -p admin -- sendalarm -n ManagementServer -t com.hp.usage.diameter.ManagementServer -s Warning -m "Belgrano" ) 2. Set AlarmTTL< 1 to icrease rate of alarm database cleaner 3. Check if the number of alive threads is increasing

Warning: provided test case does not grantee reproducing

One more test case from Rajesh In the test environment this is how it got duplicated: - There were already 3 alarms in the alarm db - Set the AlarmTTL to 1 hour to trigger the alarm db cleaner early - When the alarm cleaner kicks in it was observed it was in tight loop (using visualvm) , this holds the lock on AlarmTableDataProvider - Start sending alarms using sendalarm command in process manager shell - It was observed as long as you send alarms the cached thread pool kept creating threads each of which was locking on AlarmTableDataProvider monitor - Continue sending and after about 9000 threads the process crashes with OOM

Verifier:

Submitter Text Notes:

-------------------------------------- Verified by : Vikram Pai Malpe Release : TISSOT(eIUM 9.0) SIU version : B.09.00 2016/12/26 (RC1) TET Status : Need to be automated --------------------------------------

Test Result: ------------

AuthTokenRenewPeriod, CloudProvider attributes present in CeliometerConnector component which are currently mandatory attributes,can be made optional.

If AuthTokenRenewPeriod not defined,then it has a default value '600' which is proper and CloudProvider attribute if not defined can have a default value of 'openstack-nova', as this is the service which is used to do compute functions in openstack.

Doc snippet: ------------

Classname: com.hp.usage.telemetry.ceilometer.CeilometerConnector

AuthTokenRenewPeriod Required Single-valued Specifies the number of seconds after which the authorization token should be renewed. Syntax: <AuthTokenRenewPeriod> Datatype Long Default Value 600

CloudProvider Required Single-valued Specifies the Cloud Provider to be used. For example: openstack-nova. Syntax: <CloudProvider> Datatype String

//Vikram Pai M on 17/01/2017

Mandatory condition for SNMEType attribute need to be modified to include 'TargetURLAttribute', If TargetURLAttribute' is present then SNMEType attribute must be mandatory

Doc snippet: ------------

SNMEType Required Single-valued Specifies the SNMEType of the request SNME that is used for building telemetry request. Compulsory in case RequestAttribute is planned to be used. Syntax: <SNMEType> Datatype String

Test Info Notes:

Compare documentation in the previous RC with the next one.

ID: QXCR1001527079

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC1 RHEL 7 x64 Java 8u112 ==================

It was found that if during activation it is selected to activate security server and later client security isn't selected, instance couldn't be activated at all.

Problem is due to fact, that during user addition command "secactivate init" is launched. This command automatically secures (updates server.xml) all web apps including repository server. Secured repository server expects host.p12 file to exist, but this file isn't there since client security isn't activated. Thus repository server fails to start normally causing config server to freeze forever.

There is a separate QXCR1001527075 raised for this freeze.

Test Info Notes:

Please verify that:

- if Security Server is being activated on a host, client security checkbox will be "true" (checked) and disabled to the user will have to activate client security (in Console mode, the user will be unconditionally asked the client security parameters) - on reactivation, "Deactivate security for this host" option will not be available (only "Keep", "Modify" and "Reactivate to hybrid/full" options will be available) - if "Deactivate Security Server and client security" option will be selected, security will be correctly deactivated and ACTIVATE_SECURITY* values in activateIUM.ini will be "false"

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
--------------

It was verified that now it is not possible to not activate client sec in case that securityserver
is activated. Thus failure test case is not reproducible.

ID: QXCR1001526977

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

AnniversaryDateCalculationRule crashed with an Illegal Argument when calculating the anniversary date from the current month, if the current month was the last month of the year (December).

Resolution:

AnniversaryDateCalculationRule has been fixed to correctly calculate the anniversary date for this scenario.

Submitter Text Notes:

Unpatched IUM 8.0

At end of 2016, calculations for next billing period using AnniversaryDateCalculationRule failed with IllegalArgumentException:

Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: MONTH at java.util.GregorianCalendar.computeTime(GregorianCalendar.java:2316) at java.util.Calendar.updateTime(Calendar.java:2469) at java.util.Calendar.complete(Calendar.java:1526) at java.util.GregorianCalendar.add(GregorianCalendar.java:846) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.AnniversaryDateCalculationRule.calculateDateByMon thly (Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.AnniversaryDateCalculationRule.applyRule (Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.RuleChain$LastRule.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.AdornmentRule.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.RuleChain.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.ConditionalRule.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.AdornmentRule.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.RuleChain.applyRule(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.rules.AddToListAttributeRule.applyRule(Unknown Source) ... 54 more

I have investigated source for 80FP01 (I do not have source for plain 8.0) but can only find that this is called outside the try/catch loop that should get any overflow from the original month increment. It seems that it would be possible for this situation to cause a problem if the increment is greater than one month - which it is in the configuration (it is 2 months).

Attached is log and configuration.

Test Info Notes:

For example consider this above configuration node setExpirationDate.

Set er_TimeAux NME attribute to 20161213164106 and er_ses_dateCycle NME attribute to 20161115,then when you try to run with the above configuration

Without the patch : It will throw illegal argument exception

With the patch : It will calculate the anniversary date from the start date properly.

Run the regression for this component.

ID: QXCR1001526478

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kapil,Kumar [kkapil@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

IUM Version : B.09.00 2016/12/26 (RC1-Tissot)

In KafkaConsumerTopic,the partition attribute does not support with dynamic NME attribute value. It should support dynamic NME attribute of type integer. Ex. Partition=NumBytes ( NMEAttribute NumBytes should be of Integer Type )

Test Info Notes:

The below new output attributes have been added as a part of the fix.

TopiAttribute: Specifies the NME attribute that will contain the current topic from which this message has been retrieved.

PartitionAttribute:Specifies the NME attribute that will contain the partition number of the message being processed.

OffsetAttribute: Specifies the NME attribute that will contain the offset number in the partition from which the message was retrieved.

The above attribute should work as the per definition.

Verifier: 

IUM Version : 90 Tissot (RC3)
Test Status : PASS

The 3 new output attributes introduced works accordingly.

ID: QXCR1001526007

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SnmpTrapReceiver populated the wrong agent-address in the SNME when ProcessAllVarbinds=true.

Resolution:

The component has been fixed to now have the correct agent-address, obtained from the Trap PDU, in the SNME when ProcessAllVarbinds=true.

Submitter Text Notes:

The agentaddress obtained in the Trap PDU doesn't match the one printed in SNME Address field when ProcessAllVarbinds=true.

[development environment] RHEL : 6.7 IUM : 8.3 FP01 $ java -version java version "1.7.0_80" Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.7.0_80-b15) Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 24.80-b11, mixed mode) $ env grep JAVA_HOME JAVA_HOME=/usr/java/jdk1.7.0_80 $ ls /opt/SIU01/lib/patches/* /opt/SIU01/lib/patches/eIUM83FP01_QXCR1001513094_20161103.jar

[Steps to Reproduce] 1. Send following command from snmptrap sender server /usr/bin/snmptrap -v 1 -c grugru 172.31.159.217 .1.3.6.1.4.1.21296.2.2.1.2.1 192.168.61.128 6 123456 '' .1.3.6.1.4.1.21296.2.2.1.3.1.1.123456 s vb1

2. Check captured packet with tcpdump Please find attached file.

3. Check SnmpTrapReceiver process log 12/27/2016 17:16:24.846 JST pool-3-thread-5 (LogNMERule) INFORMATIVE: NME @ /deployment/mbiu03vv/BBSnmptrap/RuleChains/SuccesRulechainV1/Log is SnmpTrapSnme:SnmpTrap { address "/172.31.159.233" snmpTrapVersion "V1" port 40989 requestId 0 v1Trap SnmpTrapSnme:V1Trap { enterpriseOID "1.3.6.1.4.1.21296.2.2.1.2.1" genericTrapType 6 specificTrapType 123456 community "grugru" } varbinds [ SnmpTrapSnme:VarbindType { varbindOid "1.3.6.1.4.1.21296.2.2.1.3.1.1.123456" varbindValue "vb1" } ] }

This log shows "address "/172.31.159.233"". This 172.31.159.233 is the Network Interface ip address of snmptrap sender server(i.e. TCP/IP layer). But Agent Address should be get from agent-address in SNMP layer."192.168.61.128".

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure a session server and SnmpTrapReceiver under it.

2) Under SnmpTrapReceiver set ProcessAllVarbinds=true to enable it to process all the received traps.

Test Context: When a trap is received by SnmpTrapReceiver, the data from the SNMP trap is populated to SNME. One of the field in the SNME is address field, where the address of the trap sending agent is stored. For a V1 traps the agentaddress is stored in this field.

Test Issue: When a received V1 trap pdu contains a host address as agent-address that is different that the host address of the trap sending machine, then the SnmpTrapReceiver populates SNME address field with the address of the trap sending machine instead of populating it with the address that is obtained as the agent-address in the trap PDU.

For example, if the V1 trap PDU contains X as agentaddress in it and is sent from machine having address Y, then SnmpTrapReceiver populates the SNME's address field with Y instead of X. This is the bug. For a V1 trap, the SNME address should always be populated with the V1 trap agentaddress field, nothing else.

Fix: This pointpatch should contain the fix, where, when ProcessAllVarbinds=true for SnmpTrapReceiver for V1 trap the SNME address will contain the agent address of the v1 trap not the host address of the trap sending machine.

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 2.6.32-642.11.1.el6.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: B.08.03 FP01 2016/03/31
Point Patch Version: eIUM83FP01_QXCR1001526007_20170105_plugin
Java Version: 1.7.0_80
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.7.0_80/jre
===============================================================

'' .1.3.6.1.4.1.21296.2.2.1.3.1.1.123456 s vb1

Submitter Text Notes:

eIUM90 RC1 RHEL 7x64 Java 8u112 ===================

It is suggested to disable "check connection" button on JDS activation screen, if default (embedded) DB is selected. On first activation there is no embedded DB started, thus this button has no sense.

And if it is clicked it corrupts activation since connection fails and it is not possible to proceed. It is required to cancel activation and start over.

Test Info Notes:

Please ensure that connection button is only enabled for all databases (siu20, jds, partitiondb, assetstore, vnfm) when external DB is selected.

eIUM90 RC1 RHEL 7x64 Java 8u112 ===================

It should be updated (VNFMSecActivationHandler/VNFMSecDeActivationHandler) to update also web.xml for cirrus-ui.

Customer Symptom Notes:

Test Info Notes:

List of suggested new test cases The issues was with initial application (Cirrus UI) startup. There is not much else could be done at this initial step. Application either starts normally, or fails with NoClassDefFoundError.

Steps to reproduce the problem before the fix Install eIUM platform, activate it, run VNFM group of applications, Cirrus UI fails to start up, log contains NoClassDefFoundError.

Engineer: Li,Zhiwei [zli@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Env: RH Linux Enterprise 7.0, JDK 1.8.0_60, eIUM9.0 (IC7)

CaseID: LB_TPL_Algo_03.1_WeigthedRoundRobin_Overload_KeepGoing_Abnormal

Summary: Algorithm use its WeightedRoundRobinDispatcher to select one backend server like WeightedRoundRobin. Set OverloadControlPolicy to be KeepGoing. If throughput is exceed the hold threshold of all the backend servers, check result. Then stop Server2, check result, then start Server2, check result again.

Case LB_TPL_Algo_03.1_WeigthedRoundRobin_Overload_KeepGoing_Abnormal Steps: [/deployment/hostname/DiameterLB/LB/DiameterApplication/RootBackendGroup] ClassName=BackendServerGroup BSGMembers=Server1 BSGMembers=Server2 BSGMembers=Server3 [/deployment/hostname/DiameterLB/LB/DiameterApplication/RootBackendGroup/Algorithm] ClassName=ThroughputLimitationAlgorithm ThroughputThresholds=Server1,100 ThroughputThresholds=Server2,200 ThroughputThresholds=Server3,300 DispatchType= WeightedRoundRobin [/deployment/hostname/DiameterLB/LB/DiameterApplication/RootBackendGroup/Algorithm/O verloadControlOption] ClassName=com.hp.usage.loadbalancer.common.KeepGoing

Throughput=900, check ReceiveRequestsThroughput in ops console.

Expect Result: Server1 should accept about 150, Server2 should accept about 300, Server3 accept about 450. Stop Server2, wait about 15m, Server1 should accept about 225, Server3 will accept about 675. Start Server2 again, Server2 will take 300 again.

Actual Result: Stop Server2, wait about 15m, Server1 still accept about 150, Server3 still accept about 450. The screenshot is in the attachment.

Test Info Notes:

in 9.0RC2 build, eIUM LB running with ThroughputLimitationAlgorithm in KeepGoing policy, if one backend server down, the rest of the configured backends would take in charge of all the incoming traffics even if they are exceeded their threshold/

please re-validate this in RC4 build

ID: QXCR1001524561

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

ListMapEntriesRule generated a null pointer exception if it was the last rule in SwitchConditionRule.

Resolution:

ListMapEntriesRule has been fixed to work as the last rule under SwitchConditionRule.

Submitter Text Notes:

We have received a case with the following details.

----------------------------------------------------------- We encountered this issue in ListMapEntriesRule component of eIUM8.3 deployed for Sprint DEG (DEG version 3.0.1). This issue is in eIUM8.3 and not in DEG.

ListMapEntriesRule expects a rulechain to be configured after it in logical flow else it throws the error described in the logs attached. In our case, we have mentioned ListMapEntriesRule as the last rule within a SwitchConditionRule when we encountered this error. Configuring a log rule (for that matter of fact any IUM rule) after ListMapEntriesRule solves the issue.

This is a bug in eIUM8.3 and we expect it to be fixed in the future releases. -----------------------------------------------------------

They didn't upload the logs and configuration when submitting the L2 case and currently Deepthi is on vacation and she will back to the office on November 23rd. However, I think the explanation of the issue is clear but feel free to ask for any additional information to continue the investigation.

     Thanks in advance and Best Regards,
          H??ctor

Test Info Notes:

> How to recreate: 1. Configure ListMapEntriesRule as the last rule in SwitchConditionRule without the patch,It should throw a null pointer exception

> With the patch you'll not see the NullPointerException.

Run regression for ListMapEntriesRule.

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001524155

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

Security re-activation through activator need to be revised to have proper flow.

Resolution:

Security server reactivation and client security re-activation are fixed

Test Info Notes:

Security Server Reactivation ============================= SS reactivation now appears with one additional screen with below options: 1. Keep current security server parameters 2. Modify security server parameters 3. Disable security server and client security

Option 1 will not do anything but will keep the SS activated with old/existing params.

Option 2 will modify some of the parameters for Security server. Screen 1 : User should not be able to change the authorization server details other than the port or protocol type. Screen 2 : User can change the authentication server to any of the available options. Screen 3 : User can update the certification duration. Can't change the root certificate. Can reset the password for root certificate.

Option 3 will deactivate client security as well as security server.

> Make sure you test changing the password for root CA certificate on reactivation

Client Security Reactivation ============================ Case 1 : If activation was done in hybrid mode security reactivation now appears with one additional screen with below options: 1. Keep current host security parameters 2. Modify host security parameters 3. Re-activate to full security mode 4. Disable security for this IUM host

Option 1 will not do anything but will keep the security activated with old/existing params. Option 2 will allow you to modify some of the parameters for client security. Option 3 will allow you to switch to full security mode. Options 4 will just disable client security for this host

Case 2 : If activation was done in full security mode then reactivation now appears with one additional screen with below options: 1. Keep current host security parameters 2. Modify host security parameters 3. Re-activate to hybrid security mode 4. Disable security for this IUM host

Option 1 will not do anything but will keep the security activated with old/existing params. Option 2 will allow you to modify some of the parameters for client security. Option 3 will allow you to switch to hybrid security mode. Options 4 will just disable client security for this host

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC5a
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
=====================

It was verified that security reactivation works fine now.
It is possible in activator to:
#1 Keep current params
#2 Disable security
#3 Change security params
#4 Switch from full security to hybrid mode
#5 Switch from hybrid to full security mode

Submitter Text Notes:

Env: RH Linux Enterprise 7.1, JDK 1.8.0.102, eIUM9.0 (IC7)

CaseID: Acceptance instance installation&activation

Steps: 1. Install eIUM9.0 with MySQL, RTP, security server (embeded) 2. Activate the instance for security mode with valid license

Expect Result: Install and activate successfully

Actual Result: Install successfully, but security activation with embeded security server failed. The activation process will auto exist when load RTP factory template

Investigation: Found there is authorization issue in loadconfig.log, 12/15/2016 13:27:00.528 CST main (19.005.02) INFORMATIVE: Loading Configuration File: /opt/SIU_root/RTP/producttemplates/RTP_Application.config 12/15/2016 13:27:00.530 CST main (19.005.05) ERROR: Couldn't write the configuration to the config server: The server is secured and the client is unsecured 12/15/2016 13:27:00.531 CST main (19.005.01) ERROR: Use proper login / password to load configuration. com.hp.siu.utils.SIUSecurityException: The server is secured and the client is unsecured

So this issue might be the RTP activator part does not give the correct security login information.

Workaround: Tried to find the workflow for RTP activator in "activtor.jar", and remove the load RTP factory template rule first, then the instance can be actived with security successfully I commented "152_load_rtp_templates"

See attached log for reference.

ID: QXCR1001522222

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Pavlenko,Andrey [andrey.pavlenko@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

===================================================== Submitted by : Pavlov Peter IUM version : 90 ic6 OS : Linux 2.6.32-504.el6.x86_64 Java Version : 1.8.0_66 =====================================================

Was found that RepositoryManager backward compatibility is broken. Activation and automated TETs using next CLI operations with repository:

${_SIUBIN}/repositorymanager configure -metaDir <meta_dir> \ -workDir <work_dir> -- connect -- checkout -root datamodel -- disconnect

<Some changes with repository content>

${_SIUBIN}/repositorymanager configure -metaDir $TEMPOUT/${TEST_NAME}/meta \ -workDir <work_dir> -- connect -- checkout -root datamodel -- checkin -confirm no -force yes -- disconnect

Checkout was required for every similar CLI operation with repository, but actually checkout was happened only once, during first checkout call. In other cases, during second checkout call and etc., repositorymanager informed, that checkout already in progress and no checkout was actually happened.

Now, checkout is performed for every call, adding new or modifying existent files under working directory, discarding any changes or adding deleted files.

Test Info Notes:
