ID: QXCR1001521720

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Hernandez,Geoffrey [geoffrey.hernandez@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Customer policy or local regulations may require system privacy, security, and authorized usage notices, making customer compliance with NIST 800-53 difficult and enterprise best practices difficult. As a result, it is recommended that eIUM provide the ability to define and configure the web authorization screen to comply with customer policies or local regulations. The authorization screen shall be defined by the customer or local delivery team, and must be applied to the product without any code changes to the product.

Resolution:

You can now set an authorization page using the context parameter AUTHORIZATION_PAGE, by adding it to the "WEB-INF/web.xml" file in any eIUM web application directory. For example:

<context-param> <param-name>AUTHORIZATION_PAGE</param-name> <param-value>/authorization_sample.html</param-value> </context-param>

If set, then once per session, the user will see this page before accessing any eIUM web application. In order to access the eIUM web application, the page will need to redirect the user to "/authorize". For example:

<form id="authorization_form" action="authorize" method="POST"> <div> <button onclick="document.forms['authorization_form'].submit();">Authorize</button> </div> </form>

As an example, see the "authorization_sample.html" file in any eIUM web application directory. The web application directories mentioned above can be found in the %VARROOT% directory of your eIUM installation, under /webappserver/webapps. For example, C:\SIU\var\webappserver\webapps\web-console on Windows, or /var/opt/SIU/webappserver/webapps/web-console on Linux.

Submitter Text Notes:

Customer policy or local regulations may require system privacy, security and authorized usage notices.

Making customer compliance to NIST 800-53 difficult and enterprise best practices difficult.

Recommended Action:

Provide capability to define and configure the authorization screen to comply with customer policies or local regulations. The authorization screen shall be defined by the customer or local delivery team and must be applied to the product without any code changes to the product.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC5a
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
=====================

It was verified that customized authorization screen could be added to web apps based on example
provided by developer.

ID: QXCR1001521717

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

eIUM should eliminate starter certificates and generate these upon activation. It should also prompt to replace the default certificates and document the process of replacement properly. Replacement can be initiated by delivery or account or support team. Document that all certificates should be managed. Recommendation should be that all certificates are customer-provided and document that all certificates should be managed.

Resolution:

The eIUM Activation Wizard now asks for certificates to be used for web applications on the web applications screen. This is optional, so that if the user does not provide this, then the default will be used. Additionally the "secactivate webapp -httpsupdate ..." command will update the certificates through the command line.

Submitter Text Notes:

HPE eIUM includes a default certificate to enable secure (SSL) web connections, but this certificate is provided by HPE as a starter certificate and would be the same for any default deployment.

Making compliance to NIST 800-53, ISO 27001, Enterprise and HPE support best practices difficult.

Recommended Action:

Product should eliminate starter certificates and generate those upon activation.

Product should prompt to replace the default certificates and document the process of replacement properly.

Replacement can be initiated by delivery or account or support team.

Document that all certificates should be managed Recommendation should be that all certificates are customer provided and documentation that all certificates should be managed

Test Info Notes:

Activator now asks for certificates to be used for web applications on web applications screen. This is optional so if user does not provide then the default will be used. Additionally "secactivate webapp -httpsupdate ......" will update the certificates through command line.

This CR is related to QXCR1001531247 : separate securing webapps from secactivate init using new command

-httpsupdate : Arguments [-identities <identities to be updated with keystore>] [-httpsport <https port>] -certificateKeystoreFile <certificate keystore file> -certificateKeystorePassword <password for keystore> -certificateKeystoreType <type for keystore> deals with updating the https port and certificate keystore details.

By default the identities is optional and the default value is : webappserver

This means the -httpsupdate command updates the %VARROOT%/webappserver/conf/server.xml

In future if new identities added (like licenseserver) then the -identities option can be specified as -identities "webappserver,licenseserver" or -identities "licenseserver" and the corresponding folder under %VARROT%/<identities>/conf/server.xml

Activator has been enhanced to ask for https details on web applications activation screen. This provision will be there even if the deployment is secure or unsecure.

> Make sure if the external web application certificates are provided on webapplication screen under HttpsUpdate flag then the same is getting updated for all web applications under webappserver.

Verifier: 

eIUM90 RC7
RHEL6 x64
Java8u112
---------------

It was verified that all requested functionality works as expected.
Both certificate generated by SS or external one are properly installed into all web apps.

ID: QXCR1001520573

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Chernyavsky,Ivan [chernyavsky@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Current embedded security activation mechanism depends on SleepRule configuration. So for first securityserver start sleep time is 15 seconds same for consequent stop/start. But it could happen that securityserver starts longer, especially first time when it is being initialized. Activation mechanism just goes further, tries to stop and start again, while original instance of securityserver is still starting. This lead to situation when 2 ApacheDS embedded into securityserver are trying to start simultaneously and both fail. Thus security activation crashes on this step.

We need to enhance procedure and get rid of SleepRule. To ensure that securityserver is properly started/stopped we need instead to monitor it logs.

Test Info Notes:

Please ensure that:

- when embedded LDAP provider (Apache DS) is selected during activation, activator process blocks waiting for both securityserver port (e.g. 8443) and LDAP port (e.g. 10389) to became available - when external LDAP provider is selected during activation, activation process only awaits for securityserver port (e.g. 8443)

This could be checked by monitoring the activate.log for messages from SocketStateChecker class (level INFO).

Verifier: 

eIUM90 IC7
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
================

It was verified that required functionality is available in IC7 build.
Activator properly waits for sockets 8443 and 10389 (in case of embedded ApacheDS) for availability
on startup and unavailability on shutdown of securityserver.

ID: QXCR1001520279

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Golubev,Alexander [alexander.golubev@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

During 90 development Scripting Framework has been enhanced with cache capabilities for compiled scripts. Implementation of cache uses static in-memory approach by default so any compiled scripts sit in memory of the process until explicit cleanup is performed through JMX. However there are some components which allows scripting and which support hot-deployment such as Management BPMN2 workflow and partition service. So there is potential OutOfMemory problem without proper and explicit control and maintenance over memory and cache size at runtime which wasn't required before.

Test Info Notes:

Verify that bpmn2 workflow (file or management) with ScriptTask is executed without the following logging from ScriptCache class:

logger_.trace("Caching script with digest {}", scriptDigest);

The trace level most probably corresponds to DEBUG4 so for verification please set this log level. Without this fix using previous RC1..5 we should see these messages and this caching is an issue introduced by changes in Scripting framework which we don't expect to happen for BPMN2 workflow and PartitionService due to their hot-deployment nature and thus fixed.

Verifier: 

===============================================================
Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-514.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: B.09.00 2017/03/13 
Java Version: 1.8.0_102
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_102/jre
===============================================================
CR was verified on eIUM90 RC5a build.

There is FCS configured to execute bpmn2 workflow task ExecuteScript. It was checked that there 
is no "logger_.trace("Caching script with digest {}", scriptDigest);" message in the FCS's log on 
DEBUG4 level.

ID: QXCR1001520066

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

siucontrol -c updateINI logged the wrong host name SIUJava.ini when the command was executed for the remote host.

Resolution:

siucontrol -c updateINI has been fixed to log the message correctly.

Submitter Text Notes:

Hello guys,

The customer complains that siucontrol produce incorrect result.

The problem is related to siucontrol -c updateINI option.

This option can update siu.ini on any host in deployment. However if a remote host is subject of update, it does correction of right SIU.ini however it prints out message that it modifies local SIU.ini which is not true and pretty misleading

Regards Piotr

Test Info Notes:

Execute : siucontrol -c updateINI

For localhost and remote host (-host argument). Remote host applicable for multihost environment. Make sure the log message does not indicate the wrong host. Validate the changes are also done on the right host.

ID: QXCR1001519658

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: R M,Sethuraman [sethuraman.r-m@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The File Distribution Service updated the status to QUEUED after the job was already ASSIGNED to the collector. The job remained in QUEUED status even after it was processed successfully.

Resolution:

Due to the race condition among threads that update job status, the job that was already moved to ASSIGNED status was again updated back to QUEUED status, hence the job status was updated to QUEUED status only when the job was in AVAILABLE status.

Submitter Text Notes:

From the logs, we suspect that the main thread was trying to run its job, but there is no resource for the main thread, so it set the status to 2 and returned.

Our analysis given below as per the logs:

FDS log: ----------------------------------FDS log---------------------------------- 11/14/2016 03:00:50.000 JST main (105.014.46) INFORMATIVE: JobDistributionService.run(): Time to process next set of available jobs --<snip>-- (1)11/14/2016 03:00:50.050 JST RequestProcessor-67758 (JobDistributionService) DEBUG2: JobDistributionService.resourceAvailable()8KCCF9011 (2)11/14/2016 03:00:50.050 JST RequestProcessor-67758 (JobDistributionService) DEBUG2: JobDistributionService.isActive() (3)11/14/2016 03:00:50.053 JST main (JobDistributionService) DEBUG2: JobDistributionService.run(): Next job: /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme (4)11/14/2016 03:00:50.053 JST main (JobDistributionService) DEBUG2: JobDistributionService.assignJobToResource() 11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST --<snip>-- (5)11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST main (ResourceManager) DEBUG: ResourceManager.assignJobToResource(): No resource found, queueing job. (6)11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST main (JobDistributionService) DEBUG3: JobDistributionService: /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nm e status: 2 (7)11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST RequestProcessor-67758 (JobDistributionService) DEBUG2: JobDistributionService.resourceAvailable(): Job selector policy selected the job: /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme (8)11/14/2016 03:00:50.060 JST RequestProcessor-67758 (105.002.05) INFORMATIVE: FileCollectorResource.assignJob(): Assigned /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme to 8KCCF9011 ----------------------------------FDS log----------------------------------

At (1) the thread RequestProcessor-67758 informed from Collector his process finished, soon after main thread tried to get processer. But since no resource for main thread are there, it failed at (5) and STATUS=2 was set at (6). At this time, there is resource for the thread RequestProcessor-67758, the job assigned to Collector.

In other side, the Collector log at same time is below: ----------------------------------Collector log----------------------------- --- -- (A)11/14/2016 03:00:50.049 JST main (JobReceiverFileRollPolicy) DEBUG: JobReceiverFileRollPolicy.getNextFileName(): Notifying JDS (B)11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST RequestProcessor-5 (JobReceiverFileRollPolicy) DEBUG: JobReceiverFileRollPolicy.assignJob ( /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme ) (C)11/14/2016 03:00:50.055 JST RequestProcessor-5 (JobReceiverFileRollPolicy) DEBUG2: JDBCJobManager.updateJob () /<snip>//IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme ----------------------------------Collector log----------------------------- --- --

Last process finished and notified it to FDS at (A). (It caused the FDS log (1).) New file assign at (B) and update JOB table at (C).

The records from the table is given below: +-------------------+--------------+---------------------------------------- --- -----------------------------------------------------------+--------------- +--- -----+ | ID | SOURCE | FILENAME | COLLECTORNAME | STATUS | +-------------------+--------------+---------------------------------------- --- -----------------------------------------------------------+--------------- +--- -----+ | 37441534899259195 | DataSource_1 | /progtool/mdc/data/mdc07/share/data/other/8KSCD9021//IFI_D0320JD_20160220133 8 0100115865_SCD041_0.nme | 8KCCF9011 | 2 | | 38573399910243630 | DataSource_1 | /progtool/mdc/data/mdc07/share/data/other/8KSCD9021//IFI_D0320JD_20160220133 8 0106307684_SCD041_0.nme | 8KCCF9011 | 2 | +-------------------+--------------+---------------------------------------- --- -----------------------------------------------------------+--------------- +--- -----+

Their test environment: Structure: FCD-FDS-Collector Jobs: periodical put job files to FCS file get directory and run eIUM. Situation: At the time around 5000,000 files processed, this case reproduced. Process name: FCS :8KFCF9111 FDS :8KFCF9121 Collector:8KCCF9011, 8KCCF9012, 8KCCF9013, 8KCCF9014, 8KCCF9015, 8KCCF9016, 8KCCF9017, 8KCCF9018 The reproduce file name: IFI_D0320JD_2016022013380106307684_SCD041_0.nme

Test Info Notes:

You should have FCS,FDS and collector in place.

FCS will generate JOBS

FDS will assign jobs to collector,acts like a load balancer

Collector process the jobs.

Run these 3 process,check for the status in the corresponding table in the database and the logs.

If the logs shows a particular job is assigned to ASSIGNED status(status 3) as per logs,Its corresponding DB update should always be 3,It should not be in the status 2 or queued status

======= Updated by Sukhwinder on 23-Nov-2016 ======== The reported issue occurs very rare (once in couple of months) Based on the logs its been identified that: > FDS tries to assign the job to respective resource (collector). > If collector is unavailable then the job is updated to QUEUED (2) status and later when the resource is available the job is ASSIGNED. > The issue occurs when the FDS check for resource and its unavailable and the FDS initiates the call to update the job status to QUEUED. But at the same moment resoruce became available and the job was assigned. The root cause is that collector somehow updates the database table first (i.e. updates to ASSIGNED). and then FDS gets access to database and updates the status to QUEUED. > The job gets assigned to collector and got processed successfully but the job status remains as QUEUED.

To fix the issue the database query by FDS to update the job status has been updated from: UPDATE <TableName> set status= Job.QUEUED WHERE ID=<JobID>; To -> UPDATE <TableName> set status= Job.QUEUED WHERE ID=<JobID> and status != Job.ASSIGNED;

If the issue is not reproducible, please run regression for FDS.

The ListAttribute in DelimiterParser appended the value of the list attribute from the previous record to the current record.

Resolution:

DelimiterParser has been fixed to add only the values corresponding to the current record in the ListAttribute.

Submitter Text Notes:

problem with ListAttribute serialaziation in Polkomtel environment.

1. Every following record read by the collector has ListAttribute extended by all already read List Attributes, in other words ListAttribute is not cleared between parsed records.

As the consumer is consuming it Check your log file(Consumer Log file),Check the list attribute value,It should Now contain non-appended values corresponding to the current record

Changes are done in TextParser class so the regeression has to be done for below components: DelimiterParser NameValuePArser PerlRegexParser RealServerParser RegexParser TextOffsetParser

It was verified that running CS is able to continue working when MySQL becomes unavailable. But 2 more enhancements are still required:

ID: QXCR1001511509

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Baikerikar,Vivekananda [vivekananda.baikerikar@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

DeliverySFTP stopped responding with jsch jar version=0.1.48 expecting credentials from the user.

Resolution:

DeliverySFTP has been fixed to use public key and password authentication methods by default, and skip using "gssapi-with-mic,keyboard-interactive", which caused the infinite waiting for Kerberos user credentials.

Submitter Text Notes:

Issue similar to QXCR1001511085 exists in DeliverySFTP Component due to which the sftp connection hangs expecting credentials from user.

With jsch version 0.1.48 gssapi-with-mic,keyboard-interactive authentication methods were enabled thus causing prompts for Kerberos username and password prompts there by causing infinite wait for the user inputs. These authentication methods have to be disabled.

Test Info Notes:

Please test as usual. With the fix publickey and password will be used as default Authentication methods. and it shouldn't hang asking for Kerberos credentials.

Verifier:

Verified by : Chandan Viswanath
Release	    : 8.3
Branch	    : 8.3CPE
Patch       : eIUM83Patch.20161128-1015.patch [RC1]

Result      : PASS

ID: QXCR1001510364

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Stepien,Sylwester (Everett) [sstepien@hpe.com]

Symptoms:

Template service was updated based on QXCR1001477834 Ttemplate service bridge should be able to support attribute removal as well.

Resolution:

This feature has been implemented, unwanted parameter can be removed using removeAttrs attribute of templateServiceBridge example: <templateServiceBridge registryUrl="http://${MHOST}:8158/" templateFilePath="templates/user/Demo_Simple.config" templateInputValue="CollectorName=${collectorName},database_Datastore=jdbc:mysql:// ${MHOST}:3306/siu20,password_Datastore=siu20,user_Datastore=siu20,SelectedHost=${HostName}" removeAttrs="Description_Demo_-_Simple"/>

multiple attributes are comma separated removeAttrs="Description_Demo_-_Simple,yetAnotherParamter"

Test Info Notes:

For example we have following customizable attribute (PersistentConnectionAddress) in template. Based on configuration this attribute may be dropped at all (0-unbounded):

[/deployment/host/DRA/Connectors/DiameterServer]

AnswerTimeoutRulechain=NoAnswer â€¦ @Customizable(name="PersistentConnectionAddress", pattern="{Host_DiameterServer}, {Realm_DiameterServer}", numvalues="0-unbounded") PersistentConnectionAddress= â€¦ ProductName=Diameter Subscriber Router Function Server ProxiableFlagAttribute=DRA_ProxyAbleFlag_Int

Before change templateServiceBridge is used this way: <templateServiceBridge registryUrl="http://${HostIP}:8158/" templateFilePath="templates/factory/DRA/BES_Pool.config" templateInputValue="SelectedHost=${HostName},CollectorName=DiameterBES_Pool"/>

The result will be:

[/deployment/dra-application1/DiameterBES_Pool/Connectors/DiameterServer]

AnswerTimeoutRulechain=NoAnswer â€¦ @Customizable(name="PersistentConnectionAddress", pattern="{Host_DiameterServer}, {Realm_DiameterServer}", numvalues="0-unbounded") PersistentConnectionAddress= â€¦ ProductName=Diameter Subscriber Router Function Server ProxiableFlagAttribute=DRA_ProxyAbleFlag_Int

But there is no way in templateServiceBridge to say this customizable attribute occur 0 times (should be removed from the configuration). We should get configuration like this:

[/deployment/dra-application1/DiameterBES_Pool/Connectors/DiameterServer]

AnswerTimeoutRulechain=NoAnswer â€¦ ProductName=Diameter Subscriber Router Function Server ProxiableFlagAttribute=DRA_ProxyAbleFlag_Int

To get configuration as above please use following: <templateServiceBridge registryUrl="http://${HostIP}:8158/" templateFilePath="templates/factory/DRA/BES_Pool.config" templateInputValue="SelectedHost=${HostName},CollectorName=DiameterBES_Pool"/ removeAttrs="PersistentConnectionAddress">

Verifier: 

=================================
Found in Version : eIUM90
Found in Build   : eIUM90(RC6)
Target Version   : eIUM90
Tester           : Penumathsa Chaitanya Varma
=================================

If we install DRA1.1 with latest CIS and call the custom target operation which contains the 
"removeattr" key ( <templateServiceBridge registryUrl="http://${HostIP}:8158/" 
templateFilePath="templates/factory/DRA/BES_Pool.config" 
templateInputValue="SelectedHost=${HostName},Col                                           
lectorName=DiameterBES_Pool" removeAttrs="PersistentConnectionAddress" />) if we call that 
operation then it will execute successful. In Previously  build if we call this operation we will 
get an error saying that "removeattr" is not supported.

ID: QXCR1001509221

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Sadovnycha,Mariia [mariia.sadovnycha@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

===================================================== Submitted by : Pavlov Peter IUM version : 90 ic3 OS : Linux 2.6.32-504.el6.x86_64 Java Version : 1.8.0_66 =====================================================

SDK Rule class name validation is required in both groovy/Java rule code. If class name starting with lowercase character it cannot be used by Class Loader and chint cannot be generated.

Example: class IsRequired extends SDKRule { <--- works fine

class isRequired extends SDKRule { <--- doesn't work

Test Info Notes:

New SDK project will support Class name validation automatically. Validation runs during project build.

To enable Class name validation for SDK projects created earlier: Select project -> Properties -> Validation -> Select Add Validation Builder to project

Verified by : Pavlov Peter
IUM version : 90 ic6

ID: QXCR1001506995

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Test SMS message was not retried at all for the second connection if it was retried the maximum number times for the first connection for a negative response.

Resolution:

Test SMS message is now retried the maximum number of times as configured for the second connection, and also in case of a negative response.

Submitter Text Notes:

When the SMPP server is down, the test SMS sending is retried full maximum number of attempts as configured. However, for a 2nd connection to same server if the server is down again, then test SMS is not retried at all.

Test Info Notes:

1) Configure SMPPClientConnector under a SessionServer.

2) Configure RetryIfStatus under SMPPClientEndPoint.

3) Configure SendSMSOnConnectionOpen = jmx and configure TestSMSCreator sub-node under SMPPClientEndPoint to send test SMS when connetion is opened via JMX operation.

Test Scenario: For the test SMS response, if the SMPP server returns a response code that matches with RetryIfStatus code, then client will retry sending the test SMS message till Maximum number of times.

Test To reproduce: (Before Fix)

1) Now consider to create connection 1 via JMX operation, the test SMS sending is retried sending maximum number of times and at the last attempt the test SMS sending passes and connection 1 is created.

2) Now to create connection 2 in the same way through JMX, if the server again responds back with a status that should make the client retry sending the test SMS, the client doesn't retry at all to send the test SMS message. In one failure it fails to create the connection and no retry is done at all.

After Fix:

In the exact above 1&2 steps, the test SMS should be retried sending again and again till maximum number of times as was tried for connection 1. It should not fail at once.

This is because the retry variable inside the test SMS message is never reset to zero after it is incremented till max value for any connection if is retried because of server's response.

Test Case 2:

Please refer to the test Info note of the CR

QXCR1001506937: Config attribute is required to send test sms to SMPP server

for further tests related to the config attribute SendSMSOnConnectionOpen=jmx

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-327.28.3.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.08.03 2015/04/02"
Patch Version: eIUM83IM.20160808-1446
Point Patch Version: eIUM83IM_QXCR1001506995_20160912
Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
==========================================================

It was verified using attached configuration SMPPClientCon_05 and SMPPSim that proper fix was 
introduced.

Without PP retries on TestSMS sending are applied only for first attempt.
Even connection is established finally, for the second and next attempts no more retries happend if 
SMPPSim continues to reply with error code before sending success reply.

With PP applied, each new connection opened and thus attempt to send a TestSMS passes through fresh 
retry cycle.

Regression TET scenario was identified and launched with 100% pass rate.
Results are attached.

==26/Dec/2016======
eIUM90 RC1
RHEL 7x64
Java 8u112
===================

It was verified that this fix is included into eIUM90 RC1.

ID: QXCR1001506673

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

RadiusSessionState generated a NullPointerException if the input file started with a logout event.

Resolution:

RadiusSessionState has been fixed to generate the NullPointerException cause more clearly.

Submitter Text Notes:

Dear L3 team,

We have a new case related to the RadiusSessionState component. We consider it is a bug and we should fix it.

Details: eIUM 8.3 In the component reference, chapter RadiusSessionState it is written:

i. In case of a lost start event, it starts a session when the first interim event for a session arrives. ii. In case of a logout event only for the whole session (missed login and interim events), it does not drop it but takes session duration from the NME attribute defined by SessionDurationAttribute configuration attribute, calculates the session start time and flushes the incomplete NME.

But if the first file to be processed starts with ???logout??? event, the collector crashes with NPE error. I attached the collector configuration, log with the crash (DEBUG4), NME scheme and several input files.

The input file VAAAVM3_20160622052130_RADAP00_007.dat starts from the ??? login??? event, then it has ???logout??? event for the session, and then another ??? logout??? event for a new session. The input files VAAAVM3_20160622052130_RADAP00_008.dat and VAAAVM3_20160622052130_RADAP00_009.dat contain only one record in each file with ???logout??? event.

I made a test:

Test Info Notes:

CloneServer: cloned configuration will not have service attributes like MBeanServerConnection, AdminInterface, QueryInterface. These attributes will be created if necessary during the first start of the server.

UpdateServer/CloneServer does not change the order of attributes and annotations. If you use SaveConfig command to get updated/cloned config, please pay attention that this command use sorting to write config, so you may receive another order of attributes/annotations/nodes.

ID: QXCR1001505387

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

ESMEConnection created two SMPP sessions for each connection in BIND_RX mode when BindAtStartup was set to true.

Resolution:

The component has been fixed to create one SMPP session for each connection in BIND_RX mode when BindAtStartup is set to true.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently ESMEConnection creates two TCP channel for each connection in BIND_RX mode when BindAtStartup is set to true. This create an extra TCP connection which should not exist.

Test Info Notes:

ESMEConnector: -------------

1) Please refer to the attached config to the CR.

2) Configure SessionServer and ESMEConnector under it.

3) Configure BindAtStartup=true under SMPPEndPoint config.

4) Now under SMPPEndPoint configure HostAddresses.

Test Scenario:

1) When BindAtStartup=true is true, for each HostAddress there should be one SMPP session created through which SMPP messages will be sent.

Issue: At the start of the component, BindAtStartup=true, for HostAddress, two TCP connections are established underlying. This is visible from the netstat command.

(netstat -na | grep 2775 ) <considering the SMPP server/SIM run in 2775>.

Fix:

After the patch, to each HostAddress, only TCP connection is established. This will also be visible from the above netstat command.

SMPPClientConnector:

1) For SMPPClientConnector -

Please configure ReconnectInterval > 0 under SMPPClientEndPoint. This will create the same issue for new SMPPClientConnector as well.

Issue: 1) For each SMPP connection created to send an SMPP message to SMPP server, two TCP channels should be visible in the netstat command.

After the fix:

1) For each SMPP connection created to send an SMPP message to SMPP server, only one TCP channel should be visible in the netstat command.

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-327.28.3.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.08.03 2015/04/02"
Patch Version: eIUM83IM.20160808-1446
Point Patch Version: eIUM83IM_QXCR1001505387_20160901
Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
============================================================

It was verified using attached configs (configs.zip) and SMPP simulator that without PP both 
SMPPEndPoint and SMPPClientEndPoint open 2 TCP connections in case of BIND_RX mode.
This is visible in netstat output.

With PP applied only 1 TCP connection is opened.

Regression scenario was identified and launched with 100% pass rate.
Results are attached.

ID: QXCR1001502519

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

SMTPClientConnector needs to support startTLS mode to connect to the SMTP server.

Resolution:

The component now supports this mode.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently if the SMTP server expects to communicate with in a startTLS mode, the SMTPClientConnector doesn't support and email cannot be sent. It either supports plaintext or SSL mode. This needs to fix to support a startTLS mode.

Test Info Notes:

1) Configure SessionServer and SMTPClientConnector under it.

2) SMTPServer needs to be configured that supports startTLS communication on a port.

3) startTLS is a connection where the no SSL negotation is required to connect. Therefore, the EnableSSL should to set to false under SMTPEndPoint.

4) Please configure a new config attribute SMTPProperties under SMTPEndPoint. This is an multi- value attribute designed to pass SMTP properties that can be useful to create SMTP sessions and leading to connection management.

5) Add the following entry to activate startTLS mode under SMTPProperties config attribute. mail.smtp.starttls.enable,true

6) Please refer to attached config for details. The EndPoint to test the startTLS mode will be to connect to smtp.office365.com server. The EndPoint SmtpEndPoint_Office365 can be used to test this CR.

7) When using the server the from address MUST be notificaciones@claro360.com. This external server won't send email otherwise.

Test Case1:

Using the EndPoint SmtpEndPoint_Office365 where startTLS property is passed using the SMTPProperties config attribute email should be sent.

Result: 1) With the property mail.smtp.starttls.enable,true under SMTPProperties IS SET the email should go through fine.

2) If the mail.smtp.starttls.enable,true under SMTPProperties IS NOT SET, then email should not go through and exception should be displayed in the log.

Test Case2: Please check the documentation of the new config attribute SMTPProperties under SMTPEndPoint.

Test Case3: The EnableSSL attribute is deprecated. Please configure a new attribute ConnectionSecurity. The values allowed in this attribute are None, StartTLS and SSL. If the value is set to None, then no SSL handshake will be done and email will be sent over a plain non-secured connection. If the value is set to StartTLS (another mode of SMTP connection), then the connection will be established through non-secured fashion and later the connection will be upgraded to SSL mode by exchanging certificate in order to send the email. If the value is set to SSL, then entire connection setup and email sending will be done, through SSL.

For both StartTLS and SSL mode, the truststore file, password and truststore type if be configured, then these will be used for certificate exchange. If these are not configured, then default truststore settings will be used.

Test Results:

1) For None mode, the email should go through fine, without any certificate and trust store settings.

2) For StartTLS and SSL mode, the SSL handshake should happen and then email should go through fine if the truststore contains server ceritificate.

3) If truststore attributes are not configured, and JVM's default truststore doesn't contain the SMTP server certificate, then exception should be throw and email will not go through got both StartTLS and SSL mode.

Test Case 4: Check the documentation of ConnectionSecurity config attribute and EnableSSL should be shown as deprecated.

Verifier:

Symptoms:

The File Distribution Service (FDS) was reassigning the file to the collector that had been previously processed by the collector.

Resolution:

The FDS and JobReceiverPolicy have been enhanced to provide more details in the logs while processing the jobs.

Submitter Text Notes:

The customer is getting the following error in Collector( Job receiver) after restarting the process.

06/01/2016 22:25:27.334 JST RequestProcessor-5 (105.009.13) INFORMATIVE: JobReceiverFileRollPolicy.assignJob( /share01/share/data/other/1HSCD9021//IFI_D0510JD_20160205034500631_SCD182_0. nme assigned successfully 06/01/2016 22:25:27.335 JST main (105.009.05) INFORMATIVE: JobReceiverFileRollPolicy.getNextFileName(): Next file assigned by Distribution Service: /share01/share/data/other/1HSCD9021//IFI_D0510JD_20160205034500631_SCD182_0. nme 06/01/2016 22:25:27.335 JST main (08.179.02) INFORMATIVE: Setting next file to /share01/share/data/other/1HSCD9021//IFI_D0510JD_20160205034500631_SCD182_0. nme 06/01/2016 22:25:27.348 JST main (08.179.08) CRITICAL: NMEFileEncapsulator.getNME(): Stopping collector java.lang.RuntimeException: Unable to open file /share01/share/data/other/1HSCD9021/IFI_D0510JD_20160205034500631_SCD182_0.n me at com.hp.usage.nme.datastore.SNMEInputFile.open(Unknown Source) at com.hp.siu.collector.datastore.NMEInputFile.open(Unknown Source)

L2 investigation shows that this file is already processed by the collector in February month. The FCS log shows that this file has already processed in February, then FDS assigned the file to the collector and collector processed the file with out any error. The collector moved this file to some other location as per te cleanup policy defined.

Later in 1st of June the customer has restarted the processes and they have found this problem. They have to do the cleanup of the collector to make the collector running. Here there's no messages at the FCS log, but if we look at the FDS, we can see that it's assiging this file to the collector. As the file is not available the collector crashes with the error Unable to open file.

The customer has reported that this is the second time they are facing this problem. The log snippet is attached. The file size is very huge, so cannot upload it here. The log snippet file has 1. 1st of June - Collector crash 2. Collector output shows the file has processed in 5th of Feb. 3. FDS log shows the file is processed in 5th of Feb. 4. FDs assign the job to collector 5. FDS log on 1st of June - After restart

Test Info Notes:

The issue is happening rarely for the customer,we have added extra log statements in info level to track the status change of the job

If at all the issue occurs yet again we could get sufficient information from log statements that are added in info level,which prints job name with status

The reason for adding log statement in info level is because customer is operating in this level

ID: QXCR1001499662

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

LDAPConnector should never de-reference aliases.

Resolution:

LDAPConnector now has java.naming.ldap.derefAliases set to "never" to never de-reference aliases.

Submitter Text Notes:

IUM Version: PatchName=eIUM83Telcel, PatchVersion=20150803-1045

LDAP lookup fails with the following message:

UIR_ErrorCodeString=javax.naming.NamingException, UIR_ErrorMessageString= [LDAP: error code 36 - BackUDRServer does not allow derefAlways dereferencing yet]

eIUM should be enhanced to allow to set java.naming.ldap.derefAliases=never

Attached you can find the config/logs (imaConfig.rar) and a java test program that was successfully able to connect to LDAP Server if the line:

env.put("java.naming.ldap.derefAliases", "never");

is set.

ID: QXCR1001499658

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Tsoukanov,Victor [victor.tsoukanov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The oldest timer should have the highest priority to be executed, otherwise it will never be invoked by the TimerExecutor.

Resolution:

The oldest timers have the highest priority to be executed, in case they were missed in the previous execution.

Submitter Text Notes:

There is problem in the algorithm of TimerExecutor (com.hp.usage.timers.TimerExecutor) to scan and update expired timers from FSM_timers table. Suppose there are 300 (or more) rows in FSM_timers table and they all have the same fire time. The parameters are: PoolingPeriod=60s QueueCapacity=100 Renew cycle=80s (decided by business logic)

Then after 11 rounds of timer execution, timers with ID range 1-100 will be renewed for 8 times while ID range 101-200 renewed for 3 times. And timers with ID>200 are never renewed! For more detail,please refer to attachment "FireTimeUpdateSequence.xlsx"

Two problems here: 1) the renew speed is not even among timers 2) many timers never have chance to be renewed.

Suggestion: The oldest timer should have highest priority to be executed.

Test Info Notes:

Test it with latest Tissot or 8.3_fp02_cpe build

Verifier: 

this bug should be described in doc. there won't be greatly impact

It was verified that required functionality exists in eIUM83Patch RC1 build.
In 83CPE there is no possibility to use DiameterRequestRule with Router (not implemented) so there
is different approach to reproduce issue and verify fix.
Attached configs DClient2 sends requests to DRelay2 which has 2 URIs for each realm.
First URI is always unavailable. Second URI becomes available when DServer2 is started.

So without DServer2 DRelay2 is unable to relay request from DClient2 anywhere.
Without fix there is no reply for such requests, thus on DClient2 side it is always timeout event.
After starting DServer2 behaviour doesn't change.

With fix applied, without DServer2 started DRelay2 send proper 3002 code back to DClient2.
When DServer2 is started, message from DClient2 




is properly transferred by DRelay2 to it.
----
siuinvoke -n DClient2 -rulechain dcrulechain4 -data session_Id "session_Id_1A" user_Name "user2"
destrealm "realm.com"
----

ID: QXCR1001495852

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Memory usage kept increasing for HTTPEndPoint when connections were closed after each request.

Resolution:

Memory usage is now stable and no longer increases for this component when connections are closed after each request.

Submitter Text Notes:

Memory usage keeps growing for HTTPEndPoint when connections are closed after each request. This is due to non-clearing of an internal map maintained under generic EndPoint code.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure HTTPEndPoint in any configuration. The use-case is to use HTPPEndPoint.

2) Configure CloseConnectionAfterEachRequest=true under HTTPEndPoint. Memory usage keeps growing for HTTPEndPoint when connections are closed after each request. This is due to non-clearing of an internal map maintained under generic EndPoint code.

3) With this flag set to true the memory issue can be reproduced.

Test Run: Keep sending messages through HTPPConnector using HTTPEndPoint, the memory should keep growing for the process.

After the fix. The memory should be stable for the process duration after the fix.

Verifier: 

Test Scenario:

1) configure HTTPEndPoint in HTTPClientConnector. The use-case is to use HTTPEndPoint for sending 
requests and HTTPConnector is configured as server.

2) Configure CloseConnectionAfterEachRequest=true under HTTPEndPoint on client side.

3)Configure the Below session server container properties for the HTTPClientConnector and 
HTTPConnector :

JVMOPTS=%DEFAULTS%
JVMOPTS=-XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError
JVMOPTS=-XX:HeapDumpPath=/tmp/Rest_Hproc.log
JVMOPTS=-Xloggc:/tmp/Rest_GC.log
JVMOPTS=â€“Xms32m
JVMOPTS=â€“Xms256m
PROCESSARGS=-l 8
STARTUPMODE=Manual 

4)Scheduler in client side,xml requests are sent within period of 1ms for the duration of 12 mins.

5)After Session server are stopped,Rest_GC.log is saved in the location of /tmp folder,which is 
opened on Jmeter tool for Heap memory usage after Garbage collection analysis.

ID: QXCR1001495802

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

When SMPPClientEndPoint was removed through a JMX operation, the UserInitiatedFlag of the ConnectionStatusHandler was not set to 1 for each connection closed.

Resolution:

The ConnectionStatusHandler UserInitiatedFlag is now set to 1 for each connection closed, when SMPPClientEndPoint is removed through a JMX operation.

Submitter Text Notes:

When SMPPClientEndPoint is removed through JMX operation, it doesn't set the UserInitFlag of the SMPPClientConnection to 1 which it should. This UserInitFlag is used in the connection status handler rulechain where value 1 is expected for further processing.

Test Info Notes:

Test Setup:

1) Configure SessionServer , DynamicEndPointSelector and SMPPClientConnector under it.

2) Configure sub-node with name ConnectionStatusHandler of class com.hp.usage.connector.AsyncRuleChainInvoker under DynamicEndPointSelector (DEPS).

3) This ConnectionStatusHandler handler should invoke a rule chain when a connection is created, goes down, become active again (rebind) or closed.

4) Under ConnectionStatusHandler sub-node configure attribute UserInitiatedFlag. This attribute must be configured to an NME attribute which will contain either 0 or 1.

5) 0 for this flag means, the connection event is initiated with rule chain not through JMX operation. 1 for this flag means the connection event is triggered through JMX operation, like creation of a connection, close of connection etc.

6) Please refer to the attached config for details of it.

Test Case 1: Issue 1) When a connection is closed through closeConnection operation under connection MBean in OPs console, the UserInitiatedFlag value is set to 1 when the rule chain is invoked. This works fine.

2) However, when the EndPoint is closed entirely through the removeEndPoint JMX operation containing active connections, then when each connection is closed and the rule chain is invoked the UserInitiatedFlag is NOT set to 1. It should be set 1 in that case also since the endpoint is closed through JMX.

Test Result: With the fix, when the EndPoint is closed through JMX operation, then all the connections when are getting closed, invokes the rule chain with the UserInitiatedFlag set to 1. A LogNME rule can be used to verify the value of the NME attribute set against the UserInitiatedFlag config attribute.

Verifier: 

Operating System Name: Linux
Operating System Version: 3.10.0-327.13.1.el7.x86_64
Operating System Architecture: amd64
SIU Version: Z7092EA - IUM version "B.08.03 2015/04/02"
Patch Version: eIUM83IM.20160726-1408 (005-RC1)
Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
=================================================================

It was verified that UserInitFlag is properly set to 1 when whole end point is removed through JMX.

ID: QXCR1001494762

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The Unbind command was not sent for each active connection closure when SMPPClientConnector was stopped.

Resolution:

The Unbind command is now sent for each active connection closure when SMPPClientConnector is stopped.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently when SMPPClientConnector is stopped, it doesn't send any Unbind SMPP command to SMPP server for the all the active connections that are about to be closed. CloseOperation JMX operation does send it when a connection is closed. Therefore the SMPPClientConnector should do the same.

Test Info Notes:

Test Scenario:

1) During the operation of SMPPClientConnector, new connections are created either through rulechain invocation or through JMX createConnection() operation under EndPoint.

Issue: When the connection is closed through JMX operation an Unbind SMPP message is sent to the SMPP server. However, when the session server (SS) is about to stop, then no Unbind message that is sent to SMPP server. This is the problem. So, when the SS stops, for each active connections in the SMPPClientConnector an Unbind message should be sent to SMPP server.

Fix: With the fix, when SS stops, for each active connections at the time of stopping, an Unbind message should be sent. It should be visible in the Server/SIM log and also the client connectot log should show the connection state being changed from TRX/RX -> CLOSED.

Verifier:

Java Version: 1.8.0_74
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.8.0_74/jre
=================================================================

It was verified that Unbind is being properly sent whenever connection is closed from JMX or session
server with SMPPClientConnector is stopped completely.

ID: QXCR1001494479

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The connection was not obtained from the EndPoint due to an infinite loop in the HashMap.put method in a multi-threaded environment.

Resolution:

The underlying HashMap has been changed to a ConcurrentHashMap to fix the infinite loop, while putting a key in a multi-threaded environment.

Submitter Text Notes:

Currently when SMS sending process tries to fetch a connection from the EndPoint, it never gets a connection because an underlying HashMap goes into infinite loop while trying to do a put in it, in a multi-threaded environment.

Test Info Notes:

As per customer record, they ran the SMPPClientConnector for 20 hours and then they reported that after that the CPU usage is 100% by the process and is not reducing the usage.

With the thread dump it is found out that in the connector framework, the task are not getting a connection. This is because the an underlying hashmap's put method is never returned due to concurrency issue. In a multi-threaded environment the non-thread safe HashMap is believed to show such behavior of infinite loop inside it while PUT method is executed. The following link suggested that.

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/13695832/explain-the-timing-causing-hashmap-put-to-execute-an-infinite-loop

HashMap is clearly documented as not thread safe. So, the correct fix is to use a thread-safe implementation of Map, ConncurrentHashMap

1)

As per testing, we can use SMPPClientConnector and send messages continuously for longer hours and see if it can be reproduced. It cannot be assured that it can be reproduced consistenly. However, that's procedure.

2) Please run regression also for all the client connectors with EndPoint in it. This issue is related to connector framework EndPoint, therefore potentially exists for all EndPoints. With this fix, it should be solved.

Note: As an early access a loose plugin with this fix was given to the field and they confirmed that it is working after running for long period of time.

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001488616

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Tsoukanov,Victor [victor.tsoukanov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

Support is needed for disabling the statistics history in the Management Server.

Resolution:

Setting the HistoryTTL to 0 in the com.hp.usage.managementservice.ManagementService configuration allows disabling the statistics history.

Submitter Text Notes:

It should be possible to disable default performance measurement job.

Test Info Notes:

1. Apply patch 2. Set HistoryTtl=0, see com.hp.usage.managementservice.ManagementService in component reference for more details 3. Start MS 4. Monitor value for HistorySize in bean mgmt:name=performanceMeasurement,type=managementService. It should be always = 0 5. Check database table 'default_job_meas_record'. It should be no new records anymore. 6. Stop MS 7. Set HistoryTtl=2 8. Monitor value for HistorySize in , it should constantly rising and resting to '0' every 5 minutes 9. Check database table 'default_job_meas_record'. It should be some new records every 5 minutes

Verifier: 

Release: 83 + eIUM83Vivo.20151124-2047.patch
PP: eIUM83Vivo_QXCR1001488616_20160606_plugin.jar
Java Home: /opt/jdk1.7.0_65/jre 
TET Status: automation is needed
==================================

The CR was tested according test scenario from the Test Info Notes. Following steps:

0. Stop MS.
1. Run command below to see last table values:
/opt/SIU_83_rc8/mysql/bin/mysql -h localhost -P 3306 --protocol=TCP -usiu20 -psiu20 siu20 -
e "select
* from default_job_meas_record"
2. Apply patch.
3. Set HistoryTTL=0.
4. Start MS.
5. Monitor value for HistorySize in bean mgmt:name=performanceMeasurement,type=managementService
within 5 minutes using command:
/opt/SIU_83_rc8/bin/SIUJava -jar /opt/SIU_83_rc8/lib/3rdparty/iioptestclient.jar
/tmp/TET/iiopclient_prop "mgmt:name=performanceMeasurement,type=managementService" get HistorySize
6. Check database table 'default_job_meas_record'. It should be no new records anymore. 
7. Stop MS.
8. Set HistoryTTL=2.
9. Monitor value for HistorySize , it should constantly rising and reseting to '0' every 5 minutes.
10. Check database table 'default_job_meas_record'. It should be some new records every 5 minutes.
11. Stop MS.
12. Remove HistoryTTL attributes and check default behavior as in steps 9,10.

Submitter Text Notes:

Iâ€™d like to clarify following errors. When any new SMPPClientEndPoint is being created I see following error in log.

---------------- 05/25/2016 04:43:20.018 PDT RMI TCP Connection(9)-16.53.146.255 (DynamicEndPointSelector) DEBUG4: DynamicEndPointSelector.getConnection(): Creating new EndPoint for localhost9999smppclientgood 05/25/2016 04:43:20.018 PDT RMI TCP Connection(9)-16.53.146.255 (Config) DEBUG2: Instantiating config entry: /SMPPClientConnector/SMPPClientConnector/EndPointSelector/EndPoint/null â€¦ 05/25/2016 04:43:20.029 PDT RMI TCP Connection(9)-16.53.146.255 (StatRegistryImpl) ERROR: Failed to register statistical attributes for IUM:EndPoint=localhost9999smppclientgood,ConnectorID=SMPPClientConnector java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Unknown statistics provider instance IUM:EndPoint=localhost9999smppclientgood,ConnectorID=SMPPClientConnector at com.hp.usage.mgmt.naming.ObjectNameFactory.createStatProviderName(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.management.StatRegistryImpl.validateObjectName(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.management.StatRegistryImpl.registerStatAttributes(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.management.StatRegistryImpl.handleNotification(Unknown Source) â€¦ at com.hp.usage.connector.EndPoint.registerMBean(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.connector.DynamicEndPointSelector.createEndPoint(Unknown Source) at com.hp.usage.connector.DynamicEndPointSelector.addEndPoint(Unknown Source) ----------------

ID: QXCR1001484232

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Sharma,Surendra [surendra.sharma@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

A RADIUS response message expects that the "code" value should be present, otherwise it will generate an exception (java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Invalid radius message code: 0). This occurred after migrating from 8.0 Feature Pack 1 to 8.0 Feature Pack 2.

Resolution:

After migrating from 8.0 Feature Pack 1 to 8.0 Feature Pack 2, setting the "code" value while creating the RADIUS response in the rule chain is not mandatory. The RuleChainMessageProcessor component invokes the rule chain to process the RADIUS request, and for synchronous mode, it expects that the RADIUS response will be created by the rule chain. If the RADIUS response is created from one of the types present in the RADIUS namespace (that is, AccessAccept, AccessChallenge, AccessReject, or AccountingResponse), and if the RADIUS response SNME does not contain a value for "code", based on the RADIUS response type, the RADIUS server internally identifies the "code" value and populates its value. Setting the "code" value in the RADIUS response SNME meanwhile is not mandatory.

ID: QXCR1001479319

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

ESMEConnection generated an IllegalStateException while trying to rebind to the SMPP server in receiver mode.

Resolution:

The component has been fixed to allow rebinding to the SMPP server in receiver mode.

Submitter Text Notes:

ESMEConnection throws IllegalStateException while trying to rebind in BIND_RX mode. Once the ESME client disconnects from SMPP server, then bindWatchDog thread when internally tries to connect to it again, this exception appears again as it cannot connect in RX mode.

Test Info Notes:

Two test cases to fix in this CR related to com.hp.usage.smpp plugin.

For ESMEConnector: BIND_RX node.

1)start ESMEConnection without SMPP simulator in started state. Check attempt to reconnect.

Before fix: For BIND_RX mode it should throw IllegalStateException and bindWatchDog thread should die with no further attempt to reconnect.

After Fix: It should try to connect and no exception should be thrown.

2) Once an SMPP sim to client ESMEConnection is established and the connection is dropped as SIM went down. Then when SIM is up again.

Before Fix: There should not be any attempt to rebind to SIM at all.

After fix: The client should again rebind to SIM after it is up.

ID: QXCR1001478052

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

At connection creation time, TCPEndPoint needs to resolve the host name resolving to multiple IP addresses.

Resolution:

The component now resolves the configured host name to IP address at connection creation time.

Submitter Text Notes:

Note the questions in this case refer both to VzW 80FP02 and 8.3 implementations.

APNS connections seem to be notorious for having individual IP addresses taken out of service without notice and without returning to service. At the APNS end the only redundancy provided is that multiple IP addresses are returned in answer to a nameserver query for gateway.push.apple.com (CNAME pointing to multiple IP addresses for gateway.push.apple.com.akadns.net).

Previously, the solution of setting

JVMPROPERTIES=sun.net.inetaddr.ttl=0

to clear java's permanent cache of nameserver answers was given to VzW. However, this solution is untrusted and has not been implemented in production because even with this added, the initial connection pool uses the same IP address for all connections. A simple java program on the same platform will return a different IP each time gethostbyname is called, so the VzW expectation is that the connections should at least use all 8 of the addresses returned from the nameserver query, even if some addresses are used multiple times because there are more than 8 connections.

This has also led to questions about whether a new name lookup is done when a broken connection is revived and a new connection attempt is made.

This distrust is delaying implementation of the sun.net configuration entry. The end customer has recently been impacted twice with APNS IP addresses being taken out of service and the APNS connector being dead for days while continually trying and failing to access the out-of-service IP address. This has raised visibility within VzW and made this a serious issue.

We are asking the VzW team to set up tests to confirm whether or not the sun.net configuration will clear the original problem. They have in tern asked us to confirm the following:

1) Is a name request done between each of the connections being open with the initial pool in the VzW build? I note that this is something we would want to do before each connection is opened in the general release version where we open pool connections as needed (we would not want a new connection opened with a stale DNS result), so if this is not being done prior to any connection being opened it should. If it is being done but the connection loop for VzW is after the request, then VzW is asking that be changed so they start out with a redundancy of routes to APNS.

2) When a connection is revived or reconnection is attempted, is a new DNS request being made?

I have attached the simple java code being used by VzW team to show that the IP addresses vary (using both GetByName and GetAllByName).

Please not that this problem is visible to VzW as an application long-term failure while the APNS is not running due to the bad IP, and that there is no expectation that Apple will provide any redundancy solution on their end.

Test Info Notes:

1) Please find the attached zip file in the CR to get the configs for APNS client and simulator.

2) In order to reproduce the issue, the APNS client or the TCPEndPoint under the TCPConnector needs to be configured with a host name. Now this host name must return different IP address when DNS resolution is done.

Issue: Now at the client side, a remote host is connected,an IP address is fetched from the host name and a connection is created. This connections is used by APNS to send the APNS message. Therefore, once a connection with a particular IP address is created, it is cached to be used later for the same endpoint. However the DNS resolution of the host name to IP address happens at the configuration time. So the same IP is used again and again creating new connections.

So, when the host name changes is IP address, then the existing connections becomes stale as the any further connection to that remote host using old IP doesn't work.

In such case the client can never connect to the remote host and a new IP is never fetched, therefore no further APNS message can be sent to the remote host.

The frequent changing of host name to different happens in Apple's push notification gateways, therefore, APNS component always fails even with new connections.

Fix: To fix this issue, now the DNS resolution of the host name to IP address happens at the creation of the connection in stead of configuration and that resolves the issue. In such case old stale connections will be removed upon failure and new connections with new IP address are used and cached again.

Test Case:

1) Now to test this, we must have a host name returning different IP. This way we can test the scenario.

2) This fix changes the way TCPEndPoint and UDPEndPoint works in creation of connections. I will request a full regression for this CR and it involves changes in connector framework used by other client connectors.

ID: QXCR1001475755

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Popov,Alexey [alexey.popov@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

DiameterTCPTransport and DiameterSCTPTransport can configure two or more addresses for a Diameter node in the HostsMap configuration attribute. The connector used these addresses in an unpredictable order, while connecting to the Diameter node.

Resolution:

Diameter transport components now attempt the first configured address to connect. If the address is not available, they try the second one, and so on.

Submitter Text Notes:

Version: eIUM83VDRA

DiameterTCPTransport and DiameterSCTPTransport may configure 2 or more addresses for a Diameter node in HostsMap configration attribute. The connector should use these addressed in the configured order, while connecting to the DiameterNode.

Let Diameter Client open the connection to this Diameter node and ensure the first IP address is used for connection.

Let the first address unavalible for connection. Ensure that Diameter Client uses the second address for connection.

Repeat the test with DiameterSCTPTransport.

ID: QXCR1001475067

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Steps to reproduce :-

Use the attached smtp.config & smtp_schema.config

1. Configure Subject=%Subject% Content=%Content%

2. Do not pass the values for these 2 arguments in the command line

siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com"

Issue :- 1. It fails with java.lang.IllegalArgumentException. 2. Mail is not sent.

Test Info Notes:

Steps to reproduce :-

1. Configure Subject=%Subject% Content=%Content%

2. Do not pass the values for these 2 arguments in the command line

siuinvoke -n smtpConn -rulechain syncLookup -data ToAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com" FromAddress "rajni.agnihotri@hpe.com"

Issue :- 1. It fails with java.lang.IllegalArgumentException. 2. Mail is not sent.

FIX:

Now both Subject and Content are optional. If no value is passed to the NME attribute configured against these attributes, the corresponding attribute will not be sent with the email.

If both values are missing in NME, then both will be skipped in the email and the email will be sent successfully.

ID: QXCR1001450210

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab only

Engineer: Pavlenko,Andrey [andrey.pavlenko@hpe.com]

Submitter Text Notes:

Using Launchpad (and presumably other GUIs) it is possible to create a node in IUM configuration with raw "/" (slash) in its name (see attached screenshot from Launchpad).

Result of saving such configuration with saveconfig is following:

[/deployment/iumsup-d.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net/ManagementServer]

ClassName=com.hp.siu.managementservice.ManagementProcess ServiceGroups=Management

[/deployment/iumsup-d.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net/ManagementServer/deployment/iumsup-d.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net/ManagementServer/test]

Test=Test

(Here, a node with name "deployment/iumsup-d.ru.tslabs.hpecorp.net/ManagementServer/test" was created under normal ManagementServer node.)

It is obviously not possible to load such configuration back using loadconfig, however it is still possible to read it programmatically from Config object or load with TextFileConfigStore. This leads to very strange errors such as "Could not retrieve [/deployment] node from config".

It is advisable to disallow such incorrect names to appear in the configuration in the first place.

Test Info Notes:

Please check that it's impossible to create a node in IUM configuration where name contains:

    - raw "/", e.g. node with name "aaa/bbb/ccc" or "/ddd/eee"
    - raw "[" and/or "]", e.g. node with name "[ddd" or "eee[fff]"

This check could be performed in Launchpad or IUM Studio.

Resulting configuration saved with saveconfig should not contain any traces of such nodes.

Verifier: 

eIUM83FP01 RC1a
RHEL6 x64
Java 7u80
========================

It was verified that using Launchpad/ConfigEditor it is impossible to create subnode with name
containing "/" in it.

The following exception is thrown to stdout, edited config is saved without such node entered.


[3] 13292

ID: QXCR1001447771

State: Awaiting Release

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Kaur,Sukhwinder Jit [sukhwinder.kaur@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

The LoopRule first retry occurred immediately instead of waiting for the configured RetryDelay.

Resolution:

The component has been fixed to wait for the configured RetryDelay, before every retry attempt.

Submitter Text Notes:

When LoopRule is executed with nonzero RetryCount and RetryDelay, the retry after the initial failure is executed immediately instead of waiting for RetryDelay.

While the documentation states RetryDelay is between retries, it is generally accepted that a retry timer will also be the time between the initial failure and the first retry.

LoopRule.java source confirms that if the first execution fails a second execution is done immediately and we only go to the timer sleep once the second execution fails.

The timer sleep (if configured) should take place after the initial failure.

Test Info Notes:

Test the RetryCount and RetryDelay under LoopRule. Without point patch the first retry happens immediately instead of waiting for the configured RetryDelay. With point patch the first retry should happen only after waiting for RetryDelay.

Run regression for LoopRule.

ID: QXCR1001380567

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Parija,Jimmy [jimmy.parija@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

CCFFileEncapsulator needs to skip the file and move to the next file when exceptions occur while processing an NME from it.

Resolution:

The component now skips the error file and moves to the next file when such an exception occurs. All the NMEs from the error file that are yet to be processed are also discarded.

Submitter Text Notes:

When an NME is processed by rulechains under CCFFileEncapsulator and exception occurs, then CCFFileEncapsulator continues to pick the NMEs from the same file. This behavior needs to change. If an exception happens for an NME from a file in the rule chains, then all the NMEs after that from the same file must be discarded and the encapsulator should move to next file.

Test Info Notes:

Test Steps:

1- Configure a collector and CCFFileEncapsulator under it to decode the input files using CCF and to generate NME from it. 2 - Make a setup in which an exception will be thrown from the rule chains inside aggregator.

3- Please set the flag CleanupOnRuleError= true under CCFFileEncapsulator for this testing.

Test Cases:

Case 1: 1 - Consider, when a file is being decoded using CCFFileEncapsulator and NMEs are generated from it and exception is thrown while processing an NME inside rule chains of aggregator.

Test Result: In the above case either of two situation may happen related to decoding state. Either the file may be getting decoded by the decoder at that time(because the file is large) and some NMEs are already in queue OR the file is completely decoded and all the generated NMEs are in the queue of CCFFileEncapsulator to be processed. In this scenario the CCFFileEncapsulator will not proceed to the next file as all the NMEs from the previous file has not been processed yet.

In either of the case, if an exception happens the following things should happen.

1 - The entire file must be skipped and the collector should roll over to next available file if any.

2- If there are NMEs that belong to that file and that are not yet processed, then they all must be discarded. The CCFFileEncapsulator must not return NMEs that belong to the error file anymore. It must return the first NME of the next available file.

Verifier:

ID: QXCR1001370496

State: Completed

Visibility: Lab, Support & Customer

Engineer: Baikerikar,Vivekananda [vivekananda.baikerikar@hpe.com]

Content Reviewed?: Y

Symptoms:

NME values were not populated when ResultRowRule was absent in the JDBCQuery and DynamicJDBCQuery configuration.

Resolution:

JDBCQuery and DynamicJDBCQuery have been fixed to populate NME values even if ResultRowRule is not configured.

Submitter Text Notes:

NME values are not populated when ResultRowRule is absent in the configuration

Test Info Notes:

This issue occurs with JDBCQuery and DynamicJDBCQuery To reproduce this issue remove the ResultRowRule under JDBCQuery and DynamicJDBCQuery and run the siuinvoke. Without patch the return NME wouldn't have any values With patch the NME should have the values populated.

Also test this Fix for CR QXCR1001367536.

Verifier: 

Test Plan:
=========

Configuration 
and working_jdbc.config for JDBCQuery Configuration.
2. Start the SS and remove resultrow subnode.This configuration can be use as it is and a 
schedular 
exist for invoking rule chain.
3. Verify below mentioned behavior with PP.

DynamicJDBCQuery
